Cadenus and Vanessa is a poem by Jonathan Swift about one of his lovers , Esther Vanhomrigh ( Vanessa ) , written in 1712 and published as a book in 1726 , three years after the death of Vanhomrigh .
Cannibalism in the Cars is a short story written in 1868 by American writer Mark Twain .
At the Crossing Places is the second book in the Arthur trilogy by Kevin Crossley - Holland .
The Historian is the 2005 debut novel of American author Elizabeth Kostova .
Beyond Civilization ( subtitled Humanity 's Next Great Adventure ) is a book by Daniel Quinn written as a non - fiction follow - up to his acclaimed Ishmael trilogy--
The Image of Irelande , with a Discoverie of Woodkarne is a 1581 book by John Derricke .
Isle of Canes ( ISBN 1 - 59331 - 306 - 3 ) , a novel by Elizabeth Shown Mills , follows an African family from its importation and enslavement in 1735 through four generations of freedom in Creole Louisiana to its re - subjugation by Jim Crow at the close of the nineteenth century .
The First Immortal ( 1998 ) is a novel by James L. Halperin about life of a man born in 1925 who dies in 1988 and is re - animated after a cryonics procedure .
Year 's Best SF 8 ( ISBN 0 - 06 - 106453-X ) is a science fiction anthology edited by David G. Hartwell and Kathryn Cramer that was published in 2003 .
The Light Fantastic is a comic fantasy novel by Terry Pratchett , the second of the Discworld series .
The passer - through - walls ( French : Le Passe - muraille ) , translated as The Man Who Walked through Walls , The Walker - through - Walls or The Man who Could Walk through Walls , is a short story published by Marcel Aymé in 1943 .
No Other Life is a novel by Northern Irish - Canadian writer Brian Moore , published in 1993 .
The Generation of Animals ( or On the Generation of Animals ; Greek Περὶ ζῴων γενέσεως ; Latin De Generatione Animalium ) is a text by Aristotle .
The Astounding , the Amazing , and the Unknown is an alternate historical adventure novel written by Paul Malmont , the second book in a series featuring real - life pulp magazine authors of the past as the heroes of adventures reminiscent of their favored genres .
Meyebela , My Bengali Girlhood is a 1998 autobiographical book by Bangladeshi doctor , turned feminist writer Taslima Nasrin .
Study War No More is a science fiction anthology edited by science fiction author and Vietnam War veteran Joe Haldeman .
Mémoires ( Memories ) is an artist 's book made by the Danish artist Asger Jorn in collaboration with the French artist and theorist Guy Debord .
The Tango Singer is a novel by Tomás Eloy Martínez , translated to English by Anne McLean .
Sing to the Dawn is a story by the American author Minfong Ho , which was originally published as a short story and was awarded first prize by the Council of Interracial Books for Children in New York in 1975 .
The Pax Britannica Trilogy comprises three books of history written by Jan Morris , formerly James Morris .
`` The Liberation of Earth '' is a science fiction short story by William Tenn , written in 1950 , first published in 1953 , and reprinted over a dozen times in various anthologies and in 1955 in the William Tenn collection Of all Possible Worlds .
Discworld is a comic fantasy book series written by the English author Terry Pratchett ( 1948 - -2015 ) , set on the fictional Discworld , a flat disc balanced on the backs of four elephants which in turn stand on the back of a giant turtle , Great A'Tuin .
The Suffrage of Elvira is a comic novel by V. S. Naipaul set in colonial Trinidad .
She Has a Name is a play about human trafficking written by Andrew Kooman in 2009 as a single act and expanded to full length in 2010 .
Yoko Tsuno is a comics album series created by the Belgian writer Roger Leloup published by Dupuis in Spirou magazine since its debut in 1970 .
Beyond the Mexique Bay is a travel book by Aldous Huxley , first published in 1934 .
Mostly Harmless is a novel by Douglas Adams and the fifth book in the Hitchhiker 's Guide to the Galaxy series .
The History of the Lombards or the History of the Langobards ( Latin : Historia Langobardorum ) is the chief work by Paul the Deacon , written in the late 8th century .
Internet and Technology Law Desk Reference is a non - fiction book about information technology law , written by Michael Dennis Scott .
Jeevanko Chheubaata ( Nepali : जीवनको छेउबाट ) is the second collection of poetry in Nepali by internationally recognized and award - winning Nepali poet Suman Pokhrel , published by Vaani Publication , Nepal in December 2009 .
Between Mom and Jo is an American young adult novel by Julie Anne Peters , published in 2006 .
`` Byomjatrir Diary '' ( Bengali : ব্যোমযাত্রীর ডায়রি , The Spaceman 's Diary ) was the first story of Professor Shanku series by Indian writer Satyajit Ray .
`` The Tractate Middoth '' is a short ghost story by British author M. R. James .
The House on the Borderland and Other Novels is a collection of short novels by author William Hope Hodgson .
Artifact of Evil is a fantasy novel by Gary Gygax , set in the world of Greyhawk , which is based on the Dungeons & Dragons fantasy role - playing game .
Cart and Cwidder is a fantasy novel for young adults by the British author Diana Wynne Jones .
Against Eratosthenes is a speech by Lysias , one of the ten Attic orators .
A Scrap of Time and Other Stories , written by Ida Fink , is a collection of fictional short stories relating various characters to the Jewish experience of the Holocaust .
Pelléas and Mélisande ( French : Pelléas et Mélisande ) is a Symbolist play by Maurice Maeterlinck about the forbidden , doomed love of the title characters .
Our Exploits At West Poley is short story by Thomas Hardy which he wrote in 1892 - -3 , subtitled `` a story for boys '' .
The Freebooter of the Baltic ( Swedish : Fribytaren på Östersjön , 1857 ) is an early novel by the Swedish romantic novelist Viktor Rydberg .
Monster Manual III was published in 2004 , and was designed by Rich Burlew , Eric Cagle , Jesse Decker , Andrew J. Finch , Gwendolyn F.M. Kestrel , Rich Redman , Matthew Sernett , Chris Thomasson , and P. Nathan Toomey .
The Long Secret is a children 's novel written and illustrated by Louise Fitzhugh that was released by Harper & Row on October 27 , 1965 .
The Mughal Harem is a book by historian K. S. Lal published in 1988 .
In the Tall Grass is a novella written by Stephen King and his son Joe Hill .
`` N'avoue jamais '' ( `` Never admit '' ) was the French entry in the Eurovision Song Contest 1965 , performed in French by Guy Mardel .
The Merry Wives of Windsor is a comedy by William Shakespeare , first published in 1602 , though believed to have been written prior to 1597 .
Combat avec l'ange ( Struggle with the Angel ) is a novel by French playwright and novelist Jean Giraudoux and published by éditions Grasset in 1934 .
Borstal Boy is a 1958 autobiographical book by Brendan Behan .
I Am Not Sidney Poitier is a 2009 novel written by Percival Everett .
Warrior Scarlet ( 1958 ) is a historical novel by Rosemary Sutcliff .
Preserve and Protect is a 1968 political novel written by Allen Drury .
Why I Am Not a Christian is an essay by the British philosopher Bertrand Russell .
Hermeneutic Communism : from Heidegger to Marx is a 2011 book of political philosophy by Gianni Vattimo and Santiago Zabala .
Bones of Faerie is a young adult fantasy novel by Janni Lee Simner , first published in 2009 .
The Daughter of Time is a 1951 detective novel by Josephine Tey , concerning a modern police officer 's investigation into the alleged crimes of King Richard III of England .
Les Cités obscures ( literally The Obscure Cities , but initially published in English as Cities of the Fantastic ) is a graphic novel series set on a Counter - Earth , started by the Belgian comics artist François Schuiten and his friend , writer Benoît Peeters in the early 1980s .
My Utmost for His Highest is a daily devotional by Oswald Chambers ( 1874 - 1917 ) that compiles his Christian preaching to students and soldiers .
Barbarian Odes ( Italian : Odi barbare ) is a collection of three books of poetry by Giosuè Carducci , published between 1877 and 1889 .
`` The Heart of a Broken Story '' is a short story by J. D. Salinger , published in the September 1941 issue of Esquire .
When the Devil Dances is the third book in John Ringo 's Legacy of the Aldenata series .
You Shall Know Our Velocity ! is a 2002 novel by Dave Eggers .
Yellow Back Radio Broke - Down , by the African - American writer Ishmael Reed , is a satirical take on the traditional Western .
Pale Horse Coming ( ISBN 0 - 684 - 86361 - 8 ) is a novel by Stephen Hunter published in 2001 .
I Had Trouble in Getting to Solla Sollew is a 1965 children 's book by Dr. Seuss .
The Widows of Eastwick is the final novel by John Updike , author of the Pulitzer - prize winning `` Rabbit '' series .
The Sky People is an alternate history science fiction novel by American writer S. M. Stirling .
Damini Bhir ( also spelled Damini Bheer or दमिनी भीर ) is a Nepali novel by Rajan Mukarung which won the Madan Puraskar for 2012 .
The Stupids are a fictional family which appear in a series of children 's books written by Harry Allard and James Marshall .
Abhorsen is a fantasy novel by Australian writer Garth Nix , first published in 2003 .
The Butterfly that Stamped is part of a series of books known as Just So Stories by Rudyard Kipling .
The Best Halloween Ever ! is a book by Barbara Robinson .
Cicero 's Divinatio in Caecilium is his oration against Quintus Caecilius in the process for selecting a prosecutor of Gaius Verres ( 70 BCE ) .
Aunt Jane 's Nieces at Millville is a 1908 young - adult novel written by L. Frank Baum , famous as the creator of the Land of Oz . It is the third volume in `` the successful Aunt Jane Series , '' following Aunt Jane 's Nieces and Aunt Jane 's Nieces Abroad .
Haunted Mesa is a science fiction novel by Louis L'Amour , set in the American Southwest amidst the ruins of the Anasazi .
Rumo and His Miraculous Adventures is a fantasy novel , written and comically illustrated by German author Walter Moers .
Princeps ' Fury is a 2008 high fantasy novel by Jim Butcher .
Of Time and the River ( subtitled A Legend of Man 's Hunger in his Youth ) is a 1935 novel by American novelist Thomas Wolfe .
A Talent for War is a science fiction and mystery novel by Jack McDevitt , the story of a search by Alex Benedict , the protagonist , to discover the nature of a mysterious project Alex 's uncle had been working on at the time of his death .
The Other Boleyn Girl ( 2001 ) is a historical novel written by British author Philippa Gregory , loosely based on the life of 15th - century aristocrat Mary Boleyn , the sister of Anne Boleyn , of whom little is known .
Trading Secrets ( French : Confidence pour confidence ) is a 1998 novel by the French writer Paule Constant .
The Mirror and the Light is an upcoming historical novel by Hilary Mantel , the final part of a planned trilogy charting the rise and fall of Thomas Cromwell , the powerful minister in the court of King Henry VIII .
Historia de la eternidad ( in English : A History of Eternity ) is the first essay book published by Argentine author Jorge Luis Borges , in 1936 ( editio princeps ) .
Dune Messiah is a science fiction novel by Frank Herbert , the second in his Dune series of six novels .
Autumn Visits is a science fiction novel by Sergey Lukyanenko , published in 1997 in book form .
Ten Thousand a - Year is a novel written by English barrister Samuel Warren .
The Man Who Turned Into A Stick(棒になった男 -- Bō ni natta otoko ) is a one - act play written in 1957 by Kōbō Abe .
The Silent Traveller in London is a 1938 book by the Chinese author Chiang Yee .
Leather - Nose ( French : Nez - de - Cuir ) is a 1936 novel by the French writer Jean de La Varende , about Achille Perrier de La Genevraye , an officer during the Napoleonic Wars and the author 's grand uncle .
Old Man 's War is a military science fiction and debut novel by John Scalzi published in 2005 .
The Astronauts ( in Polish Astronauci ) is the first science fiction novel by Polish writer Stanisław Lem published as a book , in 1951 .
Mythago Wood is a fantasy novel written by Robert Holdstock that was published in the United Kingdom in 1984 .
The Lords of Strategy is a book by Walter Kiechel III , a business journalist , former Editorial Director of the Harvard Business Review and former Managing Editor of Fortune magazine , which presents the analysis of strategy evolution since the 1960s .
`` The Doctor 's Case '' is a short story by American author Stephen King , originally published in The New Adventures of Sherlock Holmes , a 1987 centennial collection , and reprinted in his collection Nightmares & Dreamscapes .
The War in Eastern Europe is a book that describes John Reed 's second trip after the first World War broke out .
Men of Iron is an 1891 novel by the American author Howard Pyle , who also illustrated it .
The Gospel of the Flying Spaghetti Monster is a religious book written by Bobby Henderson that embodies the main beliefs of the religion the Church of the Flying Spaghetti Monster or Pastafarianism .
Girl Got Game , originally published in Japan as Power ! ! , is a manga series written and illustrated by Shizuru Seino .
`` Big Game Hunt '' is a science fiction short story by Arthur C. Clarke , first published in 1956 .
`` Ulalume '' is a poem written by Edgar Allan Poe in 1847 .
Trigger Mortis is a 2015 James Bond novel written by Anthony Horowitz , and the latest Bond novel to be commissioned by the estate of Bond 's creator Ian Fleming , which was published on 8 September 2015 .
Atomic Lobster is the tenth novel by Tim Dorsey .
The Dangerous Journey ( Orig . Swedish Den farliga resan ) is a children 's picture book in the Moomin series by Tove Jansson .
No More Dead Dogs is a novel by Gordon Korman published in 2002 .
A Mind at Peace ( Archipelago Books , 2008 and 2011 ; English translation by Erdağ Göknar of Huzur , 1949 ) is an iconic Turkish novel by Ahmet Hamdi Tanpınar ( 1901 - -62 ) , one of the pioneers of literary modernism in Turkey .
`` The Shadow of the Vulture '' is a short story by American writer Robert E. Howard , first published in The Magic Carpet Magazine , January 1934 .
A Natural History of the Senses is a 1990 non - fiction book by American author , poet , and naturalist Diane Ackerman .
On Liberty is a philosophical work by English philosopher John Stuart Mill , originally intended as a short essay .
Dogsong is a 1985 young adult novel by Gary Paulsen and is a Newbery Honor Book winner .
The Definitive Biography of P.D.Q. Bach ( 1807 - -1742 ) ? is a book by Prof . Peter Schickele chronicling the life of fictitious composer P. D. Q. Bach .
American Conspiracies is a book written by former Governor of Minnesota Jesse Ventura , together with Dick Russell .
The Bad Girl , originally published in 2006 in Spanish as Travesuras de la niña mala , is a novel by Peruvian author Mario Vargas Llosa , who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 2010 .
Do n't Look Behind You is a 1990 young adult thriller novel by Lois Duncan .
The Legend of the Holy Drinker ( German : Die Legende vom heiligen Trinker ) is a 1939 novella by the Austrian writer Joseph Roth , published posthumously by Allert de Lange Verlag in Amsterdam .
Dark Visions is a 1989 horror fiction compilation , with three short stories by Stephen King , three by Dan Simmons , and one by George R. R. Martin .
`` The Village Blacksmith '' is a poem by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow , first published in 1840 .
The Bagford Ballads were English ballads collected by John Bagford ( 1651 - 1716 ) for Robert Harley , first Earl of Oxford .
The Silver Cloud Café ( 1996 ) is the second novel by Alfredo Véa , Jr ..
National Velvet is a novel by Enid Bagnold ( 1889 - -1981 ) , first published in 1935 .
Le Paysan de Paris is a surrealist book about places in Paris by Louis Aragon which was first published in 1926 by Editions Gallimard .
By Grand Central Station I Sat Down and Wept is a novel of prose poetry written by the Canadian author Elizabeth Smart ( 1913 - -1986 ) and published in 1945 .
Dread Jesus , published in 1999 , is a book written by William David Spencer about the Rastafari movement .
Dangerous Angels is a young adult fiction series by Francesca Lia Block .
Cynegeticus ( Greek : Κυνηγετικός , Kynegetikos `` related to hunting '' from κυνηγέω `` I hunt '' ) , is a treatise by the ancient Greek philosopher and military leader Xenophon , usually translated as `` On Hunting '' or `` Hunting with Dogs . ''
Faro 's Daughter is a Georgian romance novel by Georgette Heyer which was first published in 1941 .
`` Hell - Fire '' is a science fiction short story by American writer Isaac Asimov , originally published in the May 1956 issue of Fantastic Universe and reprinted in the 1957 collection Earth Is Room Enough .
A Topographical Dictionary of Ancient Rome is a reference work written by Samuel Ball Platner and completed by Thomas Ashby after Platner 's death that was published in 1929 by Oxford University Press .
Historia de Belgrano y de la Independencia Argentina ( in Spanish , History of Belgrano and of the Independence of Argentina ) is an Argentine history book written by Bartolomé Mitre .
The Days of the Commune is a play by the twentieth - century German dramatist Bertolt Brecht .
Pontypool Changes Everything is a novel by Tony Burgess , first published in 1995 .
Honeymoon in Hell is a science fiction short story by Fredric Brown , first published in 1950 .
The Dictionnaire des ouvrages anonymes et pseudonymes is a four volume ( 1806 - -1809 ) dictionary by Antoine Alexandre Barbier listing pen names for French and Latin authors .
Amaze Your Friends is a 1998 Ned Kelly Award - winning novel by Australian author Peter Doyle .
Jeremy Thatcher , Dragon Hatcher is a novel by Bruce Coville and is part of the Magic Shop Books .
Twentieth Century Eightball is a book collection of comics by Daniel Clowes published by Fantagraphics Books in 2002 .
Just David is a 1916 children 's novel by Eleanor H. Porter .
Mexico City Blues is a poem published by Jack Kerouac in 1959 composed of 242 `` choruses '' or stanzas .
The Rowan ( 1990 ) is the first book in `` The Tower and the Hive '' series ( also known as `` The Rowan '' series ) by Anne McCaffrey .
The Hipster Handbook ( 2003 ) is a satirical guide to hipster culture by Williamsburg , Brooklyn author Robert Lanham .
Lucien Leuwen is the second major novel written by French author Stendhal in 1834 , following The Red and the Black ( 1830 ) .
The scene of Gump running across the country is often referred to when real - life people attempt the feat . Ildikó Mádl ( born 5 November 1969 in Tapolca ) is a Hungarian chess player who holds the FIDE titles of Internationl Master ( IM ) and Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) .

My Six Convicts is the true story of a prison psychologist ( John Beal ) and his attempts to get through to his incarcerated patients .

Innamorato pazzo , internationally released as Madly in Love , is a 1981 Italian romantic comedy film , starring Adriano Celentano and Ornella Muti .

Sunshine Reggae in Ibiza ( German : Sunshine Reggae auf Ibiza ) is a 1983 West German comedy film directed by Franz Marischka and starring Karl Dall , Olivia Pascal and Chris Roberts .

The Life of Shakespeare is a 1914 British silent biographical film directed by Frank R. Growcott and J.B. McDowell and starring Albert Ward , Sybil Hare and George Foley .

Maciste the Athlete ( Italian : Maciste atleta ) is a 1918 Italian silent film directed by Vincenzo Denizot and Giovanni Pastrone and starring Bartolomeo Pagano .
Henry Browne , Farmer is an American short propaganda film produced in 1942 about African - American contributions to the war effort during World War II . It is narrated by Canada Lee .
Man in the Dark is a 1953 film noir drama 3-D film directed by Lew Landers and starring Edmond O'Brien , Audrey Totter and Ted de Corsia .

Golpo Holeo Shotti ( Bengali : গল্প হলেও সত্যি ; English : A story , but true ) is an Indian Bengali suspense supernatural thriller film directed by Birsa Dasgupta , produced by Shree Venkatesh Films , starring Soham Chakraborty and Mimi Chakraborty .
Odipolama ( English : Shall we elope ? ) is a 2009 Indian Tamil romantic film directed by Kanmani , starring newcomer , Parimal and Sandhya in the lead roles , whilst , Kota Srinivasa Rao plays a pivotal role .

Rathri Mazha is a Malayalam film by Lenin Rajendran starring Vineeth and Meera Jasmine in lead roles .

The Spanish Main ( 1945 ) is an adventure film starring Paul Henreid , Maureen O'Hara , Walter Slezak and Binnie Barnes , and directed by Frank Borzage .

Hot Property is a Channel 5 show originally broadcast from 1997 to 1998 and hosted by Sandy Mitchell .
Ambush Valley is a 1936 American western directed by Bernard B. Ray , produced by Ray and Harry S. Webb for Reliable Pictures , starring Bob Custer and Victoria Vinton .

Maria Pypelinckx ( 20 March 1538 -- 19 October 1608 ) was a writer from the Southern Netherlands , best known today as the mother of the painter Peter Paul Rubens .

Sous Lieutenant Fernand Henri Chavannes was a World War I flying ace credited with seven aerial victories .

Richard J. Nolan ( January 1 , 1848 -- August 26 , 1905 ) served in the United States Army during the American Indian Wars .
Henry Capehart ( March 18 , 1825 -- April 15 , 1895 ) was a surgeon and officer in the U.S. Cavalry during the American Civil War .
Charles Frederick Ehret ( died February 24 , 2007 ) was a World War II veteran ( Battle of the Bulge / Ardennes along the Siegfried Line ) as well as a world - renowned molecular biologist who worked at Argonne National Laboratory ( ANL ) in Lemont , Illinois , USA , for 40 years .
Ecaterina Teodoroiu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( ekateˈrina te.odoˈroju ) ; born Cătălina Toderoiu ; January 15 , 1894 - September 3 , 1917 ) was a Romanian woman who fought and died in World War I , and is regarded as a heroine of Romania .
The United Defense M42 was issued for use by Filipino troops under the Philippine Army and Philippine Constabulary during World War II from 1942 through the Post - World War II era until the 1960s and was used by the local recognized guerrillas from 1942 to 1945 during the Japanese Occupation .
Georges Guynemer ( 24 December 1894 -- 11 September 1917 missing ) was a top fighter ace for France during World War I , and a French national hero at the time of his death .
Antonio Cantore ( Sampierdarena , 4 August 1860 -- Tofana di Rozes , 20 July 1915 ) was an Italian general , active in World War I , for which he was awarded the gold medal for military valour .

David Hunter ( July 21 , 1802 -- February 2 , 1886 ) was a Union general during the American Civil War .
Thornsbury Bailey Brown ( May 15 , 1829 -- May 22 , 1861 ) of Taylor County , Virginia ( now West Virginia ) is generally considered the first Union soldier killed by a Confederate soldier during the American Civil War .
Jean - Toussaint Arrighi de Casanova ( born 8 March 1778 in Corte ; died 22 March 1853 in Paris ) , duc de Padova , was a French diplomat and soldier of the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars .

USS Theta ( 1864 ) was a steamer purchased by the Union Navy during the latter years of the American Civil War .
Tau Tauri ( τ Tau , τ Tauri ) is a triple star system in the constellation Taurus .
NGC 121 is a globular cluster in the Small Magellanic Cloud , in the constellation of Tucana .
IC 2220 , also known as the Toby Jug Nebula , is a reflection nebula located 1200 light years away in the southern constellation of Carina .
Gamma Serpentis ( γ Serpentis , γ Ser ) is a star in the equatorial constellation Serpens , in the part of the constellation that represents the serpent 's head ( Serpens Caput ) .
LP 944 - 20 is a dim brown dwarf of spectral class M9 located about 21 light - years from the Solar System in the constellation of Fornax .
HD 171028 is a yellow main - sequence star in the constellation of Ophiuchus .
HD 38529 b is an extrasolar planet approximately 138 light years away in the constellation of Orion .
NGC 4565 ( also known as the Needle Galaxy or Caldwell 38 ) is an edge - on spiral galaxy about 30 to 50 million light - years away in the constellation Coma Berenices .
Abell 665 is a galaxy cluster in the Abell catalogue in the constellation Ursa Major .
49 Ceti ' is a main sequence A1V star of magnitude 5.62 located in Cetus .
NGC 5286 , also known as Caldwell 84 , is a globular cluster of stars located some 35,900 light years away in the constellation Centaurus .
SGR 1806 - 20 is located about 14.5 kiloparsecs ( 50,000 light - years ) from Earth on the far side of the Milky Way galaxy in the constellation of Sagittarius .
Messier 56 ( also known as M56 or NGC 6779 ) is a globular cluster in the constellation Lyra .
Abell 370 is a galaxy cluster located approximately 6 billion light - years away from the Earth ( at redshift z = 0.375 ) , in the constellation Cetus .
HD 158476 is a supergiant star in the southern constellation of Ara .
NGC 2232 is a bright open star cluster in the constellation Monoceros centred on the star 10 Monocerotis .
The M101 Group is a loose group of galaxies located in Ursa Major .
35 Arietis ( abbreviated 35 Ari ) is a binary star in the northern constellation of Aries .
BD + 20 ° 307 is a close binary star system approximately 300 light - years away in the constellation Aries .
Messier 5 or M5 ( also designated NGC 5904 ) is a globular cluster in the constellation Serpens .
The Calabash Nebula , also known as the Rotten Egg Nebula or by its technical name OH 231.84 + 4.22 , is a protoplanetary nebula ( PPN ) 1.4 light years ( 13 Pm ) long and located some 5,000 light years ( 47 Em ) from Earth in the constellation Puppis .
NGC 2452 is a planetary nebula located in the southern constellation of Puppis .
The Rosette Nebula ( also known as Caldwell 49 ) is a large , circular H II region located near one end of a giant molecular cloud in the Monoceros region of the Milky Way Galaxy .
NGC 4236 ( also known as Caldwell 3 ) is a barred spiral galaxy located in the constellation Draco .
Theta Ceti ( θ Ceti , θ Cet ) is a Class K0 , fourth - magnitude star in the constellation Cetus .
Kepler-68c is an Earth - sized planet orbiting the star Kepler-68 in the constellation of Cygnus .
HD 126271 is a suspected variable star in the northern constellation of Boötes .
NGC 5746 is a barred spiral galaxy located in the eastern part of the constellation of Virgo , and it can be seen with amateur telescopes .
HD 153370 is binary star in the southern constellation of Ara .
PZ Telescopii , also known as HD 174429 or simply PZ Tel , is a young star in the constellation Telescopium .
41 Lyncis ( abbreviated 41 Lyn ) , also designated HD 81688 and named Intercrus , is a fifth magnitude star located in the northern constellation of Ursa Major .
HR 3220 ( B Car ) is a single - lined spectroscopic binary in the constellation Carina , approximately 65 light years from Earth .
Gamma Ceti ( γ Cet , γ Ceti ) is a star system in the equatorial constellation Cetus .
26 Aquarii ( abbreviated 26 Aqr ) is a star in the constellation of Aquarius .
Epidote Peak ( 84 ° 46′S 176 ° 56′W ) is a prominent rock peak just north of the mouth of Held Glacier , overlooking the west side of Shackleton Glacier in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
The Klumpane Peaks are a group of small rock peaks on the east side of the mouth of Strengen Valley , on the Ahlmann Ridge in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Hewitt Glacier ( 83 ° 17′S 167 ° 50′E ) is a glacier , 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) long , descending the eastern slopes of the Holland Range , Antarctica , between Lewis Ridge and Mount Tripp to enter Richards Inlet .
Howchin South Stream ( 78 ° 13′S 163 ° 25′E ) is a meltwater stream draining from the south side of Howchin Glacier in the Denton Hills , Scott Coast , Antarctica .
Marshall Cirque ( 78 ° 5′S 167 ° 16′E ) is an ice - filled cirque , 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) wide , located 1 nautical mile southwest of Kienle Cirque on the west side of White Island , in the Ross Archipelago , Antarctica .
Shackleton Coast is that portion of the coast along the west side of the Ross Ice Shelf between Cape Selborne and Airdrop Peak at the east side of Beardmore Glacier in Antarctica .
Hannon Hill ( 77 ° 50′S 163 ° 39′E ) is a bare rock hill , 1,110 metres ( 3,640 ft ) high , on the west side of the terminus of Amos Glacier , at the juncture with Blue Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Greenville Hole ( 76 ° 43′S 160 ° 58′E ) is a circular depression , 200 metres ( 660 ft ) deep , in the center of Greenville Valley , Convoy Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mossman Inlet ( 73 ° 17′S 60 ° 32′W ) is a narrow ice - filled inlet which recedes north 19 kilometres ( 10 nmi ) between Cape Kidson and the southwest end of Kemp Peninsula , along the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Although it is a small town , Segrate hosts large structures such as the CILEA Interuniversity Consortium , among the most advanced supercomputing centers in Europe , and the San Raffaele Hospital .
Lehrke Inlet ( 70 ° 49′S 61 ° 45′W ) is an ice - filled inlet , 15 kilometres ( 8 nmi ) wide , which recedes southwest for 31 kilometres ( 17 nmi ) between Cape Boggs and Cape Sharbonneau , along the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Hodge Escarpment ( 83 ° 3′S 50 ° 11′W ) is an escarpment to the northeast of Henderson Bluff on the northwest side of Lexington Table , in the Forrestal Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Mount Queequeg ( 65 ° 39′S 62 ° 8′W ) is a conspicuous , partly snow - covered mountain with three conical summits , the highest 900 m , situated in eastern Aristotle Mountains between the mouths of Starbuck and Stubb Glaciers on the east coast of Graham Land in Antarctica .
The Antarctic Plate is a tectonic plate containing the continent of Antarctica and extending outward under the surrounding oceans .
Potmess Rocks is a group of large rocks lying northwest of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Tunisia ( Arabic : تونس‎ Tūnis ; Berber : ⵜⵓⵏⴻⵙ ) , officially the Tunisian Republic or the Republic of Tunisia ( Arabic : الجمهورية التونسية‎ al - Jumhūrīya at - Tūnisīya ; Berber : ⵜⴰⴳⴷⵓⴷⴰ ⵏ ⵜⵓⵏⴻⵙ ) is the northernmost country in Africa , covering 165,000 square kilometres ( 64,000 sq mi ) .
Director Nunatak ( 66 ° 49′S 65 ° 6′W ) is a conspicuous nunatak standing between the heads of Balch Glacier and Breitfuss Glacier , in Graham Land in Antarctica .
Kramer Island is an ice - covered island , 4 kilometres ( 2 nmi ) long , in the Marshall Archipelago , Antarctica .
Zavera Snowfield ( Bulgarian : Ледник Завера , `` Lednik Zavera '' \'led - nik za-'ve - ra\ ) is the glacier extending 18 km in north - south direction and 16 km in east - west direction on southern Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Gleaner Heights ( 62 ° 35′S 60 ° 15′W ) are a series of elevations extending southwest from Leslie Hill in the eastern part of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Cape Denison is a rocky point at the head of Commonwealth Bay in Antarctica .
Hinkley Glacier ( 78 ° 27′S 85 ° 20′W ) is a glacier flowing northeastward from Corbet Peak and Schoening Peak , Vinson Massif on the east slope of Sentinel Range in the Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica , and continuing between Mount Segers and Zinsmeister Ridge to enter Dater Glacier southeast of Nebeska Peak and northwest of Sipey Peak .
Burkitt Nunatak is a small nunatak , rising to about 1,200 m ( 3,900 ft ) high , located in the north - west part of Dyer Plateau , 17 km ( 11 mi ) west - southwest of Crescent Scarp , Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Cape Klovstad ( 71 ° 39′S 170 ° 6′E ) is a rugged rock point between Colbeck Bay and Protection Cove in the southern part of Robertson Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Karposh Point ( Bulgarian : нос Карпош , `` Nos Karposh '' \'nos ' kar - posh\ ) is the ice - free point on the north coast of Snow Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Cook Mountains is a group of mountains bounded by the Mulock and Darwin glaciers in Antarctica .
Barton Peninsula is a small peninsula separating Marian Cove and Potter Cove at the southwest end of King George Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
The Johannessen Nunataks ( 72 ° 52′S 161 ° 11′E ) are an isolated , ridgelike outcropping of rocks about 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) long , standing 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) south of Mount Weihaupt in the southern extremity of the Outback Nunataks , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Lippert Peak ( 79 ° 59′S 81 ° 56′W ) is a sharp pointed peak at the end of a ridge that extends west from the Douglas Peaks into Horseshoe Valley , located 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) southeast of Strong Peak ( which this peak resembles ) in the Heritage Range , Antarctica .
Marck Glacier ( 72 ° 16′S 97 ° 2′W ) is a glacier flowing into the southwestern extremity of Cadwalader Inlet on the north side of Thurston Island , Antarctica .
Ibarra Peak ( 77 ° 58′S 162 ° 58′E ) is the summit at the extremity of the ridge which extends eastwards from the Royal Society Range between Mitchell Glacier and Lister Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Hampton Ridge is a ridge about 10 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long in the Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica , running north from Pagoda Peak between Montgomerie Glacier and Mackellar Glacier .
Mac . Robertson Land is the portion of Antarctica lying southward of the coast between William Scoresby Bay and Cape Darnley .
Sredorek Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Средорек , `` Vrah Sredorek '' \'vr&h sre - do-'rek\ ) is the peak rising to 1224 m in Korten Ridge east of Kasabova Glacier and west of Sabine Glacier on Davis Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Hedblom Glacier ( 76 ° 34′S 162 ° 24′E ) is a glacier between Mount Creak and Tito Peak that flows east from Endeavour Massif to Tripp Ice Tongue , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Kakure Rocks ( 67 ° 57′S 44 ° 47′E ) are two rocky exposures along the east wall of Shinnan Glacier , at the western extremity of Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Luhrsen Nunatak ( 71 ° 59′S 161 ° 41′E ) is a nunatak 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south - southeast of Mount Alford at the southeast end of the Helliwell Hills , Antarctica .
Sultan Glacier is a glacier flowing south - west into Table Bay , Elephant Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Douanier Rock is a small rocky island lying close to the coast and just east of Point Alden , Antarctica , the point which separates Adélie Coast and George V Coast .
Kellogg Valley ( 77 ° 29′S 161 ° 11′E ) is a high ( 1,400 metres ( 4,600 ft ) ) hanging valley , for the most part free of ice , between Mount Boreas and Mount Aeolus in the Olympus Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Fitzmaurice Point is a point on the northwest side of Cabinet Inlet , Foyn Coast , Antarctica , between Attlee Glacier and Bevin Glacier .
Fitch Glacier ( 72 ° 1′S 168 ° 7′E ) is a tributary glacier flowing south along the east side of the McGregor Range to enter Man - o - War Glacier in the Admiralty Mountains of northeastern Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Malawi ( /məˈlɔːwi/ , /məˈlɑːwi/ or /ˈmæləwi/ ; Chichewa : ( maláβi ) or ( maláwi ) ) , officially the Republic of Malawi , is a landlocked country in southeast Africa that was formerly known as Nyasaland .
The Astor Rocks ( 71 ° 48′S 12 ° 44′E ) are two small rock outcrops lying 4 miles ( 6 km ) southeast of Mount Ramenskiy in the southeast extremity of the Wohlthat Mountains of Antarctica .
Arthurson Bluff ( 70 ° 45′S 166 ° 5′E ) is a mostly ice - covered bluff overlooking the confluence of Ludvig Glacier and Kirkby Glacier from the west , near the north coast of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Greenville Valley ( 76 ° 44′S 160 ° 52′E ) is the large mainly ice - free valley lying south of Elkhorn Ridge in the Convoy Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Eastwind Ridge ( 76 ° 36′S 160 ° 47′E ) is a broad , partially ice - covered ridge about 10 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long between Chattahoochee Glacier and Towle Glacier in the Convoy Range of Antarctica .
Harrison Passage ( 65 ° 53′S 65 ° 11′W ) is a passage between Larrouy Island and Tadpole Island to the west , and the Llanquihue Islands and the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica , to the east .
Hawker Island is an irregularly shaped island about 2 km ( 1.2 mi ) long , lying some 7 km south - west of Davis Station between Mule Island and Mule Peninsula , Vestfold Hills , in the eastern part of Prydz Bay , Antarctica .
Victoria Upper Glacier ( 77 ° 16′S 161 ° 25′E ) is a glacier occupying the upper northwest end of Victoria Valley in Antarctica .
Mitterling Glacier ( 66 ° 50′S 64 ° 18′W ) is a glacier on the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica , draining between Mount Vartdal and Mount Hayes into the northern part of Mill Inlet .
Forlidas Ridge ( 82 ° 29′S 51 ° 16′W ) is a rock ridge that forms the west side of Davis Valley in the Dufek Massif , Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Mouillard Glacier ( 64 ° 18′S 60 ° 53′W ) is a glacier flowing into the southeast corner of Brialmont Cove , on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Gran Glacier ( 76 ° 56′S 161 ° 14′E ) is a glacier in Antarctica that flows south into Mackay Glacier between Mount Gran and Mount Woolnough .
The Darwin Mountains is a group of mountains between the Darwin and Hatherton glaciers in Antarctica .
The Sverdrup Mountains ( Norwegian : Sverdrupfjella ) are a group of mountains about 50 miles ( 80 km ) long , standing just west of the Gjelsvik Mountains in Queen Maud Land , East Antarctica .

Kista Strait ( 67 ° 35′S 62 ° 51′E ) is a strait between the Flat Islands and Jocelyn Islands in Holme Bay , Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .

Edmund Joseph Sullivan ( 1869 - -1933 ) , usually known as E. J. Sullivan , was a British book illustrator who worked in a style which merged the British tradition of illustration from the 1860s with aspects of Art Nouveau .

Lydia Thompson , born Eliza Hodges Thompson ( 19 February 1838 -- 17 November 1908 ) , was an English dancer , comedian , actress and theatrical producer .
Alan Brogan ( born 11 January 1982 ) is a Gaelic footballer from the St Oliver Plunketts / Eoghan Ruadh club who played inter - county with Dublin from 2002 until his retirement in 2015 .
Goran Ješić ( Serbian : Горан Јешић ; born 3 August 1974 in Sremska Mitrovica , SFR Yugoslavia ) is the Vice President of the Democratic Party in Serbia and was the Vice President of the Government of Vojvodina from 2012 to 2014 .
Emily Dubberley ( born 1974 , Cheltenham ) is a British author and journalist specialising in sex and relationships .
Walter Jon Williams ( born 1953 ) is an American writer , primarily of science fiction .
Tenshin Zenki Reb Anderson ( born 1943 ) is a Zen teacher and lineage holder in the Sōtō Zen tradition of Shunryu Suzuki .
Neil Abel ( born 22 December 1960 in Kirkcaldy , Fife , Scotland , United Kingdom ) is a British professional ice hockey player who has played in the United Kingdom since 1980 .
Brian McConaghy ( born 1963 ) is the founder of Ratanak International and a former Canadian forensic scientist who left the Royal Canadian Mounted Police ( RCMP ) in order to dedicate all his energies to ending child abuse and human trafficking in Cambodia .
Stanley Glasser ( born 28 February 1926 ) , is a South African - born composer and academic who studied with Matyas Seiber at Cambridge .
Mike Süsser ( born 8 January 1971 in Itzehoe ) is a German chef and author .
Asoke Kumar Mukerji ( born December 1955 ) is an Indian diplomat and writer .
Richard Foulkes ( born 1902 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a right half .
Tom Gleisner ( born 1962 ) is an Australian director , producer , writer , comedian , occasional actor and author .
Annabel Chong ( born 22 May 1972 ) is the stage name of a Singaporean - born American former pornographic film actress who became famous after starring in an adult film that was promoted as The World 's Biggest Gang Bang .
Agni Sapkota ( born 7 March 1960 , Sindhupalchok , Kubinde ) is a Nepalese politician .
Edmund , 2nd Earl of Kent ( 1326 -- before 5 October 1331 ) was a member of the English royal family .

Desmond Rex Williams ( born 20 July 1933 ) , son of Minnie Roberts and William Williams , is a retired English professional snooker and billiards player .
Theodor Bull ( 1870 -- 1958 ) was a Norwegian businessperson and genealogist .
John Leeson ( born 16 March 1943 ) is a British actor who is best known for voicing K-9 on the television series Doctor Who from 1977 to 1979 , then from 1980 to 1981 , and has returned for two single episode in the revived series .
Jeffrey Paul Smith ( born 1956 ) is an attorney , community organizer , and political activist from Illinois who is known for advocacy of progressive , reform , and independent causes .
Srđan Radovanović ( born 1959 ) is a Serbian lawyer and business executive .
Antoine Aureche ( born 4 December 1981 ) is a French musician : guitarist , singer , electro producer and composer .

Vojtěch Kubašta ( 1914 , Vienna -- 1992 ) was a Czech architect and artist .
Charles Samuel Myers , CBE , FRS ( 13 March 1873 -- 12 October 1946 ) was an English physician who worked as a psychologist .
William Warren Orcutt ( February 14 , 1869 -- 1942 ) was a petroleum geologist who is considered a pioneer in the development of oil production in California , and the use of geology in the oil industry .
Lieutenant General John Neptune Sargent CB ( 18 June 1826 -- 20 October 1893 ) was Commander of British Troops in China , Hong Kong and the Straits Settlements .
Heinrich Eggestein ( born around 1415/1420 in Rosheim , Alsace ; died 1488 or later ; also spelled Eckstein or Eggesteyn ) is considered , along with Johannes Mentelin , to be the earliest book printer in Strasbourg and therefore one of the earliest anywhere in Europe outside Mainz .
John VI , Duke of Mecklenburg ( 1439 - -1474 ) was a Duke of Mecklenburg .
Antoine Vérard ( active 1485 - -1512 ) was a late 15th and early 16th century French publisher , bookmaker and bookseller .
Edward Sparke ( died 1692 ) was an English clergyman and devotional writer .
Joseph Dandridge ( January 1665 Winslow , Buckinghamshire - 23 December 1747 London ) , was an English silk - pattern designer of Huguenot descent , a natural history illustrator , an amateur naturalist specialising in entomology , and a leading figure in the Society of Aurelians of which he was a founder member .
Margherita Cagol ( 1945 - -5 June 1975 ) was a former leader of the Italian left - wing militant organization , the Red Brigades ( Brigate Rosse ) .
Eduardo Ruberté Bisó ( ca . 1917 - ca . 1985 ) was a Puerto Rican politician and Mayor of Ponce , Puerto Rico from 1964 to 1968 .
Donald Gregory ( 1803 - -1836 ) was a Scottish historian and antiquarian , who published a valuable history of the Western Highlands and Isles of Scotland .
Tiberius Julius Aspurgus Philoromaios ( Greek : Τιβέριος Ἰούλιος Ἀσποῦργoς Φιλορώμαιος , Philoromaios means lover of Rome , flourished second half of 1st century BC & first half of 1st century AD , died 38 ) was a Prince and Roman Client King of the Bosporan Kingdom .
Paul Dognin ( 1856 - -1931 ) was a French entomologist who specialised in the Lepidoptera of South America .
Domenico Caldara ( 1814 - -1897 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of portraits and genre painting .
Fintan Kennedy ( died 24 March 1984 ) was an Irish trade unionist .
Heber Hugo Carámbula , ( 31 October 1945 -- 14 November 2015 ) , also known under the stage name of Berugo Carámbula , was a Uruguayan actor , comedian and TV host , born in Las Piedras in 1945 .
Chimalpopoca ( Classical Nahuatl : Chīmalpopōca /t͡ʃiːmaɬpoˈpoːka/ for `` smoking shield '' ) ( 1397 - -1427 ) was the third king of Tenochtitlan ( 1417 - -1427 ) .
Charles Barker ( 1791 - -1859 ) was an English advertising agent .
Karol Chodura ( 9 September 1921 - 22 March 2001 ) is a Polish cinematographer and first assistant director .
Sister Katherine Butler ( 27 May 1914 -- 8 August 2000 ) was a nun with the Religious Sisters of Charity , teacher , writer , and aviator .
Sir John Hay of Alderston , 1st Baronet ( died 1706 ) was created a Baronet of Nova Scotia on 22 February 1703 .
William Greener ( 1806 - -1869 ) was an English inventor and gunmaker .
D. Maria Francisca of Savoy ( Marie Françoise Élisabeth ; 21 June 1646 -- 27 December 1683 ) was twice queen consort of Portugal as the spouse of two Portuguese kings .
Charles Cecil , Viscount Cranborne ( 1619 - -1660 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1648 .
Robert M. Bond ( 16 December 1929 -- 26 April 1984 ) was a lieutenant general of the United States Air Force ( USAF ) .
Jan Frederik Schouten ( 29 May 1910 -- 12 August 1980 ) was a Dutch physicist , and Professor at the Eindhoven University of Technology , known for his contributions to biophysics .
Karl Kaspar von der Leyen ( 18 December 1618 -- 1 June 1676 ) was Archbishop - Elector of Trier and a Prince - Elector of the Holy Roman Empire from 1652 to 1676 .
Kenneth Rayner ( 20 June 1808 -- 4 March 1884 ) was a whig U.S. Congressman from North Carolina between 1839 and 1845 .
Frederick Thomas Pilkington ( 1832 -- 18 September 1898 ) was a Scottish architect , practising in the Victorian High Gothic revival style .
Saverino or Severino Galante ( ca . 1750 - -1827 ) was an Italian painter , active in Abruzzo and Naples .
Sharda Rani Trivedi ( died 1998 ) was a north Indian educator who contributed to higher education for women , for which she is remembered in Uttarakhand and Uttar Pradesh .
Eloy d'Amerval ( fl . 1455 -- 1508 ) was a French composer , singer , choirmaster , and poet of the Renaissance .
Emil Schulz ( 25 May 1938 -- 22 March 2010 ) was a German amateur boxer and five - time national champion , who lost only 21 of his 223 fights .
Antonio Pacchioni ( 1665 - -1726 ) was an Italian scientist and anatomist , who focused chiefly on the outermost meningeal layer of the brain , the dura mater .
Sir Henry Garraway ( died July 1646 ) was an English merchant who was Lord Mayor of London in 1639 .
Paul Esser ( 24 April 1913 -- 20 January 1988 ) was a German stage and television actor and voice actor .
Francis M. Pottenger , Jr. ( 1901 - -1967 ) was the son of Francis M. Pottenger , Sr . , the physician who co - founded the Pottenger Sanatorium for treatment of tuberculosis in Monrovia , California .
Jan Kociniak ( 8 November 1937 -- 20 April 2007 ) was a Polish film and theatre actor .
Gao Shengtai ( died 1096 ) was the ruler of the Dazhong Kingdom ( 1094 - -1096 ) .
Michel Casseux , also known as `` Pisseux '' ( 1794 - -1869 ) was a Savate instructor .
Paul Ambrose ( 11 October 1868 -- 1 July 1941 ) was a Canadian organist , conductor , composer , and music educator who was primarily active in the United States .
Kyrillos Makarios also written as Cyrillus Macaire ( in Arabic كيرلس مقار ) ( born 9 February 1867 - died 18 May 1921 ) was a leader of the Coptic Catholic Church , an Eastern Catholic sui juris particular church of the Catholic Church .
Beriah Botfield FRSE FRS FSA FRGS ( 5 March 1807 -- 7 August 1863 ) was a British Member of Parliament representing Ludlow in Shropshire .
David Nelson Beach ( November 30 , 1848 -- October 18 , 1926 ) was an American theologian , born at South Orange , N. J. , and a brother of Harlan Page Beach .
Torolv Solheim ( 7 November 1907 , Radøy -- 23 May 1995 ) was a Norwegian educator , essayist , resistance member and politician .
Jan Nepomuk Štěpánek ( 19 May 1783 -- 12 February 1844 ) was a Czech playwright , director , actor and theatre manager .
Federico Cafiero ( 24 May 1914 -- 7 May 1980 ) was an Italian mathematician known for his contributions in real analysis , measure and integration theory , and in the theory of ordinary differential equations .
Ólchobar mac Duib - Indrecht ( died 805 ) was a supposed King of Munster from the Eóganacht Áine branch of the Eóganachta .
Otto IV , Count of Ravensberg ( c. 1276 -- 1328 ) was a German nobleman .
George Dalgarno ( c.1626 - -1687 ) was a Scottish intellectual interested in linguistic problems .
Jan Vilímek ( German : Johann Vilimek ; 1 January 1860 -- 15 April 1938 ) was a Czech illustrator and painter .
Alexander Hamilton Church ( 28 May 1866 -- 11 February 1936 ) was an English efficiency engineer , accountant and writer on accountancy and management , known for his seminal work of management and cost accounting .
René Raphy ( 27 December 1920 - 11 May 2008 ) is a former French footballer .
Eógan mac Néill ( modern orthography : Eoghan mac Néill ) ( reportedly died 465 ) was a son of Niall Noígiallach and the eponymous ancestor of the Cenél nEógain branch of the Northern Uí Néill , who founded the over - kingdom of Ailech and later Tír Eoghain .
Margaret Germano , better known as Peggy Mann ( September 27 , 1919 -- summer 1988 ) , was an American Big Band singer who was prominent in the 1930s and 40s .
Romain - Octave Pelletier II ( sometimes spelled Peltier ) ( 26 August 1904 - 11 January 1968 ) was a Canadian music critic , music producer , and violinist .
Edward Carrick ( born Edward Anthony Craig ) ( 3 January 1905 -- 21 January 1998 ) was an art designer for film , an author and illustrator .
Elizabeth Farren ( c. 1759 -- 23 April 1829 ) was an English actress of the late 18th century .
S. Ramanathan ( 1917 - 1988 ) was a Carnatic music singer and musicologist .
Dimitry Markevitch ( 1923 - -2002 ) was a Russian concert cellist , researcher , teacher and musicologist .
Saint Vitonus ( died 525 ) , also called Vanne or Vaune , became a monk as a young man and was made Bishop of Verdun , c.500 .
Dumenko Borys Mokiyovych ( Ukrainian : Думенко Борис Мокійович , Russian : Думенко Борис Мокеевич ) ( 1888 - 11 May 1920 ) was a red cossack with a Ukrainian enslaved cossack origin , who was one of co - founders and commanders of the first red cossack troops , and the Red Army as a whole .
George Febres ( born Jorge Xavier Febres Cordero Icaza , Guayaquil , 10 September 1943 -- 1996 ) was an Ecuadorian - born painter , internationally acclaimed for his wildly imaginative style and humorous `` visual puns . ''
Helen Abbot Merrill ( 1864 -- 1949 ) was an American mathematician , educator and textbook author .
François Borne ( 1840 - -1920 ) , sometimes spelled Bourne , was a French flautist playing with the orchestra of `` Le Grand Théatre de Bordeaux '' ( Bordeaux Opera House ) , composer and professor at `` Conservatoire de Musique de Toulouse '' ( High School for Music in Toulouse ) .
Paul Behrens ( 1893 - -1984 ) was a clockmaker in Lübeck .

Marzio di Colantonio or di Colantonio Ganassini or di Cola Antonio ( c. 1580s -- after 1623 ) was an Italian painter , as a painter of still - lifes and landscapes , and fresco decorations of grotteschi and battle scenes with small figures .
Ralph Dodd ( c.1756 - -11 April 1822 ) was a late 18th century British civil engineer primarily known for his attempt to produce the first tunnel underneath the Thames in 1798 .
Reginald Erskine Foster , nicknamed Tip Foster , commonly designated R. E. Foster in sporting literature ( 16 April 1878 - 13 May 1914 ) was an English cricketer and football player .
Horrie Riley ( 10 September 1902 -- 8 February 1970 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Sturt in the SAFL .
Owen Browne Carter ( 1806 -- 30 March 1859 ) was an English architect , based in Winchester .
Stella Maria Sarah Miles Franklin , known as Miles Franklin ( 14 October 1879 -- 19 September 1954 ) was an Australian writer and feminist who is best known for her novel My Brilliant Career , self - published in 1901 .
Thomas Brome ( died 1380 ) was an English Carmelite monk , provincial of his order from 1362 .
Thomas Wentworth Beaumont ( 5 November 1792 -- 20 December 1848 ) of Bretton Hall , Wakefield in Yorkshire , was a British politician and soldier .
Detty Kurnia ( 1960 -- 20 April 2010 ) was an Indonesian vocalist who sang Pop Sunda ( a mix of Western pop and Sundanese music ) by blending traditional Indonesian music with western music .
Alexander Tolmer ( 1815 -- 7 March 1890 ) was a South Australian police officer and Police Commissioner .
Harry Lindbäck ( 19 December 1926 -- 9 August 2010 ) was a Swedish sprint canoer who competed in the early 1950s .
Ronald Montagu Burrows ( 16 August 1867 -- 14 May 1920 ) was a British academic archaeologist who served as Principal of King 's College London from 1913 to 1920 .
Käte Fenchel née Käte Sperling ( 21 December 1905 -- 19 December 1983 ) Jewish German mathematician , best known for her work on non - abelian groups .
Joseph Weintraub ( 1908 - 1977 ) was Chief Justice of the New Jersey Supreme Court from 1957 to 1973 .
Vardan I Dadiani ( Georgian : ვარდან I დადიანი ) ( died c. 1213 ) was a Georgian noble and the forefather of the Dadiani , the princely dynasty of Samegrelo ( Mingrelia ) , a region in western Georgia which Vardan ruled as eristavi ( `` duke '' ) from 1183 to 1213 .
Giambattista Scandella ( 1770 - 1798 ) was an Italian physician and scientist who emigrated to the United States in 1796 .
Justin - Marie Bomboko Lokumba Is Elenge ( 22 September 1928 -- 10 April 2014 ) , known as Justin Marie Bomboko , was a Congolese civil servant .
Jamie Tape ( 5 April 1974 -- 3 January 2003 ) was an Australian rules footballer .
José de la Cruz ( 21 December 1746 -- 12 March 1829 ) , more popularly known as Huseng Sisiw , was one of the great Filipino writers during the Spanish regime .
Andrew Sexton Gray ( 1826 -- 10 July 1907 ) was an Irish surgeon , who founded the Royal Victorian Eye and Ear Hospital in Melbourne , and is considered a `` founder of ophthalmology in Australia '' .
Fa Zheng ( 176 - -220 ) , courtesy name Xiaozhi , was an adviser to the warlord Liu Bei in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Hector Theophilus de Cramahé ( 1 October 1720 -- 9 June 1788 ) , born Théophile Hector Chateigner de Cramahé , was Lieutenant - Governor of the Province of Quebec , and titular Lieutenant Governor of Detroit .
Sir William Brereton , 1st Baronet ( 13 September 1604 -- 7 April 1661 ) was an English writer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1628 and 1659 .
Wally Cameron ( 13 November 1896 -- 22 April 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the VFL during the 1920s .
Agegnehu Engida ( 1905 in Mahdere Maryam - 1950 ) was an Ethiopian modern artist .
Chaleo Yoovidhya ( Thai : เฉลียว อยู่วิทยา , rtgs : Chaliao Yuwitthaya , Thai pronunciation : ( ʨʰàlǐːaw jùːwíttʰájaː ) ; born 17 August 1923 ; died on 17 March 2012 ) was a Thai businessman and investor .
Adam Sedgwick ( 22 March 1785 -- 27 January 1873 ) was one of the founders of modern geology .
Fred J. Hart ( August 20 , 1888 -- 1976 ) was an American farmer and businessman .
Erica Wilson ( 8 October 1928 -- 13 December 2011 ) was an English - born American embroidery designer based in New York , known particularly for needlepoint .
Abraham ben Isaac of Narbonne ( c. 1110 -- 1179 ) was a Provençal rabbi , also known as Raavad II , and author of the halachic work Ha - Eshkol ( The Cluster ) .
George Ernest Hamilton CE ( ca.1800 -- 8 October 1872 ) was a British civil engineer who played a leading role in development of the Colony of South Australia .
Stan Parker ( 31 May 1920 in Worksop -- 1994 ) was a professional footballer .
Nuccio Costa ( 1925 -- 27 February 1991 ) was an Italian television presenter .
Pier Francesco Tosi ( c. 1653 -- 1732 ) was a castrato singer , composer , and writer on music .
Edward Strachey , 1st Baron Strachie PC ( 30 October 1858 -- 25 July 1936 ) , known as Sir Edward Strachey , Bt , between 1901 and 1911 , was a British Liberal politician .
Dr John Fewster ( 1738 - 1824 ) was a surgeon and apothecary in Thornbury , Gloucestershire .
John Poulett , 2nd Baron Poulett DL ( 1615 -- 15 September 1665 ) , of Hinton St George in Somerset , was an English peer and Member of Parliament who fought on the Royalist side during the English Civil War .
William Brewer , 1st Baron Brewer ( alias Briwere , etc . ) ( died 1226 ) was a prominent administrator and judge in England during the reigns of Kings Richard I , his brother King John , and the latter 's son Henry III . He was a major landholder and the founder of several religious institutions .
Joseph Wasse ( 1672 - -1738 ) was an English cleric and classical scholar .
Peter Peckard ( c. 1718 -- 8 December 1797 ) was an English Whig , Vice - Chancellor of Cambridge University , Church of England minister and abolitionist .
John Hazlewood SSC ( 19 May 1924 -- 4 September 1998 ) was the seventh Anglican Bishop of Ballarat from 1975 to 1993 .
George A. Schilling ( 1850 - 1936 ) was a prominent American union leader and Georgist in the late nineteenth century .
Emanuel Shinwell , Baron Shinwell , CH , PC ( 18 October 1884 -- 8 May 1986 ) , known informally as Manny Shinwell , was a British trade union official , Labour politician and one of the leading figures of Red Clydeside .
Franz Studniczka ( 14 August 1860 -- 4 December 1929 ) was a German professor of classical archaeology born in Jasło , Galicia .
Thomas Westfield ( 1573 - -1644 ) was an English churchman , Bishop of Bristol and member of the Westminster Assembly .
John Antes ( 1740 - -1811 ) was the first American Moravian Missionary to travel and work in Egypt , one of the earliest American - born chamber music composers , and the maker of perhaps the earliest surviving bowed string instrument made in America .
Joseph Windmills ( c1640 - 1724 ) , was an eminent London watch- and clock - maker who , with his son Thomas , produced outstanding timepieces between 1671 and 1737 .
Jerry Lordan ( 30 April 1934 -- 24 July 1995 ) was an English songwriter , composer and singer .
Aqa Mirak ( fl . 1520 -- Qazvin , 1576 ) was a Persian illustrator and painter .
Edith Ranum ( 23 May 1922 -- 25 October 2002 ) was a Norwegian crime writer , novelist and playwright .
Jascha Horenstein ( Russian : Яша Горенштейн ; 6 May ( O.S. 24 April ) 1898 -- 2 April 1973 ) was an American conductor .
Darcy McDougall ( 16 April 1886 -- 7 April 1952 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ljubomir Kovačević ( 4 January 1848 - 19 November 1918 ) was a Serbian writer , historian , academic , and politician .
Sarah Mary Fitton ( c. 1796 -- 30 March 1874 ) was an Irish writer , who had an interest in botany .
Tsai Horng Chung ( also , Chai Chung Ying ; 蔡洪鐘 ) ( 1915 - -2003 ) , was a Chinese - Sarawakan painter .
Thomas Moryson ( died 19 February 1592 ) was an English government official , landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1572 and 1589 .
Morgan Owen ( 1584/5 -- 1645 ) was bishop of Llandaff , Wales from 1639 but imprisoned and unable to exercise his charge from 1644 .
Frans Claerhout ( 15 February 1919 -- 4 July 2006 ) was a Belgian painter who spent most of his adult life in South Africa .
Peter Kern ( 13 February 1949 -- 26 August 2015 ) was an Austrian actor , film director , screenwriter and producer .
Robert Hutton ( 1876 -- 5 August 1970 ) was an English metallurgist and Goldsmiths '' Professor in Metallurgy at Cambridge University from 1931 to 1942 and known for his work with the Society for the Protection of Science and Learning in assisting academics to flee the Nazi regime in Germany .
Pierre de L'Estoile ( 1546 -- 8 October 1611 ) was a Parisian diarist and collector .
William Wilson Kettle ( 21 September 1860 -- 25 January 1963 ) was a Canadian centenarian .
Claude - Antoine de Bermen de La Martinière ( 12 July 1700 -- 24 December 1761 ) was a Quebec born son of Claude de Bermen de la Martinière .
Frank Grouard ( also known as Frank Gruard ) ( 20 September 1850 -- 15 August 1905 ) was a Scout and interpreter for General George Crook during the American Indian War of 1876 .
K. M. Daniel ( 9 May 1920 -- 18 July 1988 ) was an Indian literary critic and scholar from Kerala , India .
John Poppitt ( 20 January 1923 -- 12 February 2014 ) was an English footballer who played in The Football League for Derby County and Queens Park Rangers .
William Francis Finlason ( 1818 - -1895 ) was an English journalist and legal writer .
Salim Ben Ali Al - Qasimi ( 1918 ? 2002 ) served as prime minister of Comoros under President Ahmed Abdallah from December 22 , 1978 until February 8 , 1982 .
Saint Bonifacia Rodríguez y Castro , S.S.J. , ( 6 June 1837 -- 8 August 1905 ) was the co - foundress of the Religious Congregation of the Servants of St. Joseph , who developed the `` Nazareth workshop '' as both a new format for consecrated life and to help poor and unemployed women .
Sir Douglas Veale CBE ( 2 April 1891 -- 27 September 1973 ) was a British civil servant and university administrator , who served as Registrar of the University of Oxford from 1930 to 1958 .
Zachary Langton ( 1698 - -1788 ) was an English divine .
Irina Nijinska ( 20 November 1913 - 2 July 1991 ) was a Russian - born ballet dancer .
Claudio Carosino , MD ( 12 March 1951 -- 24 October 2010 ) was an Italian general practitioner and family physician , tutor and mentor engaged in rural medicine .
Christen Winther Obel ( 1800 - 1860 ) was a Danish businessman who contributed to Aalborg 's prosperity in the 19th century by successfully developing the family 's tobacco business founded in 1787 .
Christopher Frimann Omsen ( 11 December 1761 -- 25 April 1829 ) was a Norwegian `` Founding Father '' and later Supreme Court Justice .
Edward La Trobe Bateman ( 8 January 1816 -- 1897 ) was a pre - Raphaelite watercolour painter , book illuminator , draughtsman and garden designer .
Ferdinand Grossmann ( 4 July 1887 -- 5 December 1970 ) was an Austrian choral conductor , vocal teacher and composer .
Aloisio Gardellini ( August 4 , 1759 in Rome -- October 8 , 1829 ) was an Italian editor and compiler of religious documents .
Jean Baptiste Morel or Jan Baptist Morel ( 1662 -- 1732 ) was a Flemish still life painter who specialized in flower pieces and garlands .
George Alexander Stevens ( 1710 -- 6 September 1780 ) was an English actor , playwright , poet , and songwriter .
Tikkana ( or Tikkana Somayaji ) ( 1205 - -1288 ) was born into a family of Shaivite family during the Golden Age of the Kakatiya dynasty .
Vladimír Padrůněk ( 17 February 1952 -- 30 August 1991 ) is a Czech rock bass guitarist .
Lady Louisa Stuart ( 12 August 1757 -- 4 August 1851 ) was a British writer of the 18th and 19th centuries .
Johann Christian Gottlieb Graupner ( 1767 - -1836 ) was a musician , composer , educator and publisher .
Rico Tomaso ( 1898 in Chicago , Illinois -- 1985 in New York , New York ) was an illustrator and painter .
Bhupendranath Datta ( 4 September 1880 -- 25 December 1961 ) was an Indian revolutionary and later a noted sociologist .
Phraya Phahonphonphayuhasena ( Thai : พระยาพหลพลพยุหเสนา , Thai pronunciation : ( pʰrá.jaː.pʰá.hǒn.pʰon.pʰá.jú.hà.sě.naː ) ) , 29 March 1887 -- 14 February 1947 ) , short Phraya Phahon , born as Phot Phahonyothin ( Thai : พจน์ พหลโยธิน ) , was a Thai military leader and politician .
Horace Walter Gilbert ( 1855 - 1928 ) was an English landscape painter during the Victorian era , and a member of the Williams family of painters .
Geneviève de Brunelle , Marquise de Combray ( 1742 - -1823 ) , was a French counter - revolutionary and royalist during the French Revolution and the first empire .
Johannes Andreas August Grabau ( March 18 , 1804 - -June 2 , 1879 ) was an influential German - American Old Lutheran pastor and theologian .
Charles Edmund Raven ( 1876 - -1940 ) was an Ontario merchant and political figure .
Edmund Różycki ( born January 13 , 1827 in Volhynia , died 1893 in Kraków ) was a Polish general in the January Uprising , and the overall commander of the uprising in Volhynia and Podolia .
Albrecht von Kalckstein ( 4 November 1592 -- 26 May 1667 ) was a Prussian count , Lieutenant General and opponent of Frederick William , Elector of Brandenburg .
George Selway ( 21 February 1924 - May 1994 ) was a British actor who had a lengthy career in film and television .
Gladstone Porteous died of Typhus in Salaowu ( also known as Sayingpan ) on 10 November 1944 .
Johan Hjalmar Théel ( 14 June 1848 -- 20 July 1937 ) was a Swedish zoologist and university professor .

Maggy Rouff ( 1896 - -1971 ) was a French fashion designer of Belgian origin .
Ole Ernst Pedersen ( 16 May 1940 -- 1 September 2013 ) was a Danish actor , active on stage , TV and film .
Ignaz von Szyszyłowicz ( 30 July 1857 -- 17 February 1910 ) also known as Ignacy Szyszyłowicz was a Polish botanist born in Granica ( Kielce ) .
James G. Wilson ( 1915 - -1987 ) was an embryologist and anatomist , known for his Six Principles of Teratology .
Robert Talbott Miller III or Bob Miller ( April 5 , 1910 -- January 1999 ) was an American citizen who worked in the United States Office of the Coordinator of Inter - American Affairs during World War II . He was alleged to be part of the Soviet espionage group known as the `` Golos ring '' .
Jan of Cieszyn ( Polish : Jan cieszyński ; 1339/40 -- after 18 May 1359 ) , was a Polish prince , member of the Piast dynasty in the Cieszyn branch .
