Rowland Lockey ( c. 1565 - -1616 ) was an English painter and goldsmith .
Eliza Meteyard ( 1816 - -1879 ) was an English writer .
Jean Goldschmit ( 20 February 1924 -- 14 February 1994 ) was a professional Luxembourgian road bicycle racer .
Henry Septimus Sutton ( 1825 - -1901 ) was an English journalist and temperance activist , known as a religious poet .
Stacey Tendeter ( 21 June 1949 -- 26 October 2008 ) was a British actress best known for her performance as Muriel in the 1971 film Two English Girls .
Professor Dr. Robert Eberan von Eberhorst ( 23 October 1902 - -14 March 1982 ) , later known as Robert Eberan - Eberhorst , was a noted Austrian engineer , who designed the Auto Union Type D Grand Prix motor racing car .
General Flower Mocher ( c. 1729 -- 18 July 1801 ) , was a British army officer who served 50 years in the cavalry .
John Hope Smith ( died 15 March 1831 ) was an English Colonial Head of the Gold Coast ( now Ghana ) as Governor of the Committee of Merchants of the Gold Coast from 19 January 1817 until 27 March 1822 .
Richard Senhouse ( died 1626 ) was an English churchman , Bishop of Carlisle from 1624 to 1626 .
Abel Pifre ( 1852 - 1928 ) , was a French engineer who developed the first solar power printing press .
Frederic Boase ( 1843 - -1916 ) was an English librarian and biographer .
Helen Thomas Dranga ( 1865 - -1940 ) , who is also known as Carrie Helen Dranga , was an American painter who made paintings of Hawaii .
Gonzalo de Olavide y Casenave ( 28 March 1934 -- 4 November 2005 ) was a Spanish composer born in Madrid .
Helen D'Arcy Stewart ( née Cranstoun ; 1765 - -1838 ) was Scottish poet and a noted Edinburgh society hostess of the late 18th and early 19th century , as wife to Dugald Stewart , an influential Scottish philosopher and mathematician best known for popularizing the Scottish Enlightenment .
Alexander Hamilton , 10th Duke of Hamilton , 7th Duke of Brandon KG PC FRS FSA ( 3 October 1767 -- 18 August 1852 ) was a Scottish politician and art collector .
William Michael Berry , Baron Hartwell MBE ( 18 May 1911 -- 3 April 2001 ) , was a British newspaper proprietor and journalist .
Bobby Beasley ( 26 August 1935 -- 9 January 2008 ) was an Irish jockey and horse trainer .
Edward Joseph Hansom ( 22 October 1842 -- 27 May 1900 ) was an English Victorian architect who specialised in ecclesiastical buildings in Gothic Revival style , including many Roman Catholic churches .
Eric Huxtable ( 27 October 1908 - 10 October 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Carlton in the VFL during the 1930s and briefly with South Melbourne in the early 1940s .
Penny Dwyer ( born Penelope Rosemary Dwyer ; 24 September 1953 -- 4 September 2003 ) was a British comedy writer and performer , noted for being a member of the Cambridge Footlights revue The Cellar Tapes which won the inaugural Perrier Comedy Awards in 1981 .
Zhao Shangzhi ( simplified Chinese : 赵尚志 ; traditional Chinese : 趙尚志 ; pinyin : Zhào Shàngzhì ; 1908 - 1942 ) was a Chinese military commander .
Lord William Hamilton ( c. 1706 - 11 July 1734 ) was a member of Parliament for Lanarkshire .
Francis Folliott ( 1667 - -1701 ) was an Irish Member of Parliament .
Charles Boyle , 3rd Viscount Dungarvan , 3rd Baron Clifford , FRS ( bapt . 12 December 1639 -- 12 October 1694 ) , was a British peer and politician .
Shirley Crabtree , Jr ( 14 November 1930 -- 2 December 1997 ) , better known as Big Daddy , was an English professional wrestler with a record - breaking 64 inch chest .
Arnold Kendall ( 6 April 1925 -- 12 December 2003 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a winger .
John Charles Herries PC ( November 1778 -- 24 April 1855 ) , known as J. C. Herries , was a British politician and financier and a frequent member of Tory and Conservative cabinets in the early to mid 19th century .
Erich Leo Lehmann ( 20 November 1917 -- 12 September 2009 ) was an American statistician , who made a major contribution to nonparametric hypothesis testing .
Rigmor Andersen ( 11 December 1903 , Aarhus - 10 March 1995 , Søllerød ) was a versatile Danish designer , educator and author .
Adam Drummond ( 31 January 1713 -- 17 June 1786 ) , 11th of Lennoch and 4th of Megginch in Perthshire , was a Scottish merchant , banker and Member of Parliament .
Samuel Fisher Lafone ( Liverpool , 1805 -- Buenos Aires , 1871 ) was a British - born Uruguayan businessman .
Akbar Hussain Rizvi , popularly known as Akbar Allahabadi ( Urdu : اكبر الہ آبادی ) ( October , 1846 ; 15 February 1921 ) , was an Indian Urdu poet .
Ummidia Cornificia Faustina ( AD 141 - -182 ) was a wealthy Roman noblewoman , an heiress and the niece of the Roman Emperor Marcus Aurelius .
Gustav Heynhold ( or Gustav Heinhold , 1800 - -1860 ) was a German botanist who worked at the botanic gardens of Dresden and Frankfurt .
Emil Rupp ( Philipp Heinrich Emil Rupp , 1898 - -1979 ) was a German physicist , regarded by many as a respectable and important experimentalist in the late 1920s .
Fred Mutch ( 21 November 1898 -- 11 November 1986 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Eugene Bordinat , Jr. ( 10 February 1920 -- 11 August 1987 ) was a Ford Motor Company styling executive whose career spanned several decades .
Dorothy Stevens ( 2 September 1888 -- 5 June 1966 ) was a Canadian etcher , portrait painter , print maker , illustrator and teacher , perhaps the most accomplished Canadian etcher of her day .
Domenico Paolella ( 18 October 1915 - 7 October 2002 ) was an Italian director , screenwriter and journalist .
John Padgett ( 21 November 1860 -- 2 August 1943 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played six matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1882 and 1889 , and one match for Lord Hawke 's XI in 1889 .
Dr Phay Seng Whatt ( died 2009 ) was the Chairman of Public Service Commission in Singapore from January 1962 to June 1975 .
Ingebjørg Kasin Sandsdalen ( 6 September 1915 -- 4 September 2003 ) was a Norwegian poet and politician for the Christian Democratic Party .
Saint Mac Laisre mac Luighdeach ( also called Mac Lasre , MacLaisre , M’Lasre , Macc - Laisre , mcLasre , M.Laisre ) b. c.560 - d. 12 September 623 , was the Bishop of Armagh , Ireland from 610 to 12 September 623 .
Malik Muhammad Jayasi ( Hindi : मलिक मोहम्मद जायसी ) ( 1477 - -1542 ) was an Indian poet who wrote in the Avadhi dialect of Hindi .
Veh Mihr Shapur was a Sasanian military officer and the first Marzban of Armenia from 428 to 442 .
Scott Bloemendaal ( 11 September 1912 Rotterdam - 31 October 1964 ) was a Dutch composer , music critic and essayist .
Giles Collier ( 1622 - -1678 ) , was an English divine .
Giorgio Gomelsky ( 28 February 1934 -- 13 January 2016 ) was a film maker , impresario , music manager , songwriter ( as Oscar Rasputin ) and record producer .
Alexander Nicolson ( 1827 - -1893 ) was a Scottish lawyer and man of letters , known as a Gaelic scholar and sheriff - substitute of Kirkcudbright and Greenock , and as a pioneer of mountain climbing in Scotland .
Josias Braun - Blanquet ( 3 August 1884 -- 20 September 1980 ) was an influential phytosociologist and botanist .
Raba bar Rav Huna was a Jewish Talmudist who lived in Babylonia , known as an amora of the third generation ( died 322 ) .
Angelo Sanudo ( died 1262 ) was the second Duke of the Archipelago from 1227 , when his father , Marco I , died , until his own death .
Benjamin B. Hinkson ( c. 1799 - March 1877 ) was the fourth Ohio Secretary of State .
Aert Jansse van Nes ( 1626 -- 13 or 14 September 1693 ) was a 17th - century Dutch naval commander , notable for commanding the second squadron in the raid on the Medway in 1667 .
Frederick of Montbéliard or Frederick of Mömpelgard ( died 29 June 1091 ) was from a noble family in Lotharingia .
Ahmad III ibn Abu Bakr was the Emir of Harar ( 1852 - -1866 ) .
İhsan Ketin ( April 10 , 1914 -- December 16 , 1995 ) was a Turkish earth scientist .
Ana Pelegrín ( 1938 - -2008 ) was an Argentine researcher , writer , and educator .
Marcel Martí ( 1925 - -2010 ) was an Argentine - born sculptor of Catalan descent .
Hekuran Isai ( 7 May 1933 in Peqin -- 26 March 2008 in Tirana ) was an Albanian politician of the Albanian Party of Labour ( PPSh ) .
Thomas Lionel Hodgkin ( 3 April 1910 -- 25 March 1982 ) was an English Marxist historian of Africa `` who did more than anyone to establish the serious study of African history '' in the UK .
Charles Schild ( 1902 - -1980 ) was an American inventor .
Adolph Klauber ( 29 April 1879 − 7 December 1933 ) was an American drama critic and theatrical producer .
Ernesto Galarza ( August 15 , 1905 - -June 22 , 1984 ) was a Mexican - American labor activist , professor , poet , writer , and key figure in the history of immigrant farm worker organization in California .
Alick - Maud Pledge ( 1893 - -1949 ) was an English folk dance and gymnastics teacher .
Pope Felix IV ( III ) ( died 22 September 530 ) served as the Pope of the Catholic Church from 12 July 526 to his death in 530 .
Eric Coutts ( 30 December 1913 -- 16 August 2001 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Nellie Parker Spaulding ( 1870 - -1945 ) was an American silent film actress who appeared in at least 37 films between 1915 and 1925 .
Sidney Louie Gunter Jr. ( 27 February 1925 -- 15 March 2013 ) , known as Hardrock Gunter , was a singer , songwriter and guitarist whose music at the turn of the 1950s prefigured rock and roll and rockabilly music .
Tom Jarvie ( 8 June 1916 -- 1 February 2011 ) was a Scottish professional footballer , veterinary surgeon and television personality
Richard Werner Lang ( 23 March 1922 -- 17 June 2013 ) was a German automotive engineer .
William Biggs ( 1804 - 3 October 1881 ) was a British politician and hosier .
William Frederick Webb ( March 1829 in Sussex -- 1899 in Africa ) was a High Sheriff of Nottinghamshire and officer in the British army .
James Kempson ( 1742 -- 10 March 1822 ) was an English choirmaster , the founder of the Birmingham Musical and Amicable Society in 1762 and the Birmingham Triennial Music Festival in 1768 .
Saint Curcodomus ( died ca . 680 ) was a Benedictine abbot and saint .
Rahim Fahimuddin Dagar ( 2 February 1927 -- 27 July 2011 ) was an exponent of Dagar vani Dhrupad of Indian classical music .
Aodh Ua Goirmghiallaigh , King of Partraige Cera , died 1206 .
Jacopo Gattilusio ( or Giacomo ; died 1428 ) was the third Lord of Lesbos .
Frederick Jaeger ( 29 May 1928 -- 18 June 2004 ) was a German - born actor who found success working in British television .
Bennet Woodcroft FRS ( 20 December 1803 -- 7 February 1879 ) was an English textile manufacturer , industrial archaeologist , pioneer of marine propulsion , a leading figure in patent reform and the first clerk to the commissioners of patents .
Joseph Trani ( 1538 - -1639 ) or Joseph di Trani was a Talmudist of the latter part of the 16th century who lived in Greece .
Fernando Ureña Rib ( 21 March 1951 -- 27 December 2013 ) was a Dominican painter , whose career spanned four decades .
Muhammad ibn Ahmad ibn Gazi ( Arabic-مُحَمَّد إِبنُ أَحمَد إِبن غَازِي ) ( circa 1437 -- 1513 ) was a prominent mathematician from the Maghreb .
Sir Thomas Williams , 1st Baronet ( c. 1621 - 1712 ) was an English medical doctor and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1675 to 1679 .
Johan , or Jan Lagoor ( 1620 -- 1660 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Yolande Harmer ( full name : Yolande Gabbai and then Yolande de - Botton ) ( 1913 - -1959 ) ( Hebrew name Yolande Har - Mor ) ( Hebrew : יולנדה הארמר‎ ) maiden name ) was an Israeli intelligence officer who operated in Egypt in 1948 .
William Vaux , 3rd Baron Vaux of Harrowden ( before 14 August 1535 -- 20 August 1595 ) was an English peer .
Habib Painter or Habeeb Painter ( 1915 - February 22 , 1987 ) was a noted Indian Qawwal and a folk singer .
Tong Guan ( 1054 - -1126 ) , courtesy name Daofu ( 道夫 ) , was a court eunuch , military general , political adviser , and Council of State to Emperor Huizong in the Song Dynasty .
Saluva Narasimha Deva Raya ( r. 1486 - -1491 CE ) ( or Saluva Narasimha , Saluva Narasimha I ) was an emperor of the Vijayanagara Empire from the Saluva Dynasty .
Colin McWilliam ( 1928 - -1989 ) was a British architecture academic and author .
Joseph Beldam ( 26 December 1795 -- 6 June 1866 ) was an English writer , historian and advocate of the abolition of slavery .
Ray Perry ( February 25 , 1915 -- 1950 ) was an American jazz violinist and saxophonist .
Paul Foelsche , ISO ( 30 March 1831 -- 31 January 1914 ) was a South Australian police officer and photographer born in Germany , remembered for his work in the Northern Territory of Australia from 1870 to 1904 .
John Wolley ( 13 May 1823 -- 20 November 1859 ) was an English naturalist best known for his large collection of bird eggs and studies on the dodo and great auk .
Philip Joseph , Prince of Salm - Kyrburg ( 1709 - -1779 ) was the first prince of Salm - Kyrburg , from 1743 to 1779 .
Gordon Bowman ( 10 February 1927 -- 23 September 2013 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Melbourne and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rochus Gliese ( 6 January 1891 -- 22 December 1978 ) was a German actor , director , production designer , and Academy Award - nominated art director of early films from the 1910s and 1920s .
Léopold Louis - Dreyfus ( 5 March 1833 - 9 April 1915 ) was a French businessman , founder of the Louis Dreyfus Group and patriarch of the Louis - Dreyfus family .
John Wycliffe Lowes Forster ( 31 December 1850 -- 24 April 1938 ) was a Canadian artist specializing in portraits , particularly those relating to Canadian history .
Tommy Potts ( 1912 - -1988 ) was an Irish fiddle player and composer from Dublin who gained iconic status in traditional Irish music circles for his virtuoso musicianship .
Homa Nategh ( 1935 -- 1 January 2016 ) was an Iranian historian , Professor of History at Tehran University .
Jacqueline Mazéas ( 10 October 1920 -- 9 July 2012 ) was a French athlete who competed mainly in the discus event .
Milan Nedić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Милан Недић ; 2 September 1878 -- 4 February 1946 ) was a Serbian Nazi collaborator , general and politician .
Thomas Hubbard Sumner ( 20 March 1807 -- 9 March 1876 ) was a sea captain during the 19th century .
John Lovelace , 3rd Baron Lovelace ( 1641 -- 27 September 1693 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1670 when he inherited the peerage as Baron Lovelace .
Carlo II Tocco ( died 1448 ) was the ruler of Epirus from 1429 until his death .
Herbert Lee Waters ( 1902 - -1997 ) was an American photographer and filmmaker .
Thomas O'Connor ( born Dublin , Ireland ; died 30 June 1987 ) , also known as Tommy O'Connor or Tom O'Connor , was an Irish footballer who played for Shamrock Rovers .
Vincenzo dal Prato ( 1756 - -1828 ) was an Italian castrato singer , famous for his work with Mozart .
Erminie Wheeler - Voegelin ( 2 April 1903 -- 10 July 1988 ) was an anthropologist , folklorist , and ethnohistorian .
Sixto Adalberto Tejeda Olivares ( born 28 March 1883 in Chicontepec de Tejeda , Veracruz -- died 8 September 1960 ) was a Mexican politician , who served two terms ( 1920 - -1924 and 1928 - -1932 ) as Governor of Veracruz .
Karl Klindworth ( 25 September 1830 -- 27 July 1916 ) was a German composer , pianist , conductor , violinist and music publisher .
Sng Boh Khim ( 5 February 1950 -- 29 August 2006 ) was a Singaporean poet , particularly notable in the 1970s .
Muriel Angelus ( 10 March 1912 -- 26 June 2004 ) was an English stage , musical theatre and film actress .
Johan Willem Emile Louis Hilgers ( 19 December 1886 -- 21 July 1945 ) , more commonly known as Jan Hilgers or John Hilgers , was an Indo ( Eurasian ) aviator and one of the leading pioneers of Dutch aviation .
Princess Maria Theresia of Liechtenstein ( Maria Theresia Anna Felicitas ; 11 May 1694 -- 20 February 1772 ) was the heiress to the Silesian Duchy of Troppau ( now Opava in Czech Republic ) .
After a brief illness , Dwarkanath Tagore died `` at the peak of his fortune '' on the evening of Saturday 1 August 1846 at the St. George 's Hotel in London during a tremendous thunderstorm the likes of which had not been seen for many years past .
Alvin Clarence Thomas ( November 30 , 1893 -- May 19 , 1974 ) was an American gambler , golfer and hustler better known as Titanic Thompson .
Iacopo VI Appiani ( 1539 -- 15 May 1585 ) was the lord of Piombino from 1545 until his death , although he was expelled from his state between 1548 and 1557 .
Maria Graham ( 19 July 1785 -- 21 November 1842 ) , later Maria , Lady Callcott , was a British writer of travel books and children 's books , and also an accomplished illustrator .
John Foulston ( 1772 -- 30 December 1841 ) was an English architect who was a pupil of Thomas Hardwick and set up a practice in London in 1796 .
Kenneth George Hall , AO , OBE ( 22 February 1901 -- 8 February 1994 ) , better known as Ken G. Hall , was an Australian film producer director , considered one of the most important figures in the history of the Australian film industry .
Maharaja Jhanda Singh Dhillon ( died 1774 ) was a famous royal Sikh warrior of the late 18th century .
Gabriele Manfredi ( 25 March 1681 -- 13 October 1761 ) was an Italian mathematician who undertook important work in the field of calculus .
Bhakta Bir Singh Tuladhar ( Devanagari : भक्तवीरसिंह तुलाधर ) ( 1912 - 1989 ) was a Nepalese merchant and philanthropist .
Rev Henry Hickman ( 1629 - 1692 ) was an English ejected minister and controversialist , and some time pastor of the English church at Leyden .
George Featherstone ( 5 June 1889 -- 1 January 1966 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Miguel de Bonilla y Laya - Bolívar ( 1763 - -1826 ) was a Costa Rican Roman Catholic priest and politician .
William Prout FRS ( 15 January 1785 -- 9 April 1850 ) was an English chemist , physician , and natural theologian .
Milica Branković ( died 1464 ) was the first wife of Leonardo III Tocco , whom she married on 1 May 1463 .
Reece Winstone FRPS ( 1909 - -1991 ) was an English photographer from Bristol .
William Exmew , O.Cart . , ( died Tyburn , 19 June 1535 ) was an English Catholic priest and Carthusian hermit .
Harmesh Malhotra ( 14 June 1936 -- 22 November 2005 ) was an Indian film director , producer & screenplay writer .
Uroš Knežević ( 2 January 1811 -- 21 October 1876 ) ( Урош Кнежевић ) was a Serbian painter .
Emīlija Gudriniece ( Russian : Эмилия Юлиановна Гудриниеце ; 3 August 1920 -- 4 October 2004 ) was a Latvian chemist who specialized in organic synthesis .
Arnold Wienholt ( 25 November 1877 -- 10 September 1940 ) was an Australian grazier , author and politician .
Doug Dench ( 29 January 1930 -- 19 August 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Johann Georg von Werdenstein ( 1542 - -1608 ) , canon of Augsburg and Eichstätt , was the owner of a very substantial library consisting of tens of thousands of books .
Berke Khan ( died 1266 ) ( also Birkai ; Mongolian : Бэрх хаан , Tatar : Бәркә хан ) was the ruler of the Golden Horde ( division of the Mongol Empire ) who effectively consolidated the power of the Blue Horde and White Hordes from 1257 to 1266 .
Gustave Loehr ( 1864 - -1918 ) was one of the four founders of Rotary International , one of the premier service organizations of the world .
George William Lockhart ( real name Locker , 1849 - 24 January 1904 ) was a Victorian era elephant trainer .
Viola Tree ( 17 July 1884 -- 15 November 1938 ) was an English actress , singer , playwright and author .
Lord Charles Arthur Francis Cavendish ( 5 August 1905 -- 23 March 1944 ) was the second son of Victor Cavendish , 9th Duke of Devonshire and his wife Lady Evelyn Emily Mary Petty - FitzMaurice .
Hugo Conrad von Hötzendorf ( c.1807 , Darda ( ? ) - 28 February 1869 , Osijek ) was a Croatian painter and art instructor of German ancestry .
Gopal Raju ( 3 January 1928 -- 10 April 2008 ) was an Indian - born American publisher , editor , journalist , businessman and philanthropist .
Ong Eng Guan ( Chinese : 王永元 ; pinyin : Wáng Yǒngyuán ; b. 1925 , Malacca , Malaya -- d . 2008 ) was a Singaporean politician .
Natan Ilyich Zabara ( 1908 - 1975 ) was a Jewish writer born in Rogachev , a shtetl located in the Zhytomyr area of Ukraine .
James Riker ( New York City , May 11 , 1822 -- 1889 ) was a New York historian and genealogist .
John George Will ( died on 25 March 1917 , aged 24 ) was a Scottish rugby union player .
Herman V , Margrave of Baden - Baden ( c. 1180 -- 16 January 1243 ) ruled Verona and Baden from 1190 until his death .
Patrick Moylett ( 1878 - -1973 ) was a 20th - century Irish nationalist who , during the initial armistice negotiations to end the Irish War of Independence , briefly served as president of the Irish Republican Brotherhood during late-1920 .
Thomas Shillington ( 9 May 1835 - -24 January 1925 ) was an Irish factory owner and politician .
George Mason Graham ( 21 August 1807 -- 31 January 1891 ) , often called the `` Father of LSU , '' was the first Chairman of the board of trustees of the Louisiana State Seminary of Learning , the forerunner of Louisiana State University .
Charlie Gaudion ( 14 April 1904 -- 10 October 1979 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Henry Noll ( 1871 - -1925 ) was a resident of Bethlehem , Pennsylvania made famous in a ( fictionalized and error - riddled ) anecdote used by Frederick Winslow Taylor to illustrate his theories of scientific management .
Sergeant Howard Eugene Beagle ( 31 January 1946 in Glens Falls , New York -- 11 April 1967 ) was a medical corpsman who served in the Vietnam War .

Cathassach mac Lurgain ( or Cathassach mac Fíachnai ) ( died 668 ) was a Dal nAraide king of the Cruithne in Ulaid ( Ulster ) .

Alberto Terrones ( Spanish pronunciation : ( alˈβerto teˈrones ) ; 1894 -- 1957 ) was an Argentine film and theater actor , with an extense filmography .

James Wollaston ( 1873 -- December 1918 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football Alliance for Small Heath .

Ruth Elfriede Hildner ( 1 November 1919 -- 2 May 1947 ) was a guard at several Nazi concentration camps during World War II . Hildner was conscripted into camp service in July 1944 , arriving at Ravensbrück concentration camp to be trained as a camp matron .
Paddy Scanlan ( 6 September 1896 -- 1 January 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with and coached South Melbourne and Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Essad Pasha Toptani or Esad Pasha Toptani ( Albanian : Esad Pashë Toptani ; c. 1863 -- 13 June 1920 ) , primarily known as Essad Pasha , was an Ottoman army officer who served as Albanian deputy in the Ottoman parliament .
Marcel Auguste Denise ( February 3 , 1906 -- 1991 ) was a `` President of the provisional government '' of Côte d'Ivoire during the colonial and autonomous period .
Sir Alexander Cunningham KCIE CSI ( 23 January 1814 -- 28 November 1893 ) was a British army engineer with the Bengal Engineer Group who later took an interest in the history and archaeology of India which led to his appointment in 1861 to the newly created position of archaeological surveyor to the government of India .
Shlomo Hestrin ( Hebrew שלמה הסטרין ; born 1914 ; died 2 February 1962 ) was an Israeli biochemist .
Thomas Embling ( 26 August 1814 -- 17 January 1893 ) was a doctor from the United Kingdom who took an interest in the humane treatment of inmates in asylums before emigrating to Melbourne , Australia where he set about reforming the Yarra Bend Asylum .
Eric Percival `` Percy '' Trewern ( 1895 - 1959 ) was an architect who was known professionally as E. P. Trewern .
Sir John Puckering ( 1544 in Flamborough , Yorkshire -- 30 April 1596 ) was a lawyer , politician , Speaker of the English House of Commons , and Lord Keeper from 1592 until his death .

Sir Thomas Wilkes ( c.1545 -- 2 March 1598 ( N.S in Rouen ) ) was an English civil servant and diplomat during the reign of Elizabeth I of England .
Walter Colman ( 1600 - -1645 ) was an English Franciscan friar .
Alexander Mavrocordatos ( Greek : Ἀλέξανδρος Μαυροκορδάτος ; 1636 -- 23 December 1709 ) was a member of the Greek Mavrocordatos family , a doctor of philosophy and medicine of the University of Bologna , and dragoman to Sultan Mehmed IV in 1673 -- notably employed in negotiations with the Habsburg Monarchy during the Great Turkish War .
Perctarit ( also Berthari ) ( died 688 ) was king of the Lombards from 661 to 662 the first time and later from 671 to 688 .

Charles Warren Greene ( 1840 -- 1920 ) was an American journalist and author , born in Belchertown , Massachusetts .

Joan Bocher ( died 2 May 1550 Smithfield , London ) was an English Anabaptist burned at the stake for heresy .

Abdu al - Hamuli ( 1836 -- May 12 , 1901 ) ( Arabic : عبده الحامولي‎ ) was an Egyptian musician .

Margaret Polley ( died 1555 ) was an English Protestant martyr from Popingberry , Rochester , Kent .

Garret Wesley ( circa 1665 -- 28 September 1728 ) was an Irish Member of Parliament .

Barry Flanagan RA OBE ( 11 January 1941 -- 31 August 2009 ) was a Welsh sculptor .

Nicolas Talon ( 31 August 1605 -- 29 March 1691 ) was a French Jesuit , historian , and ascetical writer .
Admiral of the Fleet George Anson , 1st Baron Anson , PC FRS ( 23 April 1697 -- 6 June 1762 ) , was a Royal Navy officer .
Denis Horgan ( 18 May 1871 -- 2 June 1922 ) was a champion Irish athlete and weight thrower , born in Banteer , County Cork , who competed mainly in the shot put .
John Orrok ( c1779 - 1838 ) was a junior British army officer in the late 18th century and early 19th century .
Władysław Mackiewicz ( 21 December 1903 -- 19 May 1963 ) was a Polish Cavalry Captain ( rotmistrz ) in the 15th Uhlan Regiment and a recipient of the Virtuti Militari , Poland 's highest decoration .
Samuel Fothergill ( 1715 - -1772 ) , was a Quaker minister .
Baltasar de Quiñones ( died 1798 ) was the Master of the Order of Preachers from 1777 to 1798 .
Ann Charlotte Bartholomew ( 1800 - -1862 ) , was an English flower and miniature painter , and author .
Petty Officer Patrick Keohane ( 1879 - -1950 ) was an Irish member of Robert Falcon Scott 's Antarctic expedition of 1910 - -1913 , the Terra Nova Expedition .
Elizabeth Somerset , Duchess of Beaufort ( née Berkeley ; c. 1713 -- 9 April 1799 ) was born in Stoke Gifford in Gloucestershire to John Symes Berkeley and Elizabeth Norborne .
Peter Illing ( 4 March 1899 -- 29 October 1966 ) was an Austrian born , British film and television actor .
Hansraj Behl ( 19 November 1916 -- 1984 ) was an Indian music composer , who composed music for Hindi and Punjabi films .
James Pytts ( c1627 - 1686 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1660 and 1686 .
Ciriaco Rocci ( 1581 - 25 September 1651 ) was an Italian Catholic Cardinal and papal nuncio to Switzerland , Austria and Cologne .
Khin Myo Chit ( Burmese : ခင်မျိုးချစ် , pronounced : ( kʰɪ̀ɴ mjó tɕʰɪʔ ) ; 1 May 1915 -- 2 January 1999 ) was a Burmese author and journalist , whose career spanned over four decades .
Claude Hobday ( b. Faversham , Kent 12 May 1872 ; d. Surbiton , 10 March 1954 ) was an English double - bass player , a member of a well - known musical family , who took part in various early chamber - music recordings .
Maxie McFarland died on 8 November 2013 and is buried at Arlington Cemetery .
Count Imre Zichy de Zich et Vásonkeő ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈimrɛ ˈzitʃi ) ; Hungarian : Zichy Imre ; 22 July 1909 -- 28 September 1999 ) was a Hungarian left - handed amateur tennis player , count and inventor .
Gunnar Dyrberg ( 12 November 1921 Faaborg -- 8 January 2012 ) was a member of the Danish resistance movement during World War II , leading the Holger Danske , a Danish resistance group in the capital Copenhagen , from 1943 to 1945 .
Abu Salih Mansur ( died 915 ) was a Samanid prince , who served as governor during the reign of his uncle Isma'il ibn Ahmad , his cousin Ahmad Samani , and Nasr II .
Sir Arthur Atye or Atey ( died 1604 ) was an English academic and politician .
Richard Cosin ( died 1596 ) was an English jurist .
Bernard Hedges ( 10 November 1927 -- 8 February 2014 ) was a Welsh cricketer who played for Glamorgan , making his first - class debut in 1950 and playing his last match in 1967 .
Thomas Spofforth , born 1743 and died on 16 May 1826 , was an English Organist .
Kamaladevi Chattopadhyay ( 3 April 1903 -- 29 October 1988 ) was an Indian social reformer and freedom fighter .
Henry Dillon , 8th Viscount Dillon ( died 1713 ) was Lord Lieutenant of Roscommon .
Esther Sandoval ( 28 December 1927 -- 6 February 2006 ) was an actress and a pioneer in Puerto Rico 's television .
Mary Anna Needell ( née Lupton , 1830 - -1922 ) , was a popular English novelist , who usually wrote as Mrs. J. H. Needell .
Kanken Tōyama ( 遠山寛賢 Tōyama Kanken , 24 September 1888 -- 24 November 1966 ) was a Japanese schoolteacher and karate master , who developed the foundation for the Shūdōkan karate style .
Peter Pond ( January 18 , 1739 or 1740 -- 1807 ) was a soldier with a Connecticut regiment , a fur trader , a founding member of the North West Company and the Beaver Club , an explorer and a cartographer .
Jacob Sonderling ( 19 October 1878 -- 30 September 1964 ) was a German and American Rabbi .
M. K. Rocksamy ( 1932 - -1988 ) was a prolific Sri Lankan musician and music director .
Violet Florence Martin ( 11 June 1862 -- 21 December 1915 ) was an Irish author who co - wrote a series of novels with cousin Edith Somerville under the pen name of Martin Ross in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Sextus Miskow ( 3 February 1857 in Nyborg -- 24 November 1928 ) was a Danish singer , composer and music critic .
Thomas Beard ( died 1632 ) was an English clergyman and theologian , of Puritan views .
Lejaren Hiller , Sr./Lejaren à Hiller / John Hiller ( 1880 - 1969 ) , was an accomplished American illustrator and photographer .
Beaumont Brenan ( died 1761 ) was an Irish poet and playwright .
Paul Laymann ( 1574 -- 13 November 1635 or 1632 ) was an Austrian Jesuit and important moralist .
Edward Arden ( c. 1542 - -1583 ) was an English nobleman and head of the Arden family , who became a Catholic martyr .
Harinath De ( 1877 - -1911 ) , was an Indian historian , scholar and a polyglot , who later became the first Indian librarian of the National Library of India ( then Imperial Library ) from 1907 to 1911 .
Marcus Fronius ( 1659 -- 14 April 1713 ) was a Lutheran theologian , pedagogue , and author whose published works covered topics such as theology , metaphysics , and humoural physiology .
Peter Arne ( born Peter Randolph Michael Albrecht , 29 September 1918 -- 1 August 1983 ) was a British character actor best known for various performances in British film and television .
T. S. Law ( Thomas Sturdy Law , 31 October 1916 -- 12 May 1997 ) was a Scottish poet whose work was published throughout the latter half of the 20th Century .
John Guillim ( c. 1565 -- 7 May 1621 ) of Minsterworth , Gloucestershire , was an antiquarian and officer of arms at the College of Arms in London .
Éamonn Ceannt ( 21 September 1881 -- 8 May 1916 ) , born Edward Thomas Kent , was an Irish republican , mostly known for his role in the Easter Rising of 1916 .
Hermann Lutz ( 1881 - 1965 ) was a German civil servant and writer .
William John Ansell ( 4 August 1921 -- 22 April 2008 ) , more commonly known as Jack Ansell , was an English footballer who played for Bletchley Brick Works , Northampton Town and Oxford United .
Korrie Layun Rampan ( 17 August 1953 -- 19 November 2015 ) was an Indonesian novelist , short story writer , poet , literary critic , journalist , and politician .
Maithripala Senanayake ( 7 July 1916 -- 12 July 1998 ) was a Sri Lankan politician and Governor of the North - Central province .
Giuseppe Fiorini ( 1861 - -1934 ) was an Italian luthier and is considered one of the most important Italian violin makers .
Emperor Shun of Han ( simplified Chinese : 汉顺帝 ; traditional Chinese : 漢順帝 ; pinyin : Hàn Shùn Dì ; Wade -- Giles : Han Shun - ti ; 115 - -144 ) was an emperor of the Chinese Han Dynasty and the seventh emperor of the Eastern Han .
Haniji ( 怕尼芝 ) , sometimes spelled Haneji , was the founder of the Okinawan kingdom of Hokuzan , which he ruled from roughly 1322 to 1395 .
Pip Harris ( 6 August 1927 - 22 February 2013 ) , born Peter Valentine Harris , was a British motorcycle racer in the sidecar class .
Eleanor Hilowitz ( 1913 - -2007 ) was an abstract expressionist painter and sculpture who was active in New York City and Rome .
Thomas Eyre Lambert ( 25 April 1820 -- 1919 ) was an Irish soldier and landlord .
Phelan Beale , Jr. ( 16 June 1920 -- 26 June 1993 ) was an American journalist and unemployment compensation law expert .
Basil Wright ( 12 June 1907 , Sutton , Surrey -- 14 October 1987 , Frieth , Buckinghamshire , England ) was a documentary filmmaker , film historian , film critic and teacher .
Constance Vella ( 1687 - -1759 ) was a major Maltese mediaeval philosopher who specialised mainly in physics , logic , cosmology , and metaphysics .
Romilly Lisle Holdsworth , commonly known as R. L. Holdsworth , ( 25 February 1899 -- 20 June 1976 ) was a British scholar , academic , educationalist , cricketer and a distinguished Himalayan mountaineer .
Queenie Leighton ( 18 July 1874 -- 19 November 1943 ) was a British music hall star of the Edwardian era .
Alexander Eduard Friedrich Eversmann ( 23 January 1794 -- 14 April 1860 ) was a biologist and explorer .
Dorothy Savile , Viscountess Halifax ( née Spencer ) ( 1640 -- 16 December 1670 ) was the first wife of George Savile , 1st Viscount Halifax and the daughter of Henry Spencer , 1st Earl of Sunderland .
Lord Arthur Chichester ( 30 September 1808 -- 25 January 1840 ) , was an Anglo - Irish Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Maria Cattarina Locatelli ( or Lucatelli ; died 1723 ) was an Italian painter .
Adolph Ernst ( April 7 , 1887 - -November 10 , 1966 ) , better known for his ring name Ad Santel , was an American professional wrestler , considered one of the greatest practitioners of catch wrestling ever .
Stanley Chapman ( 15 September 1925 -- 26 May 2009 ) was a British architect , designer , translator and writer .
Martanda Cinkaiariyan ( Tamil : மார்த்தாண்ட சிங்கையாரியன் ) ( died 1348 ) ascended the throne of Jaffna Kingdom under the throne name Pararasasekaram III . He is one of the early Aryacakravarti kings about whom historical and epigraphical evidence is available .
Felix Bowness ( 30 March 1922 -- 13 September 2009 ) was an English comedy actor best remembered for his portrayal of the jockey Fred Quilley in the BBC sitcom Hi - de - Hi!.
Gabriel Druillettes ( Dreuillettes , Drouillettes , Drouillet , Droulletes , Drueillettes , Druilletes ) ( 29 September 1610 -- 8 April 1681 ) was born in France and became a Jesuit priest .
George I , Prince of Waldeck and Pyrmont ( German : Georg Fürst zu Waldeck und Pyrmont ; 6 May 1747 -- 9 September 1813 ) was Prince of Waldeck and Pyrmont from 1812 to 1813 .
Wilhelm Junker ( Russian : Василий Васильевич Юнкер ; 6 April 1840 - 13 February 1892 ) was a Russian explorer of Africa .
Matthias van den Gheyn ( Dutch : Matthijs Vanden Gheyn or Ghein ; 7 April 1721 -- 22 June 1785 ) was a Flemish composer from a family of famous bell - founders .
Mark Perakh ( Russian : Марк Пэрах ; born Mark Yakovlevich Popereka in 1924 , Kiev , Ukraine , died 7 May 2013 in Escondido , California ) , was a professor emeritus of Mathematics and statistical mechanics at California State University , Fullerton in Fullerton , California .
Ernest Masson Anderson FRSE FGS ( 1877 - -1960 ) was a Scottish geologist .
Louis III , Count of Löwenstein ( 17 February 1530 in Vaihingen † 13 March 1611 in Wertheim ) was the ruling Count of Löwenstein - Wertheim from 1571 until his death .
John David Love ( 17 April 1913 -- 23 August 2002 ) was an American field geologist and specialist in Rocky Mountain geology who worked for the United States Geological Survey from 1942 to 1987 .
Stephen Vail ( 1780 - -1864 ) was a founding partner of the Baldwin Locomotive Works in Philadelphia and the creator of the Speedwell Ironworks in Morristown , New Jersey .
Samuel Victor Perry FRS ( 16 July 1918 -- 17 December 2009 ) was an English biochemist who was a pioneer in the field of muscle biochemistry .
Henry Willoughby , 4th Baron Willoughby of Parham ( 1612 - -1617 ) was an English peer of the House of Lords .
Tuoba Luguan ( Chinese : 拓跋祿官 ; pinyin : Tuòbá Lùguān ) ( died 307 ) , chieftain of the Tuoba , from 294 to 307 .
Rafael Hoyos Rubio ( 1924 - -1981 ) was a Peruvian general who held the rank of General of the Army and occupied the post of Commander in Chief of the Peruvian Army from December 5 , 1980 to June 1981 .
Benedetto Ghiglia ( 27 December 1921 - 4 July 2012 ) was an Italian composer , conductor and pianist .
Alan Loy McGinnis ( 10 November 1933 , Friendswood , Texas - 9 January 2005 , Glendale , California ) was an author , Christian psychotherapist , and founder and director of the Valley Counseling Center in Glendale , California , United States .
Hans von Rüte ( d. 23 March 1558 ) was a Bernese dramatist and chronicler of the Swiss Reformation .
Béla Vörösmarty ( 23 April 1844 -- 9 October 1904 ) was a Hungarian jurist and politician , son of poet Mihály Vörösmarty and Laura Csajághy and brother of Ilona Vörösmarty .
Federiko Benković ( 1667 -- 8 July 1753 ) was a prominent late Baroque painter working in Italy .
Helen Clay Frick ( 1888 - -1984 ) was an American philanthropist and art collector .
Frank Ludlow OBE ( 10 August 1885 -- 25 March 1972 ) was an English officer stationed in the British Mission at Lhasa and a naturalist .
Elie Kedourie , CBE , FBA ( 25 January 1926 -- 29 June 1992 , Washington ) was a British historian of the Middle East .
Federico Cerruti ( 1 January 1922 -- 15 July 2015 ) was a reclusive Italian art collector whose collection was described by Artribune as one of the best in Europe .
Henry Fletcher Hance ( 4 Aug 1827 -- 22 June 1886 ) was a British diplomat who devoted his spare time to the study of Chinese plants .
Ēriks Pētersons ( 1909 in Riga , Soviet Union -- 1987 in United States ) was Latvian footballer and hockey player .
Sir John Oldcastle ( died 14 December 1417 ) was an English Lollard leader .
Maria McAuley ( 1847 , US - 19 September 1919 ) , along with her husband Jerry , founded the McAuley Water St Mission in New York City .
Benjamin Franklin Haynes ( 1851 - -1923 ) , usually known as B. F. Haynes , was a Methodist and later Nazarene minister and theologian from Tennessee .
The Reverend Brother Brigant Cassian OBE , FSC ( born 1889 , Brittany , France -- 31 October 1957 , Hong Kong ) was the priest and education worker in Hong Kong .
Kalidas Gupta Riza ( 1925 - -2001 ) was an Indian writer , considered by many as an authority on the writings of the renowned Urdu poet , Mirza Ghalib .
Charles Thurber was a black man lynched in Grand Forks , North Dakota on October 24 , 1882 .
Ernst Philipp Karl Lange ( 21 December 1813 - 20 February 1899 ) was a German novelist who wrote under the pseudonym Philipp Galen .
King Seocheon of Goguryeo ( died 292 , r. 270 - -292 ) was the 13th ruler of Goguryeo , the northernmost of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Edward Rhodes Carswell ( 1813 -- 1862 ) was a member of the Georgia General Assembly House of Representatives from Jefferson County , Georgia and the father of Confederate States Army Lieutenant Colonel , Georgia militia Brigadier General and Georgia state legislator Reuben Walker Carswell .
Edmund Alexander Parkes ( 29 December 1819 -- 15 March 1876 ) was an English physician , known as a hygienist , particularly in the military context .
Jonathan Apphus ( Hebrew : יונתן הוופסי , Ancient Greek : Ἰωνάθαν Ἀπφοῦς ) was leader of the Hasmonean Dynasty of Judea from 161 to 143 BCE .
John Jewell Penstone ( 1817 - -1902 ) was a portrait and genre artist who worked with paint , but is known mainly for his engravings , and has been associated with the Pre - Raphaelite movement .
Boris Pushkin , Russian Борис Иванович Пушкин ( ca . 1590 - -1659 ) was a Russian diplomat and officeholder .
Anne Caldwell ( née Anne Payson Caldwell ; 30 August 1868 -- 22 October 1936 ) , also known as Anne Caldwell O'Dea , was a prolific playwright and lyricist .
William de St Croix ( born 13 May 1819 at Windsor Castle , Berkshire ; died 18 March 1877 at Glynde , Sussex ) was an English amateur cricketer and clergyman .
Dirkie Uys ( 1823 - 1838 ) was a Voortrekker hero during the Great Trek .
Saint Gorgonius of Nicomedia was a Christian martyr , part of the group Gorgonius , Peter Cubicularius and Dorotheus , who died in 304 AD at Nicomedia during the persecution of Emperor Diocletian .
John Sen Inches Thomson ( 1845 - -1933 ) , was a Scottish whaler and sealer , ship owner , captain and author .
Gamaliel King ( Shelter Island , New York , 1 December 1795 -- 6 December 1875 ) was an American architect who practiced in New York City and the adjacent city of Brooklyn , where he was a major figure in Brooklyn civic and ecclesiastical architecture for several decades .
Swami Bhaskarananda Saraswati ( 1833 - -1899 ) was a noted 19th - century sannyasin and saint of Varanasi , India .
Miao Tien ( Chinese : 苗天 , 6 December 1925 -- 19 February 2005 ) was a Chinese film actor .
Chan Heung ( August 23 , 1806 -- August 20 , 1875 ) was the founder of the Choy Li Fut 蔡李佛 martial arts system .
Count Aladár Zichy de Zich et Vásonkeő ( 4 September 1864 -- 16 November 1937 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister besides the King twice : between 1906 - -1910 and during the end of the First World War .
Felix Bloch ( 23 October 1905 -- 10 September 1983 ) was a Swiss physicist , working mainly in the U.S. He and Edward Mills Purcell were awarded the 1952 Nobel Prize for `` their development of new ways and methods for nuclear magnetic precision measurements . ''
Edward Bligh , 2nd Earl of Darnley ( 9 November 1715 -- 22 July 1747 ) was an Irish peer born of an English family who resided in Kent .
Kitty Harris ( May 25 , 1899 -- 1966 ) was a Soviet secret agent and `` long - time special courier of the OGPU - NKVD foreign intelligence during the 1930s and 1940s . ''
Hubert van Es ( 6 July 1941 -- 15 May 2009 ) was a Dutch photographer and photojournalist who took the well - known photo on 29 April 1975 , which shows South Vietnamese civilians scrambling to board a CIA Air America helicopter during the U.S. evacuation of Saigon .
Dr. Anneliese Groscurth ( 1910 - -1996 ) was the wife of Georg Groscurth and a member of the European Union , ( Europäische Union ) an antifascist German resistance group in Berlin , during the Nazi era .
Sir John Chandos , Viscount of Saint - Sauveur in the Cotentin , Constable of Aquitaine , Seneschal of Poitou , KG ( c.1320 -- 31 December 1369 ) was a medieval English knight who hailed from Radbourne Hall , Derbyshire .
Eleanor Albert Bliss ( 1899 - -1987 ) was an American bacteriologist who did pioneering work on antimicrobials , especially regarding the development and use of sulfa drugs .
Alexander Muir ( 5 April 1830 -- 26 June 1906 ) was a Canadian songwriter , poet , soldier , and school headmaster .
Graham Lord ( 16 February 1943 -- 13 June 2015 ) was a British biographer and novelist .
Maurice Auguste Régimbart ( 1852 in Evreux -- 22 September 1907 in Evreux ) was a French entomologist who specialised in Coleoptera , particularly Dytiscidae , Gyrinidae and Hydrophilidae .
Barbatio ( died AD 359 ) was a Roman general of the infantry under the command of Constantius II . Previously he was a commander of the household troops under Gallus Caesar , but he arrested Gallus under the instruction of Constantius , thereby ensuring his promotion on the death of Claudius Silvanus .
J. C. Ramaswamy ( c. 1928 -- 2 August 1986 ) , known by his screen name Shakti Prasad , was an Indian actor who appeared in Kannada films in mostly villainous roles .
Banzarjavyn Baasanjav ( Mongolian : Банзаржавын Баасанжав ; 1906 - -1940 ) was leader of the Mongolian People 's Revolutionary Party from 1936 to 1940 .
Joseph E. Woodworth ( 1837 - 1889 ) was a ship builder , merchant , and member of the Woodworth political family .
John Napier Burnett ( born 1899 , and died in 1989 ) was an important pioneer of education in British Columbia .
Moshe Levin ( 1897 - -1943 ) , alias ' Batlan ' and ' Elisha ' , was a Jewish socialist .
Theophil Mitchell Prudden ( 1849 - 1924 ) was an American pathologist , born at Middlebury , Connecticut .
General Horace Binney Sargent ( June 26 , 1821 -- 1908 ) was American soldier and politician .
Thomas Cottle , Esq . ( 1761 - -1828 ) was a lawyer on the island of Nevis .
Natan Peled ( Hebrew : נתן פלד‎ , born 3 June 1913 , died 8 January 1992 ) was an Israeli politician who served as Minister of Immigrant Absorption from 1970 until 1974 .
Nescambious ( c. 1660 - -1727 , many variant spellings , including Escumbuit and Nescambiouit ) , was a Native American leader of the Pequawket tribe of the Abenaki who was knighted by Louis XIV of France in 1706 .
Isaac Rochussen or Isaac Rockesen ( 1631 - -1710 ) was a 17th - century Dutch corsair and privateer during the Second and Third Anglo - Dutch War .
Mattia Bortoloni ( 31 March 1696 -- 1750 ) was an Italian painter of the Rococo period , mainly active in the area of Bergamo and Venice .
Hugh Tootell ( 1671/1672 -- 27 February 1743 ) was an English Catholic historian .
A painter and traveller , Georges Ricard - Cordingley ( 1873 - 1939 ) constantly searched for an original contact with the world of sea .
Franco de Franco ( circa 1585 in Corulani -- June 30 , 1611 in Vilnius ) was an Italian Calvinist who was sentenced to death in the Polish--
George Chippendale ( 18 April 1921 -- 16 February 2010 ) was an Australian botanist and a strong proponent of growing Australian Native plants .
Caroline Kaye Walters ( 1957 -- 12 July 2008 ) , known as Caroline K , was an English singer , songwriter and artist / producer .
Sankarankutti Menon Marath , better known as Menon Marath , ( born in 1906 in Kerala -- died 2 January 2003 ) was an Indo - Anglican novelist who settled in England and spent more than half of his life there .
Archduchess Caroline Ludovika of Austria ( Karoline Ludovika Leopoldine ; 4/9 December 1795 , Hofburg Palace , Vienna , Austria - 30 June 1799 , Hofburg Palace , Vienna , Austria ) was the third daughter and fourth child of Francis II , Holy Roman Emperor and his wife Maria Theresa of Naples and Sicily .
Zordun Sabir ( 1937 -- 13 August 1998 ) ( Uyghur : زوردۇن سابىر ) was a popular Uyghur author .
Charles Durang ( 1794 - -1870 ) was an American dancer .
Norman Whitehead ( 1915 - -1983 ) was a landscape painter , working mainly around his hometown Alfreton , Derbyshire .
John Lonyson or Lonison ( 1525 - -1582 ) was an English goldsmith and Master of the Mint in the reign of Elizabeth I. John Lonyson was of Flemish descent , one of a family of goldsmiths established In King 's Lynn , Norfolk .
Gustave Maurice Heckscher ( 15 May 1884 - 1967 ) , was a pioneer aviator with seaplanes .
Sir Thomas Foxley ( c.1305 -- 1360 ) was MP for Berkshire several times in the 14th century , and Constable of Windsor Castle , also in the English county of Berkshire , from 1328 to his death .
Harry Leander Ells ( 1854 - 1943 ) served in the California legislature and was born in Canada .
Mort O'Shea ( 1882 - -1970 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a full - back for the Cork senior team .
Khun Lo died in 780 and was succeeded by Khun Sung .
Buck Nelson ( April 9 , 1895 -- 1982 ) was an American farmer who claimed to have had an encounter with an unidentified flying object and its human crew in 1954 while living in Missouri .
Mirza Abdul Karim Roushan Tehrani ( 1903 - -1992 ) was an Iranian mystics , philosopher and jurist .
Johan Wilhelm Heinrich Giess aka Willi Giess ( 21 February 1910 Frankfurt - am - Main - 28 September 2000 Swakopmund ) is noted for having started an official herbarium at Windhoek , his extensive collection of Namibian plants and generally furthering botanical knowledge of the territory .
Vincenzo Sangermano , C.R.S.P. ( 1758 - 1819 ) , was an Italian Roman Catholic priest , of the Barnabite Order , who served as a missionary in Burma from 1783 to 1806 .
James Joseph Meadows ( 1 September 1835 -- 12 December 1914 ) , Protestant Christian missionary to China and one of the first missionaries with the China Inland Mission .
Robert William Buss ( 4 August 1804 -- 26 February 1875 ) was a Victorian artist , etcher and illustrator perhaps best known for his painting Dickens ' Dream .
Tô Vĩnh Diện ( died 1954 ) was a soldier in the Viet Minh during the First Indochina War against France in Vietnam .
Finn Hald ( 8 July 1929 -- 17 October 2010 ) was a Norwegian ceramist , sculptor , illustrator , poet and playwright .
Thomas Annan ( 1829 - -1887 ) was a Scottish photographer , notable for being the first to record the bad housing conditions of the poor .
Constantin Antoniade ( 1880 - -1954 ) was a Romanian jurist , writer , historian , philosopher and diplomat .
George Emlyn Williams , CBE ( 26 November 1905 -- 25 September 1987 ) , known as Emlyn Williams , was a Welsh dramatist and actor .
José de la Cruz Sánchez ( November 8 , 1799 - -1878 ) was the eleventh Alcalde of San Francisco in 1845 .
Pal Dushmani ( died 1457 ) was an Albanian prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Leonard Insull ( 1883 - -1974 ) was Britain 's leading ventriloquial figure maker of the twentieth century .
Ludwig Mestler ( 1891 - 1959 ) was an artist in Austria before the Anschluss and then later in the United States .
Renée of Bourbon , Duchess of Lorraine also called , Renée , Lady of Mercœur , ( 1494 -- 26 May 1539 ) , was a Duchess consort of Lorraine .
Ansgar Elde ( 27 November 1933 -- 4 December 2000 ) was a Swedish artist famous for his work in ceramics .
Not long after the Norwegian fleet left the Hebrides , Gofraid Donn was killed on the Outer Hebridean island of Lewis , in 1231 .
Ferdinand Budicki ( 11 April 1871 -- 25 June 1951 ) was a Croatian pioneer of car , bicycle and airplane culture .
Jack Aranson ( 29 December 1924 -- 3 January 2008 ) was an American actor , trained in Ireland and England , noted for acting in many Shakespeare plays and several one - man shows .
Carl R. Fellers ( 1893 - -1960 ) was an American food scientist and microbiologist who was involved in the pasteurization of dried foods and canning Atlantic blue crab .
Naboth Winsor ( October 5 , 1916 -- June 1997 ) was born to Robert Stewart Winsor and Jane ( Butt ) Winsor , on Winsor 's Island , one of the islands comprising Swain 's Island , Bonavista Bay , Newfoundland .
Edward Henry Whinfield ( 1836 - 1922 ) was a translator of Persian literature .
Adja Yunkers ( 1900 - -1983 ) was an American abstract painter and printmaker .
Tzavalas Karousos ( Greek : Τζαβαλάς Καρούσος ; 8 September 1904 -- 3 January 1969 ) was a Greek actor .
Delino Dexter Calvin ( May 15 , 1798 -- 18 May 1884 ) was a naturalized Canadian citizen , former resident of New England , successful Ontario businessman and political figure .
Thomas Cuming Hall ( born 1858 , died on May 27 , 1936 at Göttingen / Germany ) An American Presbyterian theologian , son of the Rev. John Hall ( 1829 - 98 ) .
Tan Kah Kee or Chen Jiageng ( 21 October 1874 -- 12 August 1961 ) was a Chinese businessman , community leader and philanthropist active in Southeast Asia , Hong Kong , and various Chinese cities such as Shanghai , Xiamen , and Guangzhou .
Jakob Fuchs ( 1 August 1920 -- 3 November 2005 ) was a highly decorated Feldwebel in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a Hauptfeldwebel in the Bundeswehr .
Gottlieb Christoph Adolf von Harless ( German : von Harleß ; November 21 , 1806 -- September 5 , 1879 ) , was a German Lutheran theologian .
Gérard Barreaux ( 1948 -- 16 October 2010 ) was a French accordionist , composer , and actor .
` Abd ar - Rahman ibn Muhammad ( died 16 June 1825 ) was the Emir of Harar ( 1821 - 1825 ) .
André Jean René Lacrampe ( 17 December 1941 -- 15 May 2015 ) was the Roman Catholic Archbishop Besançon .
Jules Cottin ( 1868 - -1922 ) was a mandolin virtuoso who played in Paris from the 1890s .
Benedict Kisdy ( Hungarian : Benedek Kisdy , Slovak : Benedikt Kishdy ) ( c. 1598 -- 22 June 1660 ) was a Hungarian Roman Catholic bishop in the 17th century .
Edmondo Zacchini ( 27 March 1894 - 3 October 1981 ) was a circus entertainer credited with inventing the human cannonball act as one of the Zacchini Brothers .
Elkanah Kelsey Dare was a New England Methodist minister born 1782 , and died 1826 .
Timoteo Maradona ( 1793 -- 24 August 1863 ) was an Argentine official and priest who played a leading role in San Juan Province in the first half of the nineteenth century .
Millard Gardner ( 1903 - -1989 ) was a noted Texas lawman known as the `` Dry Wolf '' during Prohibition , later being elected Police Chief of Highland Park near Dallas , Texas .
Murakami Yoshikiyo ( 村上 義清 , 1501 -- 1573 ) was a Japanese Samurai from Murakami clan and retainer of the Japanese clan of Uesugi during the Sengoku Period of the 16th century .
Valerie Ganz ( 1936 -- 2015 ) was a Welsh artist , known for her paintings of South Wales coal miners .
John Michael O'Keefe , known as Johnny O'Keefe ( 19 January 1935 -- 6 October 1978 ) , was an Australian rock and roll singer whose career began in the 1950s .
Enrique Bertolino ( 3 November 1912 -- 1997 ) is an Argentine professional golfer .
Zaida Ben - Yusuf ( 21 November 1869 -- 27 September 1933 ) was a New York - based portrait photographer noted for her artistic portraits of wealthy , fashionable , and famous Americans of the turn of the 19th--20th century .
William Oughtred ( 5 March 1574 -- 30 June 1660 ) was an English mathematician and Anglican minister .
Baltazar Kuncz ( 1580 - 1650 ) was a Polish sculptor and woodcarver .
Hu Sheng ( 11 January 1918 -- 5 November 2000 ) was a renowned Chinese Marxist theorist and historian .
The Very Rev. James Henry Leslie Pennell ( 1906 - 1996 ) was Provost of St Andrew 's Cathedral , Inverness from 1949 to 1965 .
Clement Reid FRS ( 6 January 1853 -- 10 December 1916 ) was a British geologist and palaeobotanist .
Tony Reedus ( 22 September 1959 -- 16 November 2008 ) was an American jazz drummer .
Theophilus Gale ( 1628 - -1678 ) was an English educationalist , nonconformist and theologian of dissent .
Justin Huntly McCarthy ( 1859 -- 20 March 1936 ) was an Irish author and nationalist politician .
Gvido Jekals ( 1 July 1904 -- 2 January 1969 ) was a Latvian sprinter and decathlete .
Pietro Vinci ( c. 1525 -- after 14 June 1584 ) was an Italian composer of late Renaissance music .
Frederick Remsen Hutton , M.E. , Sc . D. ( 1853 - -1918 ) was an American mechanical engineer .
Chan Kwok - Hung ( 陳國雄 ) ( c. 1963 -- 17 December 2014 ) was a Hong Kong cinematographer .
Richard Steward or Stewart ( 1593 ? -- 1651 ) was an English royalist churchman , clerk of the closet to Charles I and designated Dean of St. Paul 's and Westminster , though not able to take up his position because of the wartime circumstances .
Horia Demian ( 1942 - 1989 ) was a Romanian basketball player who played for U Cluj ( Ştiinţa Cluj between 1951 - 1965 , currently U Mobitelco Cluj ) from 1960 until 1970 .
Armand Penverne ( 26 November 1926 -- 27 February 2012 ) was a French international defender and coach .
Ella Briggs ( born Ella Baumfeld ; 5 March 1880 -- 20 June 1977 ) was an Austrian architect .
Yusof Rawa ( died 27 April 2000 ) was a Malaysian politician .
Lorenzo di Bicci ( c. 1350 -- 1427 ) was an Italian painter of the Florentine school , traditional in outlook .
Jacques Lebaudy ( 1868 - January 11 , 1919 ) was a Frenchman from a wealthy family of sugar refiners known for his eccentricity and his attempt to establish a new nation , the Empire of the Sahara .
John Stanton Ward CBE ( 10 October 1917 - 13 June 2007 ) was an English portrait artist , landscape painter and illustrator .
Samuel Hoadly ( 1643 - -1705 ) , was a schoolmaster and writer of educational books .
William Llewellyn Thomas ( 6 May 1872 -- 9 January 1943 ) was a Welsh international rugby union player who played club rugby for Newport , international rugby for Wales and invitational rugby for the Barbarians .
Jože Babič ( 13 February 1917 -- 10 May 1996 ) was a Slovenian film , theatre and television director .
James Amaziah Whitney ( 30 June 1839 , Rochester , New York - 1907 ) was a United States lawyer and author .
Heinrich von Lichtenau ( 1444 - -1517 ) was Prince - Bishop of Augsburg from 1505 to 1517 .
Maurice II de Craon ( c. 1132 - -1196 ) was Lord of Craon , Governor of Anjou and Maine under Henry II , a military figure and Anglo - Norman of the 12th century .
Allender Steele Adams , known as Allen Adams , ( 16 February 1946 -- 5 September 1990 ) , was a British Labour politician .
Gordon C. Bond ( 1939 - -1997 ) was an American historian who specialized in studies of Napoleon .
Gustav Ludolf Martens ( 20 October 1818 -- 7 January 1882 ) was a German architect and state master builder of Kiel .
Marguerite Sawyer Hill Davis ( died 1948 ) was one of the wealthiest women in the United States in the mid 1900s .
Liu Zhidan ( 4 October 1903 ( many sources give 1902 ) -- 14 April 1936 ) ( Liu Chih - tan ) was a Chinese military commander and Communist leader , who founded the Shaanxi - Gansu - Ningxia Base Area in north - west China , which became the Yan'an Soviet .
Savjibhai Korat ( 6 August 1953 -- 26 November 1998 ) was an Indian politician , a cabinet minister of Gujarat state .
Clara Elsene Peck ( April 18 , 1883 -- February 1968 ) was an American illustrator and painter known for her illustrations of women and children in the early 20th century .
Hugo Meisl ( 16 November 1881 ( Maleschau , Bohemia ) - 17 February 1937 ) , brother of the journalist Willy Meisl , was the multi - lingual football coach of the famous Austrian ' Wunderteam ' of the early 1930s , as well as a referee .
Emile Darl'mat ( 1892 - -1970 ) was the creator and owner of a Peugeot distributor with a car body business established at the rue de l'Université in Paris , France in 1923 .
Alexander Victor Edward Paulet Montagu , 10th Earl of Sandwich ( 22 May 1906 -- 25 February 1995 ) , known as Viscount Hinchingbrooke from 1916 to 1962 , as the Earl of Sandwich from 1962 to 1964 and as Victor Montagu from 1964 to 1995 , was a British Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Jesse Gause ( 1785 -- c. 1836 ) was an early leader in the Latter Day Saint movement and served in the First Presidency as a counselor to President of the Church Joseph Smith .
Namiki Shōzō II ( 並木正三)(died 1807 ) was a kabuki playwright and relative of the more prominent Namiki Shōzō I. Though none of his surviving plays are prominent ones , he may have been the author of the 1801 Kezairoku ( or Gezairoku ) , a kabuki playwriting manual .
Adrien - Jean - Pierre Thilorier ( 16 February 1790 -- 2 December 1844 ) was a French inventor who was the first person to produce solid carbon dioxide ( `` dry ice '' ) .
Samuel de Missy ( Samuel , Pierre , Joseph , David , de Missy or Demissy , 30 October 1755 -- 20 October 1820 ) was a French trader and businessman , from the city of La Rochelle , where he was born .
Michael Francklin or Franklin ( 6 December 1733 -- 8 November 1782 ) served as Nova Scotia 's Lieutenant Governor from 1766 - 1772 .
Wang Niansun ( Chinese : 王念孫 ) ( 1744 - 1832 ) , courtesy name :
Richard Blome ( 1635 - 1705 ) was a publisher and cartographer from the Kingdom of England .
Bernard Eyston , D.D. ( 1628 - -1709 ) , was an English Franciscan friar , called in religion Bernard à Sancto Francisco .
Ján Valašťan Dolinský ( 15 February 1892 , Békéscsaba ( Békéšská Čaba ) -- 2 March 1965 , Nitra ) was a Slovak composer , teacher , journalist , esperantist and collector of folk songs .
Sir Edward Osborne ( 1530?--1591 ) , was one of the principal merchants of London in the later sixteenth century , and Lord Mayor of London in 1583 .
Fred Fox ( 22 January 1884 -- 1 December 1949 ) was an English assistant director and film actor .
Dominique Pierrat ( 11 February 1820 , Gerbamont -- 19 November 1893 , Gerbamont ) was a French naturalist known for botanical and zoological investigations of Vosges .
Pathologic ( Russian : Мор. Утопия , tr . Mor . Utopiya ; IPA : ( mˈor . ʊtˈopʲɪjə ) ; En . Pestilence . Utopia ) is a 2005 psychological horror adventure survival role - playing video game developed by Russian game studio Ice - Pick Lodge .
Dungeon Party is a 3D MMOG developed by Cyanide Studio .
Lost Eden is an adventure game produced by Cryo Interactive and published by Virgin Interactive in March 1995 for the PC running DOS , Macintosh , 3DO and CD - i . It is set in a world where humans and dinosaurs coexist .
Zombie Tycoon is a real - time strategy for the PlayStation Portable developed by Frima Studio and published by Sony Computer Entertainment , with the participation of Telefilm Canada .
CityDesk is a proprietary Content Management System created by Fog Creek Software , which was founded by Joel Spolsky .

Racing Hero is a 1989 arcade game from Sega which runs on Sega 's X Board hardware ( the same hardware used for games such as After Burner and Power Drift ) .
Moto Roader ( spelled Motoroader in Europe ) is a futuristic racing game developed by Hudson Soft for the TurboGrafx-16 and is also available on the Nintendo Wii 's Virtual Console .

360 Secure Browser ( Chinese : 360安全浏览器 ) is a web browser developed by the Qihoo company of Beijing , China .
Rush Rush Rally Racing , also known as R4 , is an independently developed , commercially released videogame developed by Senile Team and published by RedSpotGames .
Harrier Attack is a computer game for the Amstrad CPC , Commodore 64 , Oric 1 and ZX Spectrum initially released in 1983 by Durell Software .
Escape Velocity Nova ( a.k.a . EV Nova or EVN ) is a video game by Ambrosia Software , in collaboration with ATMOS .

HERO Hosted PBX is a SIP - based hosted IP - PBX business phone system , first released in 2008 by Canadian telecommunications software provider Dialexia .
Angry Birds Epic is a free - to - play role - playing video game that is the ninth installment in the Angry Birds series , developed by Chimera Entertainment and published by Rovio Entertainment .
Originally conceived and written by Allen Razdow ( of MIT , co - founder of Mathsoft ) , Mathcad is now owned by PTC and is generally accepted as the first computer application to automatically compute and check consistency of engineering units such as the International System of Units ( SI ) , throughout the entire set of calculations .
DJMax Portable 2 ( DJMAX Portable 2 , DMP2 ; Korean : 디제이맥스 포터블 2 ) is a music video game published and developed by Pentavision , for the PlayStation Portable which was released on March 30 , 2007 .
Microsoft Internet Explorer 5 ( IE5 ) is a discontinued graphical web browser and one of the main participants of the first browser war .

NBA 2K14 is a basketball video game that was developed by Visual Concepts and published by 2 K Sports .

The Nieuwe Republiek ( `` New Republic '' ) was a small Boer republic , which existed from 1884 to 1888 in present - day South Africa .
The Electoral district of Port Phillip was an electorate of the New South Wales Legislative Council before it became the separate colony of Victoria ( Australia ) on 1 July 1851 .
The New Zealand Shipping Company ( NZSC ) was a shipping company whose ships ran passenger and cargo services between Great Britain and New Zealand between 1873 and 1973 .
The Colony of Southern Rhodesia was a self - governing British Crown colony in southern Africa from 1923 to 1980 , equivalent in territorial terms to modern Zimbabwe .
Połock Voivodeship ( Polish : Województwo połockie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth ( Grand Duchy of Lithuania ) since the 15th century until the partitions of Poland in 1793 .
The Hartford Blues of the National Football League played only in the 1926 NFL season , with a record of 3 - -7 .
The Second French Empire ( French : Le Second empire français ) was the Imperial Bonapartist regime of Napoleon III from 1852 to 1870 , between the Second Republic and the Third Republic , in France .
The Gallic Empire ( Latin : Imperium Galliarum ) is the modern name for a breakaway part of the Roman Empire that functioned de facto as a separate state from 260 to 274 .

Parekklisia ( Greek : Παρεκκλησιά ( locally ( parekliˈʃa ) ) ) is a town in the Limassol District of Cyprus , located northeast of Agios Tychonas .
The Hluhluwe River originates in the Hluhluwe Game Reserve , KwaZulu - Natal , South Africa .
Ochraniew ( ɔˈxraɲef ) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Zduńska Wola , within Zduńska Wola County , Łódź Voivodeship , in central Poland .
The Château de la Roche is a ruined castle situated in the commune of Bellefosse in the Bas - Rhin département in Alsace , France .
The Söse Dam is a dam in the Lower Saxon part of the Harz mountains near Osterode in the German state of Lower Saxony .
Bircham Tofts is one of the three villages that make up the civil parish of Bircham , in the west of the English county of Norfolk .
One London Place is an office tower in London , Ontario , Canada .
The Protestant Children 's Home , also known as the Protestant Orphans ' Asylum , is a historic orphanage building in Mobile , Alabama , United States .

The AGM-129 ACM ( Advanced Cruise Missile ) was a low - observable , subsonic , turbofan - powered , air - launched cruise missile originally designed and built by General Dynamics and eventually acquired by Raytheon Missile Systems .

The Hino Liesse II is a rebadged Toyota Coaster .
The EE-11 Urutu is a combat proven 6x6 armored personnel carrier developed by Engesa of Brazil .

MAZ-504 is a Soviet truck , manufactured at the Minsk Automobile Plant .
The Colt Canada C7 rifle is a Canadian assault rifle , manufactured by Colt Canada ( formerly Diemaco prior to 2005 ) , a variant of the Armalite AR-15 , and having similar design and function to the Colt M16A3 .

VAXmate was an IBM PC / AT compatible personal computer introduced by Digital Equipment Corporation in September , 1986 .

In mathematics , Puiseux series are a generalization of power series , first introduced by Isaac Newton in 1676 and rediscovered by Victor Puiseux in 1850 , that allows for negative and fractional exponents of the indeterminate T. A Puiseux series in the indeterminate T is a Laurent series in T1/n , where n is a positive integer .

Diedrich Diederichsen is a prolific writer whose articles and texts are printed in a variety of periodicals and publications .
Dr . Pappu Venugopala Rao ( born 30 June 1948 ) is a well - known Indian educationist and renowned musicologist .
Daniel Patrick Ellis ( Born May 3 , 1988 ) is an American actor , best known for his work as a former child model and now today as an actor , in both movies and television , as well as a singer with albums and tours .
The Berlin Painter ( active c. 490s - c . 460s BCE ) is the conventional name given to an Attic Greek vase - painter who is widely regarded as a rival to the Kleophrades Painter , among the most talented vase painters of the early 5th century BCE ( see Pottery of Ancient Greece ) .
Raj Krishna was an Indian economist who taught at the Delhi School of Economics .
Chuck Ainlay is a record producer and audio engineer .
Kaadyr - ool Bicheldey ( Russian : Каадыр-оол Бичелдей ; born January 2 , 1950 ) is a Russian philologist and politician of Tuvan descent .

Dr. Steven Kull is a political psychologist who studies public opinion on public policy .
Donnovan Malik Blocker ( born May 13 , 1992 ) , commonly known by his stage name Dyme - A - Duzin , is an American rapper from Brooklyn , New York .
Frank Van Deren Coke , F. Van Deren Coke , or Van Deren Coke ( July 4 , 1921 -- July 11 , 2004 ) was an American photographer , scholar and museum professional .

Alhaji Mohamed Kemoh Fadika ( born in Bo , Sierra Leone ) is a Sierra Leonean diplomat and the current Sierra Leone 's ambassador to Iran .

Fiona Hayes ( b. September 13 , 1982 ) is an Irish rugby union player .
Mark Bayes ( born 15 March 1967 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Sydney Swans in the Victorian / Australian Football League .
Steve Veriato ( born May 6 , 1946 ) is an American professional golfer who played on the PGA Tour , Asian Tour , Canadian Tour , and Champions Tour where he won once .
Eugen Siebecke was a German politician and member of the SPD .
Chang Chun - hsiung ( traditional Chinese : 張俊雄 ; simplified Chinese : 张俊雄 ; pinyin : Zhāng Jùnxióng ; Pe̍h - ōe - jī : Tiuⁿ Chùn - hiông ) , born March 23 , 1938 is a Taiwanese politician .
John Knox Blair ( September 19 , 1873 -- November 11 , 1950 ) was a Canadian politician , physician and teacher .
He was an engineer by trade and at some point in his adult life , inherited the title 4th Baron Bliss of the Kingdom of Portugal from an ancestor named Sir John Moore .
Hélène Brodeur ( July 13 , 1923 -- August 15 , 2010 ) was a Franco - Ontarian educator , journalist and writer .
Diamanda Galás ( born August 29 , 1955 ) is an American avant - garde composer , vocalist , pianist , organist , performance artist , and painter .
Tori Sparks ( born December 5 , 1983 ) is an American singer - songwriter known for her unconventional lyrics and her blending of folk , rock , and blues influences .
Harvey Slocum ( October 23 , 1887 - November 11 , 1961 ) was an American civil engineer and dam - building expert , known primarily for his part in the construction of Grand Coulee Dam in the United States and the Bhakra Dam in India .
Connie Bruck is an award - winning American journalist and a reporter on subjects covering business and politics .
David Holliday ( August 4 , 1937 -- March 26 , 1999 ) was an American Broadway actor and television voice actor .
Igor Raykhelson ( Russian : Игорь Райхельсон ; born 24 April 1961 in Leningrad ) is a Russian born American classical and jazz pianist and composer .
P. Ramdas ( 1933 - -2014 ) was an Indian film director and screenwriter best known for his film Newspaper Boy which was influenced by Italian neorealism .
Wolfgang Kraushaar ( born 2 September 1948 ) is a political scientist and historian at the Hamburger Institut für Sozialforschung .
Joseph Ulysse Edgar Rochette ( April 28 , 1890 -- June 15 , 1953 ) was a Canadian lawyer , judge , and provincial politician .
A. Hays Town ( June 17 , 1903 -- January 6 , 2005 ) was an American architect whose career spanned over sixty - five years .
Tamela D'Amico is an American jazz singer , actress , and filmmaker .
Robert Kennicott ( November 13 , 1835 -- May 13 , 1866 ) was an American naturalist and herpetologist .
Thomas Alan Greene , known as Tom Greene ( born September 7 , 1948 ) , is a veterinarian and rancher from Maringouin in Iberville Parish , Louisiana , who served in the Louisiana State Senate from 1992 to 2000 .
Kathrin Haacker ( born April 3 , 1967 in Wismar ) is a German former rower , who competed for SC Dynamo Berlin .
Matti Kovler ( born September 14 , 1980 ) ( Hebrew : מתי קובלר‎ ) is a Russian - born Israeli - American composer , creator of new music theatre works , and the executive and artistic director of Floating Tower .

Frank Shepard Fairey ( born February 15 , 1970 ) is an American contemporary street artist , graphic designer , activist , illustrator and founder of OBEY ( clothing ) who emerged from the skateboarding scene .

William Shakespeare Hays ( July 19 , 1837 -- July 23 , 1907 ) , was an American poet and lyricist .
Doretta Morrow ( January 27 , 1927 -- February 28 , 1968 ) was an American actress , singer , and dancer who appeared in stage and television productions during the 1940s and 1950s .
Eduard Prugovečki ( March 19 , 1937 -- October 13 , 2003 ) was a Canadian physicist and mathematician of Croatian - Romanian descent .
Mohammad Nadeem Khan ( Urdu : محمد ندیم خان‎ ; born December 10 , 1969 , Rawalpindi , Punjab ) is a former Pakistani cricketer who played in 2 Tests and 2 ODIs from 1993 to 1999 .
Karl Wallenda ( January 21 , 1905 -- March 22 , 1978 ) was a German - American high wire artist and founder of The Flying Wallendas , a daredevil circus act which performed dangerous stunts , often without a safety net .

Jean - Paul Bruneteau is a French - Australian chef and author who is credited with playing a pioneering role in the development of an authentic Australian cuisine based on indigenous ingredients .
Tony Tarracino ( August 10 , 1916 -- November 1 , 2008 ) , commonly called Captain Tony , was an American saloonkeeper , boat captain , politician , gambler , and storyteller in Key West , Florida .

John Boese , AIA , ( pronounced BOW - SE ) was a minor American architect practicing in New York City in the late nineteenth and early twentieth century .
