The Opening Bell on Fox Business was an American business news program airing on the Fox Business Network at 9:00am Eastern Time and was hosted by Alexis Glick until December 23 , 2009 .
Bringing Up Buddy is an American situation comedy which aired on CBS during the 1960 - -1961 season .
Amish in the City is an American reality television series which premiered on UPN on July 28 , 2004 .
Sons of Guns is a reality television series that aired on the Discovery Channel between 2011 and 2014 .
Morning Becomes Eclectic ( MBE ) is a three - hour adult album alternative radio program first aired in 1977 and broadcast live every weekday from KCRW in Santa Monica , California .
Basta Sports is an informative sports program created by the ABS - CBN Foundation and airs weekly on ABS - CBN .
The Dutch Top 40 is one of the three official charts in the Netherlands , the other two being the Single Top 100 , which is based entirely on sales and streaming and the Mega Top 50 ( 3FM ) which , like the Dutch Top 40 also includes airplay data .
Tomasa Tequiero ( I Love Tomasa ) is a Venezuelan telenovela that was produced and aired on Venevisión between 2009 and 2010 .
`` Hi Hi Puffy Club '' , more accurately titled `` Hi Hi Puffy Bu '' ( Hi Hi Puffy 部 Hi Hi Puffy Kurabu ) is Puffy AmiYumi 's reality television series , which premiered on TV Asahi on 22 July 2007 .
Shel Mi HaShura HaZot ? ( Hebrew : של מי השורה הזאת‎ , lit . Whose Line Is It ? ) is an Israeli version of the British improvisational comedy TV show Whose Line Is It Anyway ? , which aired from 2000 to 2001 on Channel 2 and from 2006 to 2007 on Channel 10 .
ITV News London is a regional news programme for the ITV London region ( previously Carlton / LWT ) , produced by ITN .
The Real L Word is an American reality television series aired on the cable station Showtime , where it premiered on June 20 , 2010 .
Masters of Sex is an American period drama television series that premiered on September 29 , 2013 , on Showtime .
Gamer 's Guide to Pretty Much Everything is a live - action comedy series created by Devin Bunje and Nick Stanton , and produced by Devin Bunje , Nick Stanton , and Jim O'Doherty for Disney XD .
Justice League Unlimited ( JLU ) is an American animated television series that was produced by Warner Bros. Animation and aired on Cartoon Network .
Top of the Pops 2 ( also known as TOTP2 ) is a British television music show broadcast on BBC Two , showing archive footage from the long - running Top of the Pops show , some dating back to the 1960s when the programme first aired on British television .
The Rockford Files is an American television drama series starring James Garner that aired on the NBC network between 1974 to 1980 and has remained in syndication to the present day .
TV Nation is a satirical newsmagazine television series written , directed and hosted by Michael Moore that was co - funded and originally broadcast by NBC in the United States and BBC2 in the United Kingdom .
Office Monkey was a British Hidden Camera Comedy programme that aired on ITV2 for 2 series .
Yasmin 's Getting Married was a short - lived Australian reality television program that aired live on Network Ten in early August 2006 .
America Undercover is a series of documentaries that airs on the cable television network HBO .
Not Necessarily the News is a satirical sketch comedy series that first aired on HBO in September 1982 as a comedy special , and then ran as a series from 1983 to 1990 .
Raising the Roofs is a 2006 reality television show on Spike TV , following the life of aspiring actor Michael Roof , and the misadventures of his self described Florida cracker dad and uncle , in Hollywood , California .
Atlanta Exes is an American reality documentary television series on VH1 that premiered on August 18 , 2014 .
The Cool Stuff Collective is a British children 's television programme , which was produced for three series that aired on the ITV Network and CITV respectively from 13 September 2010 to 24 December 2011 .
Canal de las Estrellas aired the series from February 28 to August 26 , 2011 , Univision aired 2 hours of Ni contigo ni sin ti from October 18 to October 28 , 2011 , and then it aired in 1 hour from October 31 , 2011 to April 6 , 2012 at 2pm/1c .
P.S. I Luv U is an American crime drama series that aired on CBS as a part of its 1991 - 92 schedule .
Dead Boss is a British sitcom shown on BBC Three .
Penthouse Party is a TV variety series which aired on American Broadcasting Company in 1950 and 1951 .
Mr. Dressup was developed and produced by Daniel McCarthy , who later became the head of children 's programming for CBC Television .
Knightmare is a British television programme for children and was broadcast on CITV from 7 September 1987 to 11 November 1994 .
The Big Surprise is a television quiz show broadcast in the United States by NBC from October 8 , 1955 , to June 9 , 1956 , and from September 18 , 1956 , to April 2 , 1957 .
La ley del silencio is an American telenovela produced by Telemundo in 2003 .
AJ 's Infinite Summer is an animated television pilot created by Toby Jones for Cartoon Network .
Music From Chicago was a program broadcast on the DuMont Television Network from WGN - TV in Chicago on Sundays .
We Have Ways of Making You Laugh was a comedic television series produced by Humphrey Barclay and directed by Bill Turner for London Weekend Television .
Flor do Caribe ( English : Caribbean Flower ) is a Brazilian telenovela produced and broadcast by Rede Globo originally ran from March 11 to September 19 , 2013 .
Colonel Humphrey Flack is an American sitcom which ran Wednesdays at 9 pm ET from October 7 , 1953 to July 2 , 1954 on the DuMont Television Network , then revived from 1958 to 1959 for first - run syndication .
Leptopilina is a genus of parasitoid wasp in the family Figitidae .
Pseudomelatomidae is a family of predatory sea snails , marine gastropods included in the superfamily Conoidea ( previously Conacea ) and part of the Neogastropoda ( Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Dracoglossum was originally treated in Tectaria , but is not related and was therefore described in family Dryopteridaceae .
Weintrauboa is a spider genus of the small Pimoidae family .
The Anchieta 's ridged frog or plain grass frog ( Ptychadena anchietae ) is a species of frog in the Ptychadenidae family .
The Punta de Vacas chinchilla rat ( Abrocoma vaccarum ) , also known as the Mendozan chinchilla rat , is a species of chinchilla rats in the family Abrocomidae .
Sapranthus is a genus of flowering woody plants in the family Annonaceae .
While other genera from the family Palaemonidae are known from the Aptian age in the lower Cretaceous period , Yongjiacaris represents the first member described from the Barremian age .
Maurandella is an obsolete genus of flowering plants in the plantain family , Plantaginaceae .
The Afep pigeon ( Columba unicincta ) , also known as the African wood - pigeon or gray wood - pigeon , is a member of the family Columbidae which lives in Africa .
The Coosa rocksnail , scientific name †Leptoxis showalterii , also known as the `` ribbed rocksnail '' , was a species of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pleuroceridae .
The Hildebrandt 's francolin ( Pternistis hildebrandti ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Pacifichelys is an extinct genus of sea turtle from the Miocene of Peru and California .
Jaimehintonia is a genus of plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Brodiaeoideae , first described in 1993 .
Callionymus grossi , Gross 's stinkfish , is a species of dragonet found in the waters off of northwestern Australia .
Verticordiidae is a taxonomic family of very small saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the order Pholadomyoida .
Wright 's sportive lemur ( Lepilemur wrightae ) , or the Kalambatritra sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Tricuspes is an extinct genus of cynodont that lived in what would be Europe during the Triassic from 203.6 - -199.6 mya , existing for approximately 4 million years .
Oenococcus is a genus of Gram - positive bacteria , placed within the family Leuconostocaceae .
The Society parakeet ( Cyanoramphus ulietanus ) , also known as the Society kakariki or brown - headed parakeet , is an extinct parakeet of the genus Cyanoramphus .
The New Guinea big - eared bat ( Pharotis imogene ) is a vesper bat endemic to Papua New Guinea .
The Gran Canaria giant rat ( Canariomys tamarani ) is an extinct species of rat endemic to the island of Gran Canaria ( Canary Islands , Spain ) .
Kohekohe ( Dysoxylum spectabile ) is a medium - sized tree native to New Zealand .
The Levant water frog ( Pelophylax bedriagae ) , formerly belonging to the genus Rana , is a southern European species of frog .
The Pyrenean desman ( Galemys pyrenaicus ) is a small semiaquatic nocturnal mammal related to moles and shrews , and is one of only two surviving species of the tribe Desmanini .
Apium ( including celery and the marshworts ) is a genus of about 20 species of flowering plants in the family Apiaceae , with a subcosmopolitan distribution in Europe , Asia , Africa , South America and Australia .
Stenanthium is a North American genus of flowering plants in the family Melanthiaceae , tribe Melanthieae .
Cephetola sublustris , the Greasy Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Fort Maguire aulonocara ( Aulonocara hansbaenschi ) , also known as Aulonocara ' Fort Maguire ' in the aquarium fish trade , is a species of fish in the Cichlidae family .
Platax is a genus of Indo - Pacific , reef - associated fish belonging to the family Ephippidae .
Ariolimacidae is a family of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Arionoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Mozambique girdled lizard or flame - bellied armadillo lizard ( Smaug mossambicus ) is a large , flattened , girdled lizard found in the Gorongosa Mountains in Mozambique and low elevations in the Chimanimani Mountains at the border of Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
Cymaceras is a genus within the oppeliid subfamily Ochetoceratinae from the Kimmeridgian stage , around the middle of the Upper Jurassic .
Pentachondra is a genus of prostrate shrubs in the family Ericaceae .
The Mongolian redfin ( Chanodichthys mongolicus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Chanodichthys .
The Cape hare ( Lepus capensis ) , also called brown hare and desert hare is a hare native to Africa and Arabia extending into India .
The Ankole mole - rat or Ankole African mole - rat ( Tachyoryctes ankoliae ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae found in Angola and Uganda .
The Hydromylidae are a taxonomic family of small sea slugs , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the suborder Gymnosomata , the sea angels .
Cecidothyris is a genus of moths of the Thyrididae family from Africa .
Zootermopsis is a genus of termites ( Isoptera ) in the family Termopsidae , a group known as the dampwood termites .
Gryllacridinae is a cricket subfamily in the family Gryllacrididae .
Orchidinae is one of two subtribes of the tribe Orchideae in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) of flowering plants .
The family Archaeopterygidae is the only family in the order Archaeopterygiformes , which was coined by Max Fürbringer in 1888 to contain Archaeopterygidae and genus Archaeopteryx .
Cliftonoceras is a barrandeoceroid type tarphycerid from the Uranoceratidae characterized by a smooth gyroconic shell with a rounded dorsum and flattened venter , and by a subvental siphuncle composed of thin connecting rings and necks that are straight ventrally , recumbent dorsally .
Mango mealybug ( Drosicha mangiferae ) , is a pest of mango crops in Asia .
The Banggai cuscus ( Strigocuscus pelengensis ) is a species of marsupial in the family Phalangeridae .
The Snow Mountains grassland mosaic - tailed rat ( Melomys frigicola ) , also known as the Snow Mountains grassland melomys , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Cook reed warbler or Cook Islands reed warbler ( Acrocephalus kerearako ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
The Philippine crocodile ( Crocodylus mindorensis ) , also known as the Mindoro crocodile , the Philippine freshwater crocodile or locally , bukarot , is one of two species of crocodile that are found in the Philippines , the other is the larger Indo - Pacific crocodile or saltwater crocodile ( Crocodylus porosus ) .
The Osteoglossomorpha are a group of bony fish in the Teleostei .
Amusium is a genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks belonging to the family Pectinidae .
Vulcanophilus calathoides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Vulcanophilus .
Emathis is a genus of the spider family Salticidae ( jumping spiders ) with ten described species .
Walter 's duiker ( Philantomba walteri ) is a species of duiker found in Togo , Benin and Nigeria .
Platygryllus is a genus of the true cricket family Gryllidae .
The Daurian ground squirrel ( Spermophilus dauricus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Hexalectris ( crested coralroot ) is a genus of the family Orchidaceae , comprising 10 known species of fully myco - heterotrophic orchids .
The Nile tilapia ( Oreochromis niloticus ) is a species of tilapia , a cichlid fish native to Africa from Egypt south to East and Central Africa , and as far west as Gambia .
The Fernando Po swift ( Apus sladeniae ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
The Sunda robin ( Myiomela diana ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Parvitragulus is an extinct genus belonging to the family Hypertragulidae , within the order Artiodactyla , endemic to North America during the Eocene , living 38 - -33.9 Ma , existing for approximately 4.1 million years .
Albertonykus is a member of an unusual theropod group known as the Alvarezsauridae and is one of only a few alvarezsaurid fossils that has been found outside of South America and Asia .
Spelaeovulcania canariensis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Spelaeovulcania .
Xylocopa darwini , the Galápagos carpenter bee , is the only native species of bee found in the Galápagos Islands , to which it is endemic .
The Kirby 's tiger ( Parantica kirbyi ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Finsch 's euphonia ( Euphonia finschi ) is a species of bird in the Fringillidae family .
Campnosperma is a genus of plant in the family Anacardiaceae .
Fumaria muralis , known as common ramping - fumitory or wall fumitory , is a many branched , annual herbaceous plant , native to Europe .
Ombrocharis is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1936 .
Archispirostreptus is a genus of giant African millipedes in family Spirostreptidae , containing 26 species :
The Cuban gambusia ( Gambusia punctata ) is a species of freshwater fish .
Lophotis is a genus of bustard in the family Otididae .
Gadus is a genus of demersal fish in the family Gadidae , commonly known as cod , although there are additional cod species in other genera .
The Mascarene grass frog or Mascarene ridged frog ( Ptychadena mascareniensis ) is a species of frog in the Ptychadenidae family .
Fenouilia is a genus of small freshwater snails with gills and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
The Bocage 's sunbird ( Nectarinia bocagii ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
The Chinese hamster ( Cricetulus griseus ) , is a species of hamster originating from the deserts of northern China and Mongolia .
The Chocó vireo ( Vireo masteri ) is a species of bird in the Vireonidae family .
Rainiera is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Holocompsa is a genus of hairy sand cockroaches in the family Polyphagidae .
Obigrella nigra is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The African pygmy squirrel ( Myosciurus pumilio ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Anthaxioides aurorus is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Anthaxioides .
The Crocodilefish ( Cymbacephalus beauforti ) , also known as De Beaufort 's flathead or Giant flathead , is a member of the order Scorpaeniformes , which also includes the scorpionfishes and stonefishes .
Caspian gull is a name applied to the gull taxon Larus cachinnans , a member of the herring gull / lesser black - backed gull complex .

Dendrocnide is a genus of 37 species of shrubs to large trees in the nettle family Urticaceae .
Hyriidae is a taxonomic family of pearly freshwater mussels , aquatic bivalve mollusks in the order Unionoida .
Phymatopus lack spurs on the tibiae and like other members of the Hepialidae family , also lack a proboscis or frenulum and have very short antennae .
The Ormyridae are a small family of parasitic wasps in the superfamily Chalcidoidea .
The Bolivian tyrannulet ( Zimmerius bolivianus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Elaphidionopsis fasciatipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Elaphidionopsis .
Feostoma irregulare is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Feostoma .
The Caparaó grass mouse , Akodon mystax , is a rodent species from South America .
Thor 's hero shrew ( Scutisorex thori ) is an extant species of shrew native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
The Pacific gopher snake ( Pituophis catenifer catenifer ) is a subspecies of large nonvenomous colubrid snake native to the western coast of the United States .
The Malayan snail - eating turtle ( Malayemys macrocephala ) is a species of turtle in Malayemys genus of the Geoemydidae family .
The European leaf - toed gecko or the European leaf - toed gekko ( Euleptes europaea ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
The Aspredinidae are a small South American family of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) also known as the banjo catfishes , with about 39 species .
The American herring gull or Smithsonian gull ( Larus smithsonianus or Larus argentatus smithsonianus ) is a large gull that breeds in North America , where it is treated by the American Ornithologists ' Union as a subspecies of herring gull ( L. argentatus ) .
The Horsfield 's shrew ( Crocidura horsfieldii ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Litaneutria is genus of praying mantises in the family Mantidae represented by species of ground mantis .
The Ouachita dusky salamander ( Desmognathus brimleyorum ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
The Argentine fat - tailed mouse opossum ( Thylamys sponsorius ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
In a 2008 phylogenetic analysis , Aiolosaurus was classified as a member of Varanidae .
Ailuropoda is the only extant genus in the ursid ( bear ) subfamily Ailuropodinae .
Cerautola semibrunnea , the Semibrown Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Marquesan swiftlet ( Aerodramus ocistus ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Ctenophryne aterrima ( common name : Costa Rica Nelson frog , reflecting its earlier placement in Nelsonophryne ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Colsyrnola is a small genus of minute sea snails or marine gastropod mollusks within the subfamily Syrnolinae , which is a part of the family Pyramidellidae .
Warnockia is a genus from the family Lamiaceae , first described in 1996 .
The Cuban nightjar ( Antrostomus cubanensis ) , is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
Cox 's roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros coxi ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
The Baron 's spinetail ( Cranioleuca baroni ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Lithodryas is a prehistoric genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
Candiru ( English and Portuguese or candirú in Spanish ) , Vandellia cirrhosa , also known as cañero , toothpick fish , or vampire fish , is a species of parasitic freshwater catfish in the family Trichomycteridae native to the Amazon Basin where it is found in the countries of Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
The relationships of Heterolepis to other genera in Asteraceae are not well understood .
Betula austrosinensis ( Chinese : 华南桦 ; pinyin : hua nan hua ) is a species of birch that is endemic to China where it is found on elevation of 700 - -1,900 metres ( 2,300 - -6,200 ft ) .
Eothyris is an extinct genus of the family Eothyrididae .
The Andaman treepie ( Dendrocitta bayleyi ) is a species of bird in the family Corvidae .
Erythromelana is a genus of flies in the family Tachinidae .
The Tandy 's sand frog ( Tomopterna tandyi ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Atrax yorkmainorum is a species of Australian funnel - web spider found in forests in the vicinity of Canberra and southeastern New South Wales .
Stegolepis is a group of plants in the family Rapateaceae described as a genus in 1872 .
The Chloephorinae is a subfamily of the moth family Nolidae .
Liposcelididae ( historically often referred to as `` Liposcelidae '' ) is a family of barklice ( Psocoptera ) belonging to the suborder Troctomorpha .
Striped Raphael catfish ( Platydoras armatulus ) is a catfish of the family Doradidae .
Lepteutypa is a genus of plant pathogens in the family Amphisphaeriaceae .
Xenitenopsis jacoti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Xenitenopsis .
The Ozark shiner ( Notropis ozarcanus ) is a species of freshwater cyprinid fish from Missouri and Arkansas , USA .
The Lewin 's honeyeater ( Meliphaga lewinii ) is a bird that inhabits the ranges along the east coast of Australia .
Neoibidion comatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Neoibidion .
Kindleoceras is an oncocerid genus belonging to the Valcouroceratidae , extinct nautiloid cephalopods that lived during the Middle and Late Ordovician .
The Sumatran striped rabbit ( Nesolagus netscheri ) , also known as the Sumatra short - eared rabbit or Sumatran rabbit , is a rabbit found only in forests in the Barisan Mountains in western Sumatra , Indonesia and surrounding areas .
Ancylastrum is a genus of air - breathing freshwater limpets , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
The Moupin pika ( Ochotona thibetana ) is a species of mammal in the pika family , Ochotonidae .
Melanodytes pustulatus is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Melanodytes .
Ildobates neboti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Ildobates .
Kossmaticeras is an extinct ammonoid genus belonging to the desmoceratacean family Kossmaticeratidae .
Ambrosi 's cave salamander , the French cave salamander , or the Spezia cave salamander ( Speleomantes ambrosii ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Ridley 's leaf - nosed bat , Ridley 's roundleaf bat , or Singapore roundleaf horseshoe bat ( Hipposideros ridleyi ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Trichilia is a flowering plant genus in the family Meliaceae .
The Prolecanitaceae are also sometimes known as the suborder Prolecanitina .
Macaca jiangchuanensis is a prehistoric macaque from the early Holocene of China .
The Main 's frog ( Cyclorana maini ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Neohelice granulata is a species of crab in the family Varunidae , and the only species in the genus Neohelice .
Previously Ataxioceras was assigned to the Perisphinctidae but has now been placed in the Ataxioceratidae for which it is the type genus .
Diapheromerinae is a subfamily of the stick insect family Diapheromeridae .
Copholandrevus is a genus of cricket in the family Gryllidae .
Mandela 's nudibranch , Mandelia mirocornata , is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch .
Fraxinus hubeiensis is a species of ash native to Hubei province in China .
The Salokko rat ( Taeromys arcuatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Galtonia is a genus of plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae .
Dichostemma is a flowering plant genus in the Family Euphorbiaceae ( Spurge family ) first described as a genus in 1896 .
The European mole ( Talpa europaea ) is a mammal of the order Eulipotyphla .
Prionus Geoffroy , 1762 is a genus of long - horned beetles of the subfamily Prioninae , tribe Prionini , widespread in Europe , Asia and North America .
Acidobacteria are a newly devised phylum of Bacteria , whose members are physiologically diverse and ubiquitous , especially in soils , but are under - represented in culture .
Enneapterygius vexillarius , known commonly as the Blacksaddle triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Hamilton 's barb ( Barbus afrohamiltoni ) , also known as the plump barb , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .

The Drakensberg dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion dracomontanum ) occurs in the Drakensberg , South Africa .
Axonya championi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Axonya .
Dolichothrix is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
Vochysiaceae is a plant family belonging to the order of Myrtales .
The family containing Moschorhinus is Akidnognathidae , large , carnivorous theraspids all sharing strong skulls and large upper canines .
The Andean mouse ( Andinomys edax ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Phacops is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , family Phacopidae , that lived in Europe , northwestern Africa , North America and China from the early until the very end of the Devonian .
Desmodema lorum Rosenblatt & J. L. Butler , 1977 ( Whiptail ribbonfish ) Desmodema polystictum ( J. D. Ogilby , 1898 ) ( Polka - dot ribbonfish )
Strepsiduridae is a taxonomic family of predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Muricoidea , but its position is doubtful .
The Turbellaria are one of the traditional sub - divisions of the phylum Platyhelminthes ( flatworms ) , and include all the sub - groups that are not exclusively parasitic .
The Nymphalinae are a subfamily of brush - footed butterflies ( family Nymphalidae ) .
Cepora is a genus of butterflies , commonly called gulls , in the Pieridae family .
Protopterus is the sole genus in the family Protopteridae .
Alcidodes is a genus of weevils in the family Curculionidae .
Venaticosuchus is a member of Ornithosuchidae , a family of facultatively bipedal carnivores that were geographically widespread during the Late Triassic .
Joffre 's pipistrelle ( Hypsugo joffrei ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Gobius geniporus , the Slender goby , is a species of goby endemic to the Mediterranean Sea where it can be found in inshore waters to a depth of about 30 metres ( 98 ft ) .
The Cayenne stubfoot toad ( Atelopus flavescens ) , known in French as atélope jaunâtre , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae found in northeastern French Guiana and in the adjacent Brazilian state Amapá .
The Alaska blackfish , Dallia pectoralis , is a fish that grows to 7 in ( 180 mm ) in length .
Brants 's whistling rat ( Parotomys brantsii ) is one of two species of Murid rodent in the genus Parotomys .
The Caribbean roughshark ( Oxynotus caribbaeus ) is a rough shark of the family Oxynotidae , found on the upper continental slopes of the Caribbean Sea , at depths between 400 and 450 m ( 1,310 and 1,480 ft ) .
Altenglanerpeton belongs to a similar group called Recumbirostra , which is a clade .
The Mount Glorious day frog ( Taudactylus diurnus ) , also known as Mount Glorious torrent frog and southern day frog , is an extinct species of frog native to south - east Queensland .
Micropsalliota is a genus of small agaric fungi in the family Agaricaceae .
Pegomya is a genus of flies within the family Anthomyiidae .
Oligonicella is a wide - ranging genus of mantises in the family Thespidae .
The Caspian cobra ( Naja oxiana ) , also called the Central Asian cobra , Oxus cobra or Russian cobra , a member of the family Elapidae found in Central Asia .
Raphidiidae is a family of snakeflies in the order Raphidioptera .
Cosgriffius is an extinct genus of trematosaurian temnospondyl within the family Trematosauridae of the Moenkopi Formation .
Rivina is a genus of flowering plants in the pokeweed family , Phytolaccaceae .
The Indian pike conger ( Congresox talabonoides , also known as the common eel , the conger - pike eel , the daggertooth pike - conger , and the Indian putyekanipa ) is an eel in the family Muraenesocidae ( pike congers ) .
Eulamprus , the water skinks , are a genus of skinks in the subfamily Lygosominae .
Rhabdodendron is placed in its own family , Rhabdodendraceae , which has only been recognized for the past few decades .
Parakneria is a genus of fish in the family Kneriidae , with 14 species , all of which are restricted to Africa .
The Western patch - nosed snake , Salvadora hexalepis , is a species of nonvenomous colubrid snake , which is endemic to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
The Northern banjo frog ( Limnodynastes terraereginae ) is a species of ground - dwelling burrowing frog native to eastern Queensland and northeastern New South Wales , Australia .
The Junín grass mouse ( Akodon juninensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Sardinian tree frog or Tyrrhenian tree frog ( Hyla sarda ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , found in Corsica , Sardinia , and the Tuscan Archipelago .
The Tian Shan wapiti or Tian Shan maral ( Cervus canadensis songaricus ) , often called the Tian Shan elk by North Americans , is a subspecies of Cervus canadensis , found in the Tian Shan Mountains in eastern Kyrgyzstan , southeastern Kazakhstan , and North Central Xinjiang , China .
The Longdong stream salamander ( Batrachuperus londongensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family endemic to China .
The Madagascan grebe ( Tachybaptus pelzelnii ) is a grebe found only in western and central Madagascar .
Alnus formosana , or Formosan Alder , is a species of alder native to Taiwan .
Eumorsea is a genus of grasshoppers in the family Eumastacidae , the monkey grasshoppers .
The Malaysian earthtiger tarantula ( Cyriopagopus schioedtei ) is a large and colourful arboreal tarantula from the subfamily Ornithoctoninae .
Odontomasoreus humeralis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Odontomasoreus .
Aecidium is a genus of rust fungi in the Pucciniales order .
Doriva played for the Brazil national football team between 1995 and 1998 , making a brief substitute appearance in the 1998 FIFA World Cup in which Brazil finished as runners - up .
Václav Roubík ( born 16 August 1919 ) is a former Czech rower who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Cronier was a sailor from the France , who represented his native country at the 1900 Summer Olympics in Paris , France .
József Pércsi ( 19 March 1942 in Földes -- June 2011 ) was a Hungarian wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Utkirbek Haydarov ( Уткирбек Хайдаров ; born January 25 , 1974 in Andijon ) is an Uzbekistani boxer who competed in the light heavyweight ( 81 kg ) at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal .
Olavi Rinteenpää ( born 24 September 1924 ) is a Finnish former steeplechase runner who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics and in the 1956 Summer Olympics .
Bonaparti.lv is a sextet consisting of Latvian tenors , that participated in Eurovision Song Contest 2007 with their song `` Questa Notte '' .
Isabella Minna Veronica Wagner , better known as Veronica ( born July 7 , 1987 in Stockholm , Sweden ) , is a gymnast who competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics as a member of the Swedish Olympic team .
Yoko Isoda ( born 26 August 1978 ) is a Japanese synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Ewa Grabowska - Gaczorek ( born 8 September 1962 in Nowy Targ ) is a Polish former alpine skier who competed in the 1984 Winter Olympics .
William Frank Southall ( 2 July 1904 -- 1 March 1964 ) was an English racing cyclist who won silver medals for Great Britain in the individual road race ( run as an individual time trial ) at the 1928 Summer Olympics and a track cycling medal at the 1932 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles .
René Texier ( 28 October 1882 -- 10 October 1967 ) was a French sports shooter who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics , in the 1920 Summer Olympics , and in the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Marq Mellor ( born March 5 , 1968 in Long Island , New York ) is a former field hockey forward from the United States , who finished twelfth with the national team at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , Georgia .
Thomas Coe was a British water polo player who won a gold medal in the 1900 Summer Olympics .
Athanasia Tsoumeleka ( Greek : Αθανασία Τσουμελέκα , ( aθanaˈsia tsumeˈleka ) , born January 2 , 1982 ) is a Greek race walker , who won a gold medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens .
Aarzemnieki ( from the Latvian word `` ārzemnieki '' , meaning `` foreigners '' ) are a Latvian band that represented Latvia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2014 in Copenhagen , Denmark , with their song `` Cake to Bake '' .
Martin Urra ( 1931 -- 11 September 2002 ) was a Filipino basketball player who competed in the 1956 Summer Olympics .
On 11 October 2006 DJ BoBo announced in a press conference that he had applied to represent Switzerland at the Eurovision Song Contest 2007 .
Eric Niklas Henning ( born 6 March 1964 ) is a Swedish former alpine skier who competed in the 1984 and 1988 Winter Olympics .
Dimitar Zapryanov ( Bulgarian : Димитър Запрянов ) ( born 27 January 1960 ) is a Bulgarian former judoka who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Shawn O'Sullivan ( born May 9 , 1962 in Toronto , Ontario ) is a retired Canadian boxer who won gold at the World Amateur Championships in 1981 and the light middleweight silver medal at the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Javier Bosma started playing beach volleyball in 1994 and also competed at the 1996 Summer Olympics and the 2000 Summer Olympics , finishing 5th both times .
Alexandru Nyisztor ( born 27 June 1979 ) is a Romanian épée fencer , who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Charalambos Cholidis ( Greek : Χαράλαμπος Χολίδης , born 1 October 1956 ) is a Greek former wrestler who competed , in the 1976 Summer Olympics , in the 1980 Summer Olympics , in the 1984 Summer Olympics , and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Ramón Abeledo ( born 29 April 1937 ) is an Argentine football midfielder who played for Argentina in the 1962 FIFA World Cup .
Ignatius Gronkowski ( March 28 , 1897 -- September 1981 ) was an American professional cyclist , who represented the United States at the 1924 Summer Olympics in Paris .
Ernst Kyburz ( 14 August 1898 -- 16 October 1983 ) was a Swiss freestyle wrestler who won gold medals at the 1928 Summer Olympics and 1931 European Championships in the middleweight category .
Branko Skroče ( born 17 May 1955 in Zadar ) is a Croatian former basketball player who competed for Yugoslavia in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Jennifer Pinches ( born 25 May 1994 ) is a British artistic gymnast who competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Mamoru Morimoto ( Japanese : 森本 葵 , born 11 July 1939 ) is a Japanese former middle distance runner who competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Adriana Samuel Ramos ( born April 12 , 1966 in Resende , Rio de Janeiro ) is a Brazilian volleyball player , who won the silver medal in the inaugural women 's beach volleyball tournament at the 1996 Summer Olympics , partnering Mônica Rodrigues .
Ubaldesco Baldi ( 13 July 1944 -- 13 June 1991 ) was an Italian sport shooter who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics , winning a bronze medal in the Mixed Trap event .
Emily Halliday ( born 5 April 1979 ) is an Australian field hockey player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics and in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Silke Müller ( born November 11 , 1978 ) is a field hockey midfielder from Germany , who won the gold medal with the German National Women 's Team at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Jon Lilygreen ( born 4 August 1987 ) is a Welsh singer , who along with the band The Islanders represented Cyprus in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 in Oslo , Norway , with the song `` Life Looks Better in Spring '' and they took the 21st place out of 39 entrants .
Jon Holst - Christensen competed in badminton at the 1992 Summer Olympics in men 's doubles with Thomas Lund .
Gábor Boczkó ( born 1 April 1977 ) is a Hungarian fencer , who won a silver medal in the team Épée competition at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens together with Krisztián Kulcsár , Géza Imre and Iván Kovács .
Andrzej Piątkowski ( 22 October 1934 -- 11 June 2010 ) was a Polish sabreur who won three medals at the 1956 , 1960 and 1964 Summer Olympics .
Hena Akhter ( Bengali : হেনা আক্তার ) is a Bangladeshi national women Kabaddi player who was part of the team that won the bronze medal at the 2010 Asian Games .
William Meyers ( 23 July 1943 -- 7 May 2014 ) was a South African boxer who won a bronze medal at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome fighting as a featherweight .
Elen Shakirova ( née Bunatyants , born 2 June 1970 in Mary , Turkmen SSR ) is a Russian former basketball player who competed in the 1992 Summer Olympics , in the 1996 Summer Olympics , and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Andreas Stadler ( July 31 , 1896 -- February 14 , 1941 ) was an Austrian weightlifter who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics and in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Ranza Clark ( born December 13 , 1961 in Calgary , Alberta ) is a retired middle distance runner from Canada , who won the gold medal in the women 's 1.500 metres at the 1983 Pan American Games .
Attila Vári ( born February 26 , 1976 in Budapest ) , nicknamed Doki , is a Hungarian water polo player , who played on the gold medal squads at the 2000 Summer Olympics and 2004 Summer Olympics .
Li Yaguang ( born 8 June 1958 ) is a Chinese former basketball player who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Genaro Sermeño , ( born 28 November 1948 ) is a former footballer from El Salvador who represented his country at the 1970 FIFA World Cup in Mexico .
Ferenc Tégla ( born 15 July 1947 in Szegvár ) is a Hungarian former discus thrower who competed in the 1968 Summer Olympics , in the 1972 Summer Olympics , and in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Werner Obschernikat ( born 9 July 1955 in Duisburg ) is a German former water polo player who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics , in the 1984 Summer Olympics , and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Massimo Nistri ( born 10 October 1955 ) is an Italian former swimmer who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Károly Szittya ( June 18 , 1918 -- August 9 , 1983 ) was a Hungarian swimmer and water polo player who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics and in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Bernhard Knauß ( born 25 June 1965 in Schladming ) is an Austrian and later Slovenian former alpine skier who competed in the 1998 Winter Olympics .
Pierre Coppieters ( born 24 June 1907 , date of death unknown ) was a Belgian swimmer and water polo player who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics and in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Igor Hinić ( born 4 December 1975 in Rijeka ) is a water polo player from Croatia , who was a member of the national team that won the silver medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , Georgia and a member of the Croatian team that won gold in the water polo at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Eva Boto ( born December 1 , 1995 ) is a singer who represented Slovenia at the Eurovision Song Contest 2012 in Baku , Azerbaijan with Verjamem .
Ferenc Török received an individual gold medal at the 1964 Summer Olympics in Tokyo , and a bronze medal with the Hungarian team .
Bahri Tanrıkulu ( born March 16 , 1980 in Ankara , Turkey ) is a Turkish taekwondo practitioner , who competed in the Men 's 80 kg division at the 2004 Summer Olympics held in Athens , Greece and won the silver medal .
Jacqueline Delord ( born 29 January 1970 ) is a French former swimmer who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics , in the 1992 Summer Olympics , and in the 1996 Summer Olympics .
Catriona Sens ( née Oliver ) ( born 2 April 1980 in Sale , Victoria ) was a member of the Australia 's 2004 Summer Olympics women 's eight rowing crew with Sally Robbins .
Zhang Yufeng ( simplified Chinese : 张玉峰 ; traditional Chinese : 張玉峰 ; pinyin : Zhāng Yùfēng ; born 9 February 1977 in Shanghai , China ) is a Chinese baseball player who was a member of Team China at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Ali Asghar Bazri ( Persian : علی اصغر بذری‎ , born September 11 , 1980 in Behshahr , Iran ) is an Iranian wrestler who competed in the 2006 Asian Games in the 74 kg division and won the gold medal .
Léon Scieur ( pronounced : ( le.ɔ̃ sjœʁ ) ; 19 March 1888 -- 7 October 1969 ) was a Belgian cyclist who won the 1921 Tour de France , along with stages 3 and 10 .
Gaëtan Llorach ( born 16 January 1974 in Saint - Martin - d'Hères , Isère , France ) is a former French alpine skier who competed in the 2002 Winter Olympics .

Sven Pettersson ( born July 24 , 1927 in Härnösand ) is a Swedish ski jumper who competed in the 1950s .

Femi Emiola was born in Iowa City , Iowa to a Filipina mother and a Nigerian father , then both PhD candidates at the University of Iowa .
George Brittain ( born 1821 , Chester , England ) was Locomotive Superintendent of the Caledonian Railway from 1876 to 1882 , between Benjamin Connor and Dugald Drummond .

Alain Pellet ( born 2 January 1947 ) teaches international law and international economic law at the Université de Paris Ouest - Nanterre La Défense .

Corporal Sidney William Ware , VC , was born in November 1892 at Whatcombe in the Parish of Winterborne Whitechurch , Dorset .
Themis Rigas ( Greek : Θέμης Ρήγας ) ( born 1945 - died 13 January 1984 ) , popularly nicknamed The Train , is a former Greek footballer ( winger ) born in Patras .
André Alexis ( born 15 January 1957 in Port of Spain , Trinidad and Tobago ) is a Canadian writer who grew up in Ottawa and currently lives in Toronto , Ontario .
Philemon Holland , born at Chelmsford , Essex , in 1552 , was the son of John Holland ( d.1578 ) , a member of the same Norfolk family as John Holland , 1st Baron Holland ( 1603 - -1701 ) .
Arturo Naón ( born 31 December 1912 in La Plata , died 5 May 1999 ) was an Argentine football ( soccer ) striker .
Heinz Felfe was born in Dresden , in the southern part of what was then the central part of Germany .
Paul Marek , ( born 25 July 1964 in Mount Isa ) , Australian politician , was the National Party member of the Australian House of Representatives from 2 March 1996 until 3 October 1998 , representing the Division of Capricornia , Queensland .

Frank Monte ( June 21 , 1931 in South Philadelphia -- May 13 , 1982 in South Philadelphia ) was a member of the Philadelphia crime family .

Anders Holmertz ( born 1 December 1968 in Motala ) is a Swedish retired swimmer who was a leader in freestyle ( 200 and 400 meters ) races in the 1980s and at the beginning of the 1990s , though often missing personal success .
Giuseppe Tellera ( March 14 , 1882 in Bologna -- February 7 , 1941 ) was a general in the Italian Army during World War II .

Victor Löw ( born 25 August 1962 in Amsterdam ; originally Victor Löwenstein ) , is a Dutch actor .

Roy Maloy ( born Roy Timothy McPherson , 27 October 1975 in Melbourne , Victoria ) , is an Australian stilt walker , fire breather , stunt performer , and the holder of several records .

Rickard Olsson , ( born 7 February 1967 in Gävle ) is a Swedish television and radio presenter .

Hilsman was born on November 23 , 1919 , in Waco , Texas the son of Roger Hilsman , Sr . , a career officer with the United States Army , and Emma Prendergast Hilsman .

Miroslav Singer ( born 14 May 1968 , Prague ) is a Czech economist and currently ( from 1 July 2010 ) the Governor of the Czech National Bank .

Pierre Quantin ( born in Fervaques , Calvados , 19 June 1759 - died 7 February 1824 ) was a French general .

Sander Thoenes ( November 7 , 1968 -- September 21 , 1999 ) was a Dutch journalist who was killed , near Dili in East Timor , by soldiers of Indonesian army .
Johann Georg Holtzhey ( 1729 , Amsterdam -- 1808 , Amsterdam ) , was an 18th - century Dutch medallist and mint master .

Francisco Cervantes de Salazar ( 1514 ? -- 1575 ) was a Spanish man of letters and rector of the Royal and Pontifical University of Mexico , founded in 1551 .
Angela Gregory ( October 18 , 1903 -- February 13 , 1990 ) was an American sculptor and professor of art . Born in New Orleans , Louisiana , Gregory has been called the doyenne of Louisiana sculpture .
Eustorgius II ( Italian : Eustorgio ) was Archbishop of Milan from c. 511 to 518 .
Nikolay Breshko - Breshkovsky ( Russian : Никола́й Никола́евич Бре́шко-Брешко́вский , also transcribed as Nikolaĭ Brechko - Brechkovskiĭ etc . ; 20 ( O.S. 8) February 1874 , Saint Petersburg -- 23/24 August 1943 , Berlin ) was a Russian writer , a son of the renowned revolutionary Catherine Breshkovsky .
Mario Ardissone ( born 9 October 1900 in Vercelli ; died in 1975 ) was an Italian football player .
Antonio Dusi was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , mainly active in Brescia .
Simon Fraser , 11th Lord Lovat ( c. 1667 -- 9 April 1747 , London ) , was a Scottish Jacobite and Chief of Clan Fraser of Lovat , who was famous for his violent feuding and his changes of allegiance .

Jakob Erdheim ( 24 May 1874 , Boryslav , Galicia -- 18 April 1937 , Vienna ) was an Austrian pathologist .
Hans Gerle ( c.1500 , Nuremberg - 1570 , Nuremberg ) was a German lutenist and arranger of the Renaissance .

Christoph Amberger ( c. 1505 -- 1562 ) was a painter of Augsburg in the 16th century , a disciple of Hans Holbein , his principal work being the history of Joseph in twelve pictures .
Jules - Jean Ravel ( 6 March 1901 , Guillaumes - 19 June 1986 , Nice ) , was a Communist politician and trade union organizer in Nice , France .

William V. Skall ( October 5 , 1897 , Chicago -- March 22 , 1976 , Los Angeles ) was an American cinematographer who specialized in Technicolor .

Rabbi Yisroel ben Ze'ev Wolf Lipkin , also known as `` Yisroel Salanter '' or `` Israel Salanter '' ( November 3 , 1810 , Zhagory -- February 2 , 1883 , Königsberg ) , was the father of the Musar movement in Orthodox Judaism and a famed Rosh yeshiva and Talmudist .
Elsie Eaves died March 27 , 1983 in Roslyn , New York , aged 84 .
Eugen Ruffínyi ( 1 March 1846 , Dobsina , Hungary -- 13 January 1924 , Dobšiná , Czechoslovakia ) was a mining engineer and amateur speleologist who , together with Gustav Lang und Andreas Méga , was the first to explore the Dobšinská Ice Cave .
Fernand Charron ( 30 May 1866 , in Angers -- 13 August 1928 , in Maisons - Laffitte ) was a French pioneer of motor racing and automobile manufacturing .

Antoine Léon Morel - Fatio ( born 1810 in Rouen − d. 1871 in Paris ) was a French naval painter , peintre officiel de la Marine , curator of the naval and ethnographic museum of the Louvre , and mayor of the 20th arrondissement of Paris .
Johann Heinrich Roos ( 29 September 1631 , Otterberg -- 3 October 1685 , Frankfurt ) was a German Baroque era landscape painter and etcher .

Johann Gerhard Reinhard Andreae ( born ca . 17 December 1724 in Hanover , died 1 May 1793 in Hanover ) , often known as J.G.R. Andreae or I.G.R. Andreae , was a Hanoverian natural scientist , chemist , geologist , court pharmacist ( Hofapotheker ) and alchemist in the Age of Enlightenment .
Almon Brown Strowger ( February 11 , 1839 in Penfield , New York , United States -- May 26 , 1902 in St. Petersburg , Florida , United States ) gave his name to the electromechanical telephone exchange technology that his invention and patent inspired .
John W. Lavelle ( January 26 , 1949 -- January 24 , 2007 ) formerly represented the 61st Assembly District in the New York State Assembly , which comprises much of the North Shore of Staten Island .

Ottó Dóra ( 1 June 1962 -- 29 November 2015 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as mayor of Salgótarján from 12 October 2014 until his death .
Pehr Henrik Ling ( 15 November 1766 in Södra Ljunga -- 3 May 1839 in Stockholm ) pioneered the teaching of physical education in Sweden .
Franz Hofmeister ( 30 August 1850 , Prague -- 26 July 1922 , Würzburg ) was an early protein scientist , and is famous for his studies of salts that influence the solubility and conformational stability of proteins .

Hermann Weigert ( 20 October 1890 , Breslau - 2 April 1955 , New York City ) was a German vocal coach , pianist , and conductor .
Brigadier General Carl Rogers Darnall ( December 25 , 1867 in Weston , Texas , USA -- January 18 , 1941 in Washington , D.C. , USA ) was a United States Army chemist and surgeon credited with originating the technique of liquid chlorination of drinking water .
Pietro Luigi Galletti was an Italian Benedictine , historian and archaeologist ; b. Rome in 1724 ; d. there , 13 December 1790 .
Giuseppe Francica - Nava de Bontifè ( 23 July 1846 - -7 December 1928 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Catholic Church who served as Archbishop of Catania from 1895 until his death , and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1899 .
Nolasc del Molar ( el Molar , 1902 -- Barcelona , 1983 ) was the name of religion of the Catalan capuchin friar Daniel Rebull i Muntanyola .
Pieter Schoubroeck , or Schaubroeck ( ca.1570 -- May 10 , 1607 ) , was a German landscape painter of the Frankenthal school .
Christian Theodor Weinlig ( July 25 , 1780 -- March 7 , 1842 ) was a German music teacher , composer , and choir conductor in Dresden and Leipzig .
Maria of Calabria ( May 1329 -- 20 May 1366 ) was a Neapolitan princess of the Capetian House of Anjou whose descendants inherited the crown of Naples following the death of her older sister , Queen Joanna I.
Bartolomeo Bassi ( early 1600s ( decade)-1640s ) was an Italian painter active in the early - Baroque period , mainly in his hometown of Genoa .

William Gillette was born in Nook Farm , Hartford , Connecticut , a literary and intellectual center with residents such as Mark Twain , Harriet Beecher Stowe , and Charles Dudley Warner .
Hendrik Maarten Krabbé , or Heinrich Martin Krabbé ( 4 May 1868 , London - 22 December 1931 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch genre and portrait painter .
Florian Johann Deller ( bapt . 2 May 1729 in Drosendorf , Lower Austria -- 19 September 1773 in Munich ) was an Austrian composer and violinist .
William Edward Barclay ( 14 June 1857 -- 30 January 1917 ) was the first manager of Everton and also the first manager of Liverpool , working with club secretary John McKenna .
Alexander Felszeghy ( 28 October 1933 in Košice -- 20 December 1994 in Košice ) was a Slovak football defender or midfielder , and later coach .
Alfred Grünfeld ( Prague , July 4 , 1852 -- January 4 , 1924 , Vienna ) was an Austrian pianist and composer .
Vera Brühne ( February 6 , 1910 in Essen -- April 17 , 2001 in Munich ) got famous throughout Germany as a victim of miscarriage of justice .
Vilhelms Purvītis ( 3 March 1872 in Zaube , Latvia -- 14 January 1945 in Bad Nauheim , Germany ) was a landscape painter and educator who founded the Latvian Academy of Art and was its rector from 1919 to 1934 .

Howard , although insufficient business during this Great Depression era forced Kline to close his company after a year and a half .
Vilém Tauský CBE ( 20 July 1910 , Přerov , Moravia -- 16 March 2004 , London ) was a Czech conductor and composer .
Joseph Vendryes ( French : ( vɑ̃dʁi ) ; 13 January 1875 , Paris -- 30 January 1960 ) was a French Celtic linguist .
Sir Robert Yewdall Jennings ( 19 October 1913 -- 4 August 2004 ) was Whewell Professor of International Law at Cambridge University from 1955 to 1982 and a Judge of the International Court of Justice from 1982 .
Herman , or Harmen Hals ( 1611 , Haarlem -- 1669 , Haarlem ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Awdy Kulyýew ( July 30 , 1936 , Ashgabad -- April 10 , 2007 , Oslo ) served as the first Foreign Minister of Turkmenistan .

Mieszko the Younger ( also known as of Kalisz ) ( Polish : Mieszko Młodszy ( kaliski ) ) ( between 1160 and 1165 -- 2 August 1193 ) was a Duke of Kalisz since 1191 until his death .
Josef Florian ( February 9 , 1873 -- December 29 , 1941 , both in Stará Říše in Moravia ) was a Czech book publisher and translator .

Bertha Galland died in an automobile accident in White Plains , New York on November 20 , 1932 .
Enrico Martínez , Henri Martín or Heinrich Martin , ( Born in Hamburg , date unknown ; d. in Mexico in 1632 ) was cosmographer to the King of Spain , interpreter for the Spanish Inquisition , publisher , and hydraulic engineer .

Vicente Casanova y Marzol was born in Borja , and studied at the seminaries in Zaragoza and in Madrid .
Pierre - Nicolas Beauvallet ( born in Le Havre on 21 June 1750 and died in Paris on 15 April 1818 ) , is a French sculptor , draftsman and printmaker .
Jimmy Yates ( 1871 -- 5 September 1922 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a right winger in the 1900 FA Cup Final for Southampton .
Walter Ehrlich ( May 16 , 1896 in Berlin -- December 26 , 1968 in Bad Ragaz , Canton of St. Gallen , Switzerland ) was a German philosopher .

Semisalsa galilaea is a species of small brackish water snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Cochliopidae .
Superciliaspis is an extinct genus of jawless fish which existed in what is now the Northwest Territories of Canada during the Lochkovian age .
Streptomyces cinnamoneus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Japan .
Gnaphalium is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , commonly called cudweeds .
Tropidophis wrighti , or the gracile banded dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family endemic to Cuba .
Streptomyces glycovorans is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from marine sediments of the South China Sea near the Xisha Islands in China .
Calliphora latifrons is a species of blue bottle fly .
Rory Cooper 's false antechinus ( Pseudantechinus roryi ) , also known as the tan false antechinus and the tan pseudantechinus , is a recently named species of small carnivorous marsupial which inhabits rocky outcrops in Western Australia .
Allium dumetorum is a Middle Eastern species of onion found in Israel , Palestine , Lebanon and Jordan .
Rubus multifer is a North American species of brambles in the rose family .
Hyloniscus riparius is a species of woodlouse found in Central and Eastern Europe and subsequently introduced to North America .
Cleisostoma recurvum is a species of orchid found in Cambodia , Laos , Thailand , Vietnam and China .
Traunsteinera , the Round Headed Orchid , or globe orchid , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Hoplomyzon papillatus is a species of banjo catfish found in Ecuador and Venezuela where it occurs in the Napo and Portuguesa River basins respectively .
Pomacea falconensis is a South American species of freshwater snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae .
Fucus distichus or rockweed is a species of brown alga in the family Fucaceae to be found in the intertidal zones of rocky seashores in the Northern Hemisphere , mostly in rock pools .
Neocrepidodera albanica is a species of flea beetle in the leaf beetle family that can be found only in Albania and the Republic of Macedonia .
Stephanomeria lactucina is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names lettuce wirelettuce and woodland wirelettuce .
Rapana is a genus of large predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
Megacephala asperata is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by C. O. Waterhouse in 1877 .
Sivaladapinae is a subfamily of adapiform primate that lived in Asia during the middle to late Miocene .
Brassolis sophorae is a species of large butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Iliamna corei is a rare species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Peters Mountain mallow .
Spigelia genuflexa is a species of annual herb of the family Loganiaceae from Bahia state , Brazil , which was described in 2011 .
Dicerca moesta is a species of beetle from Argante subgenus which can be found everywhere in Europe ( except for various European islands ) .
Withania riebeckii is a species of plant in the Solanaceae family .
Philodromus blanckei is a spider species found in Corsica , Sardinia and Italy .
The Myanmar snub - nosed monkey or Burmese snub - nosed monkey ( Rhinopithecus strykeri ) is a critically threatened species of colobine monkey discovered in 2010 in northern Burma ( Myanmar ) .
Agamidae is a family of over 300 species of iguanian lizards indigenous to Africa , Asia , Australia , and a few in Southern Europe .
Anopheles balabacensis is a species of mosquito in the Culicidae family .
The Parechinidae are a family of sea urchins in the class Echinoidea .
Quercus similis , or swamp post oak , also known as bottomland post oak , is an oak species native to the southeastern and south - central United States .
Ostrinotes tarena is a species of butterfly , described by William Chapman Hewitson in 1874 , belonging to the family Lycaenidae .
Anagrus epos is a species of fairyfly which has been proposed as a biological control agent against Homalodisca vitripennis .
Vallonia costata is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Valloniidae .
Angolasaurus is an extinct genus of mosasaur found in the Upper Cretaceous ( Turonian ) of Angola and described by Miguel Telles Antunes in 1964 .
Haworthia bolusii is a species of Haworthia that was originally described by John Gilbert Baker in 1880 .
Paralacinius podoliensis is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Phalangiidae .
Colochirus quadrangularis , commonly known as the thorny sea cucumber , is a species of sea cucumber in the family Cucumariidae .
Catafimbria boliviana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Catafimbria .
Plagiochila is a large , common , and widespread genus of liverworts in order Jungermanniales .
Cochranella punctulata is a species of frog in the family Centrolenidae , endemic to Colombia .
Perideridia is a small genus of plants in the parsley family .
Pritchardia affinis , the Hawai'i pritchardia , is a species of palm tree that is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Cladonia perforata is a rare species of lichen known by the common names Florida perforate cladonia and Florida perforate reindeer lichen .
Spathodus erythrodon is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika though absent from the southern end of the lake .
The Caulleryellidae are a family of parasitic protozoa in the phylum Apicomplexa .
Leishmania major is a species of protozoa found in the genus Leishmania , and is associated with the disease zoonotic cutaneous leishmaniasis ( also known as Aleppo boil , Baghdad boil , Bay sore , Biskra button , Chiclero ulcer , Delhi boil , Kandahar sore , Lahore sore , Oriental sore , Pian bois , and Uta ) .
Ameles africana is a species of praying mantis that inhabits Algeria , Morocco , Corsica , Dalmatia , Sardinia , Sicily , and Portugal .
Bartsia alpina is a species of perennial flowering plant .
Megatrema anglicum is a species of acorn barnacle that grows in association with or semi - parasitically on corals and octocorals .
Neptosternus arnecornelii is a species of beetle , named after Arne Cornelius .
Mearns 's squirrel ( Tamiasciurus mearnsi ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Badis ruber is a species of freshwater fish found in Mekong , Salween and Irrawaddy basins in Laos and Thailand .
Houstonia wrightii , pygmy bluet , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
The Asiatic lion ( Panthera leo persica ) , also known as the Indian lion or Persian lion , is a lion subspecies that exists as a single population in India 's Gujarat state .
Puntius amphibius , also called the scarlet - banded barb , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Puntius .
Bull pipefish ( Syngnathus springeri ) is a pipefish species , inhabits the Western Atlantic from Canada to North Carolina ( USA ) , Bahamas and northeastern Gulf of Mexico to Panama .
Drosera ordensis is a species of sundew , native to Australia and part of the `` petiolaris complex '' of sundews making up the subgenus Lasiocephala .
Ancyloceratoidea , formerly Ancylocerataceae , is a superfamily of typically uncoiled and loosely coiled heteroomorph ammonoids established by Hyall , 1900 , that may contain as many as 11 families , depending on the classification accepted .
Rumex venosus is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common names veiny dock , winged dock , and wild - begonia ( it is not related to genus Begonia ) .
Duvalius abyssimus is a species of beetle described in 2014 by biologists Ana Sofia Reboleira and Vicente Ortuño .
Cerobasis guestfalica is a species of Psocoptera belonging to the family Trogiidae .
Aphaenogaster avita is an extinct species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae known from a solitary early to middle Miocene fossil found in Japan .
Panulirus argus , the Caribbean spiny lobster , is a species of spiny lobster that lives on reefs and in mangrove swamps in the western Atlantic Ocean .
Asteiidae is a small but widespread family of acalyptrate flies or Diptera .
Phacelia mutabilis is a species of phacelia known by the common name changeable phacelia .
The Hartmannellidae are a family of amoebozoa , usually found in soils .
Rhododendron micranthum ( 照山白 ) is a rhododendron species native to China and Korea , where it grows at altitudes of 1000 - -3000 meters .
Cavendishia is a genus of about 100 species of woody perennial plants , many of which are epiphytic .
Anguimorphs of the infraorder Anguimorpha include the anguids ( alligator lizards , glass lizards , galliwasps and legless lizards ) .
Gomphoscopa catoryctopsis is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Gomphoscopa .
Amphiprion pacificus , is a species of anemonefish that is found in the western Pacific Ocean .
The Roman Dactylorhiza ( Dactylorhiza romana ) is a species of orchid .
Chelydropsis murchisoni is an extinct species of snapping turtle of the extinct genus Chelydropsis that lived from the Oligocene to the Pliocene in Asia and Europe .
Nanuqsaurus ( meaning `` polar bear lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of carnivorous tyrannosaurid theropod known from the Late Cretaceous ( early Late Maastrichtian stage ) Prince Creek Formation of the North Slope of Alaska , USA .
Clarkia lewisii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Lewis ' clarkia .
Kalimeris pinnatifida , also known as the Double Japanese Aster is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
The family Flavobacteriaceae is composed of environmental bacteria .
Croomia japonica is a plant species native to China and Japan .
Paspalum plicatulum is a species of grass known by the common name brownseed paspalum .
Proterotheriidae is an extinct family of fossil ungulates from the Cenozoic era that displays toe reduction .
Stenopsocus immaculatus is a species of Psocoptera from Stenopsocidae family that can be found in Great Britain and Ireland .
Hygrophoropsis aurantiaca , commonly known as the false chanterelle , is a species of fungus in the family Hygrophoropsidaceae .
Trachipterus arcticus is a species of ribbonfish found predominantly in the North Atlantic Ocean , with one report from the Mediterranean Sea .
Rhynchophreatia is a genus of 10 species of orchids found in Australia , New Guinea , the Solomon Islands , Indonesia , Micronesia , and New Caledonia .
Aereniphaula machadorum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aereniphaula .
Anomochilus monticola , the mountain pipe snake , or Kinabalu giant blind snake , is a species of snake in the Anomochilidae family .
Lophozonia glauca ( Hualo ) is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae family .
Coprosma elegans is a flowering plant species in the genus Coprosma found in New Guinea .
Eragrostis dielsii , commonly known as mallee lovegrass , is a species of grass endemic to Australia .
Bafutia tenuicaulis is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family , and the only species in the genus Bafutia .
Rhyothemis fenestrina , known as the Black - winged flutterer , Golden flutterer , or Skylight flutterer , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Pirskenius is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the early part of the Miocene epoch .
Nyctibatrachus beddomii ( common names : Beddome 's night frog , pigmy wrinkled frog , Beddome 's dwarf wrinkled frog , and Tirunvelveli 's hill frog ) is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family .
Capriocornites is a rutoceratid genus ( Nautiloidea - Cephalopoda ) from the Devonian , related to such genera as Rutoceras and Goldringia .
Praegmelina is an extinct genus of crustacean in the order Amphipoda .
Oreostylidium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Stylidiaceae with a single species , Oreostylidium subulatum , that is endemic to New Zealand .
Austrochaperina mehelyi is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family , endemic to Papua New Guinea , known only from two localities , Adelbert Range and mountains of Huon Peninsula .
Grunion are two fish species of the genus Leuresthes : the California grunion , L. tenuis , and the Gulf grunion L. sardinas .
Rhynchodina is a monotypic genus of noctuoid moths in the Erebidae family .
Microraptor ( Greek , μίκρος , mīkros : `` small '' ; Latin , raptor : `` one who seizes '' ) was a genus of small , four - winged paravian ( possibly dromaeosaurid ) dinosaurs .
Physa marmorata is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae .
Crataegus iracunda , with common name passionate hawthorn , and sometimes called the stolon - bearing hawthorn is a North American species of hawthorn .
Nanocheirodon insignis is a species of characin endemic to Colombia where it is found in Lake Maracaibo and the Magdalena River basin .
Asarum lemmonii is a species of wild ginger which is endemic to California .
Croton lawianus is a species of the genus Croton and the family Euphorbiaceae located in the Baba Budan range in Karnataka , India .
Gagata sexualis is a species of sisorid catfish endemic to India .
Luciobarbus escherichii is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to freshwater habitats in Turkey .
Dictyotenguna angusta is a species of planthopper native to Guangxi , China .
Lotus rubriflorus is a rare species of legume known by the common name red - flowered bird's - foot trefoil .
Pelocetidae is an extinct family of baleen whales .
× Ascocenda , abbreviated as Ascda in the horticultural trade , is a man - made hybrid orchid genus resulting from a cross between Ascocentrum and Vanda ( Asctm × V ) .
Mycena acicula , commonly known as the orange bonnet , or the coral spring Mycena , is a species of fungus in the Mycenaceae family .
It is the only member of the monotypic genus Steinbachiella .
Indigofera is a large genus of over 750 species of flowering plants belonging to the family Fabaceae .
Athyrtis is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Felder in 1862 .
Polistes annularis ( P. annularis ) is a species of paper wasp which lives in North America .
Penicillium madriti is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces orsellinic acid .
Enneapterygius obscurus is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Abies delavayi , the Delavay 's silver - fir or Delavay 's fir , is a species of fir , native to Yunnan in southwest China and adjoining border areas in southeastern Tibet , far northeastern India , northern Myanmar , and far northwestern Vietnam .
Carabus marietti inexpectatus is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to Turkey .
The Capulidae , the cap snails or cap shells , are a taxonomic family of limpet - like sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Cypraeovula capensis , common name the Cape cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Penicillium claviforme is a species of Penicillium within the phylum Ascomycota .
Orhantarctia is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from Lesser Sundaland :
Rhabdoblennius nigropunctatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific Ocean , around Fiji and Tonga .
Chimonanthus praecox , also known as wintersweet or Japanese allspice , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Chimonanthus of the family Calycanthaceae , native to China .
Crepidodera is a genus of beetle from a leaf beetle family .
Cystoseira elegans is a brown alga species in the genus Cystoseira endemic to the Mediterranean .
Plectaster decanus , the mosaic sea star , is a species of sea star found off the south coast of Australia .
Ranunculus flammula , the lesser spearwort , greater creeping spearwort or banewort , is a species of perennial herbaceous plants in the genus Ranunculus ( buttercup ) , growing in damp places throughout the Boreal Kingdom .
Laternea triscapa is a species of fungus in the Phallaceae family .
Yakuhananomia bidentata is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the genus Yakuhananomia .
Delphinium nuttallianum is a species of larkspur known by the common names twolobe larkspur and Nuttall 's larkspur .
Scartichthys crapulatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the southeast Pacific ocean , and is endemic to Chile .
Plesiadapidae is a family of plesiadapiform mammals related to primates known from the Paleocene and Eocene of North America , Europe , and Asia .
Lachesilla tanaidana is a species of Psocoptera from Lachesillidae family that can be found in Germany , Hungary , Portugal , Sardinia , Switzerland , and Ukraine .
Pelecyphora is a genus of cacti , comprising 2 species .
Faurea macnaughtonii ( Terblanz beech ) is a species of tree in the Proteaceae family .
Penstemon scapoides is an uncommon species of penstemon known by the common name pinyon beardtongue .
Impatiens platypetala is variable species of perennial Impatiens discovered on the island of Java and widespread throughout Indonesia .
Southern pipefish , Syngnathus folletti , is a pipefish species , inhabits the Southwest Atlantic near Uruguay .
Anisopodus xylinus is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Bates in 1881 .
Citharichthys amblybregmatus is a species of flatfish in the large - tooth flounder family Paralichthyidae .
Burykhia hunti is a Precambrian fossil genus from the White Sea region of Russia dating to 555 million years ago .
Brunellia acostae is a species of plant in the Brunelliaceae family .
Protobrama is an extinct genus of teleost fish from the Cretaceous period of Lebanon .
Coelotrochus oppressus , common name the shouldered top shell , is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top snails or top shells .
Harpegnathos saltator , sometimes called the Indian jumping ant or Jerdon 's jumping ant , is a species of ant found in India .
It contains only one species , Tortrimosaica polypodivora , which is found in Brazil .
Brasilicereus markgrafii is a species of cactus which is endemic to Brazil .
Gammarus roeseli is a species of freshwater amphipod found across Europe from the Benelux countries to European Turkey .
Dactylopteryx is a genus of praying mantis in the family Liturgusidae .
Leiognathus is a genus of ponyfishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Thorncroftia is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described as a genus in 1912 .
Necrophila is a genus of carrion beetles , with around 20 species : most found in Asia and India , and one species in North America , Necrophila americana .
Asima is an extinct genus of prehistoric fish and not much is known about it.bony fish .
Nebria chitralensis is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Pakistan .
Eucommiales is a botanical name for an order of flowering plants .
Philophthalmus gralli , commonly known as oriental avian eye fluke , is found in conjunctiva sac of eyes of many species of birds .
Mycobacterium fluoranthenivorans is a species of the phylum actinobacteria ( gram - positive bacteria with high guanine and cytosine content , one of the dominant phyla of all bacteria ) , belonging to the genus mycobacterium .
Columna leai is a species of tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinidae .
Laminacauda maxima is a species of sheet weaver found in Tristan da Cunha .
Dubautia herbstobatae ( Na'ena'e or Keaau Valley dubautia ) is an endangered species of shrub which is endemic to Oahu , Hawaii .
Pegusa is a genus of soles native to the Eastern Atlantic Ocean , Mediterranean Sea , and Black Sea .
Philanthus nasalis is a species of bee - hunting wasp ( or `` beewolf '' ) originally described from Contra Costa County , California .
In taxonomy , the Golenkiniaceae are a family of algae , specifically of the Chloroccocales .
Pristilepis oligolepis , the spinyface soldier , is a species of soldierfish found in association with reefs in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Only one species are recorded for genus , Rupelramphastoides knopfi , and it is classified `` family incertae sedis '' , pending discovery of additional specimens .
Eragrostis desertorum is a species of grass known from Queensland , Western Australia , and the Northern Territory .
Bothriospondylus ( `` excavated vertebra '' ) is an dubious genus of sauropod dinosaur .
Salix integra ( Chinese : 杞柳 qi liu ; Japanese : イヌコリヤナギ inukoriyanagi ; syn . S. multinervis Franch . & Savatier ) is a species of willow native to northeastern China , Japan , Korea and Primorsky Krai in the far southeast of Russia .
Agave phillipsiana is a rare species of flowering plant in the asparagus family known by the common names Grand Canyon century plant and Phillips agave .
Heliamphora pulchella ( Latin : pulchellus = pretty ) is a species of marsh pitcher plant endemic to the Chimanta Massif and surrounding tepuis in Venezuela .
Sagra femorata is a species of beetle belonging to the family Chrysomelidae .
Populus ilicifolia ( Tana River poplar ) is a species of poplar in the family Salicaceae .
Brachyptera is a genus of taeniopterygid stoneflies of mostly western Paleartic distribution .
Pseudorinelepis genibarbis is a species of armored catfish native to Brazil and Peru where it is found in the Upper Amazon basin .
Cirsium occidentale , with the common name cobweb thistle or cobwebby thistle , is a North American species of thistle in the sunflower family .
Rubus parviflorus , commonly called thimbleberry , salmonberry , and snow bramble , is a species of Rubus , native to North America .
Datura lanosa is a species of Datura .
Calotomus is a parrotfish genus from the Indo - Pacific , with a single species ranging into the warmer parts of the east Pacific .
Enneapterygius philippinus , known commonly as the Minute triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Ponerosteus is a dubious genus of archosaur which was first identified as `` Iguanodon exogirarum '' by Antonin Fritsch in 1878 for a specimen from the Cenomanian ( Late Cretaceous of the Czech Republic ) .
Discodeles malukuna ( common name : Malukuna webbed frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Caupedactylus is an extinct genus of tapejarid azhdarchoid pterosaur known from the Early Cretaceous Romualdo Formation of Araripe Basin , northeastern Brazil .
Megosmidus tuberculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Megosmidus .
Jovellania is an extinct prehistoric nautiloid genus from the order Oncocerida known from the Lower Devonian of Europe ( France , Germany ) .
Salsola imbricata is a small species of shrub in the family Amaranthaceae .
Clitoria fragrans is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name pigeon wings , or sweet - scented pigeon wings .

Geitoneura is a genus of nymphalid butterflies , commonly known as xenicas .
