Eczemotellus subtilipectus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Eczemotellus .
Lathyrus hirsutus is a species of wild pea known by several common names , including Caley pea , hairy vetchling , and Austrian winterpea .
Oophila amblystomatis , commonly known as chlamydomonad algae or salamander algae , is a species of single - celled green algae .
Silene lemmonii is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Lemmon 's catchfly .
The Mudur caecilian , Gegeneophis madhavai , is a species of caecilian found in India .
Desmanthus bicornutus is a species of flowering plant in the legume family native to northern and central Mexico and the southwestern United States .
Alcithoe grahami is a species of medium - sized deepwater sea snail , a gastropod mollusc in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Thyridopteryx is a genus of bagworm moth .
Cellana strigilis strigilis is a species of large limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Cyclostremellini is a minor tribe , a taxonomic grouping , of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks , in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Citioica anthonilis is a species of moth from a Saturniidae family , which can be found from Central America to Brazil .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Barria piceae .
Cetostoma regani , the Pink flabby whalefish , is a species of flabby whalefish found in the ocean depths down to 2,250 metres ( 7,380 ft ) .
Chorizanthe cuspidata is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name San Francisco spineflower .
Psathyrostachys is a genus of Eurasian plants in the grass family .
Baeriopsis is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Baeriopsis guadalupensis .
Methylibium petroleiphilum is a species of methyl tert - butyl ether - degrading methylotroph , the type species of its genus .
Fahrenholzia pinnata is a species of louse .
Cypraeidae , common name the cowries ( singular : cowry ) , is a taxonomic family of small to large sea snails .
Bromus commutatus , known as Meadow Brome , is an annual or biennial species of plant in the grass family Poaceae .
It contains the single species Geriojennsa cunegunda , which is found in Argentina .
Phrynops hilarii , commonly known as Hilaire 's toadhead turtle or Hilaire 's side - necked turtle , is a species of turtle endemic to South America .
Volvarina angustata , common name : the narrow marginella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Spinacia is a flowering plant genus in subfamily Chenopodioideae of family Amaranthaceae .
Acrossocheilus aluoiensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Acrossocheilus found mostly in Vietnam .
Pyramidelloidea is a superfamily of mostly very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks and micromollusks within the clade Panpulmonata .
Nostolepis is an extinct genus of acanthodian fish which lived in the Late Silurian ( Pridoli ) to Middle Devonian ( Lochkovian ) .
Artemisia campestris is a common and widespread species of plants in the sunflower family .
Phelsuma quadriocellata is a species of gecko known by the common name peacock day gecko .
The Ecuador slender - legged tree frog , Osteocephalus verruciger , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia and Ecuador .
Festuca eskia is a species of grass which is endemic to southwestern Europe .
Anthocercis viscosa , also known as Sticky Tailflower , is a species of shrub in the Solanaceae family , native to the south coast of Western Australia .

Conus ochroleucus , common name the prefect cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .

Antipodromia is a monotypic genus of fly from New Zealand that was first described by Plant in 2011 .
Antennaria umbrinella is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names umber pussytoes and brown pussytoes .
Heterodontosauridae is a family of early ornithischian dinosaurs that were likely among the most basal ( primitive ) members of the group .
Gaioxenus pilipalpis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Gaioxenus .
Otiorhynchus cribricollis is one of the many species in the weevil family ( Curculionidae ) .
Lupinus elmeri is an uncommon species of lupine known by the common names Elmer 's lupine and South Fork Mountain lupine .

Ostreococcus tauri is a unicellular species of marine green alga about 0.8 micrometres ( μm ) in diameter , the smallest free - living ( non - symbiotic ) eukaryote yet described .
The sea anemone Edwardsia claparedii is a species of marine invertebrate in the Family Edwardsiidae .
Sabacon cavicolens is a species of harvestman .

Paracrossotus multifasciculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paracrossotus .
Simian immunodeficiency viruses ( SIVs ) are retroviruses able to infect at least 45 species of African non - human primates .
Musculus niger , or the little black mussel , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae .

Galium magellense , Maiella bedstraw , is a plant species of the Rubiaceae .

Xenodon rabdocephalus , commonly known as the false fer - de - lance , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake endemic to Central America and northern South America .
Vanda is a genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) which , although not massive ( about eighty species ) , is one of the genera more commonly found in the market place .

Phoroctenia is a genus of true crane flies found in northern Europe , eastern Russia , and western North America .
Calamagrostis ( small reed or reed grass ) is a genus in the grass family Poaceae , with about 260 species that occur mainly in temperate regions of the globe .
Kryptopterus bicirrhis , often called the glass catfish , is an Asian glass catfish species of the genus Kryptopterus .
Allium ovalifolium is a Chinese species of onion widely cultivated as an ornamental in other regions .
Solidago altiplanities , the high plains goldenrod , is a plant species native to the high - altitude plains of Oklahoma and the Texas Panhandle , often found on ridges and escarpments .

Afrozomus machadoi is a species of arachnid , belonging to the family Hubbardiidae in the order Schizomida ( `` shorttailed whipscorpions '' ) .

Bantiella pallida is a species of praying mantis in the genus Bantiella in the order Mantodea .
Marah horridus , common name Sierra manroot , is a species of flowering plant in the family Cucurbitaceae , endemic to the foothills of the Sierra Nevada and the Tehachapi Mountains in California .
The species was known as Gillmeria tetradactyla until recently , but is now known as Gillmeria ochrodactyla .
Actinomyces israelii is a species of Gram - positive , rod - shaped bacteria within the Actinomyces .
Caristanius tripartitus is a species of snout moth in the genus Caristanius .
Diplograptus was a Cambrian genus of graptolite , .
At present , the only species recognized is Sanblasia dressleri L.Andersson , endemic to Panamá .
The Amatola toad ( Vandijkophrynus amatolicus ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Ranunculus muricatus is a species of buttercup known by the common names rough - fruited buttercup and spinyfruit buttercup .
Exidiopsis effusa is a species of fungus in the family Auriculariaceae , and the type species of the genus Exidiopsis .
Musumecia is a clitocyboid agaric fungal genus with a soft , pseudosclerotium - like base .
Bacidina contecta is a species of fungi within the Ramalinaceae family , first found in inland rainforests of British Columbia .
Actaea racemosa ( black cohosh , black bugbane , black snakeroot , fairy candle ; syn . Cimicifuga racemosa ) is a species of flowering plant of the family Ranunculaceae .
Calliostoma sayanum , common name Say 's top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Endomychus coccineus , common name Scarlet Endomychus or False Ladybird , is a species of beetles in the family Endomychidae .
Neonesomia is a genus of North American flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Antennophorus is a genus of mites in the family Antennophoridae .
Oenothera longissima is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name longstem evening primrose .
Epitonium scalare , common name the precious wentletrap , is a predatory or ectoparasitic species of marine gastropod with an operculum , in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Indarbela is a genus of moths in the Metarbelidae family .
Hinasuri is an extinct genus of rhea from the Pliocene .
Miomoptera is an extinct order of insects .
Chromolaena oteroi ( Mona Island thoroughwort ) , is a West Indian species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family .
The flowering plant genus Trochetiopsis consists of two extant and one extinct species endemic to the island of Saint Helena ( South Atlantic Ocean ) .
It consists of only one species , Anticoreura salmoni , which is found in Colombia .
Ochrobactrum tritici is a species of bacteria first isolated from wheat rhizoplane .
Cordulegaster princeps is a species of dragonfly in the family Cordulegastridae .
Eriogonum apiculatum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name San Jacinto buckwheat .
Ploiariolini is a tribe of thread - legged bugs , comprising 16 genera and 142 described species .
Polyonax ( meaning `` master over many '' ) was a genus of ceratopsid dinosaur from the late Maastrichtian - age Upper Cretaceous Denver Formation of Colorado , USA .
Acer heldreichii , common names Heldreich 's maple , Greek maple , and Balkan maple is a European species of maple .
Novosphingobium is a genus of Gram - negative bacteria that includes N. taihuense , which can degrade aromatic compounds such as phenol , aniline , nitrobenzene and phenanthrene .
Vanda denisoniana is a species of orchid found from China ( Yunnan ) to northern Indochina .
Lactarius fumosus , commonly known as the smoky milkcap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Mepraia is a genus in the subfamily Triatominae , endemic of Chile , and vector of Chagas disease .
Downingia pusilla is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name dwarf calicoflower .
Palaeocuma hessi is an extinct species of cumacean , the only species in the genus Palaeocuma , and one of very few fossil cumaceans ever discovered .
Paratriaenops furculus , also known as Trouessart 's trident bat , is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Hudsonia ericoides is a species of flowering plant in the rock - rose family known by the common names pine barren goldenheather , false heather , and golden - heather .
Achaeopsis spinulosa , the hotlips spider crab , is a species of crab in the family Inachidae , found only around the South African coast .
Pseudosphromenus cupanus , also known as the spiketail parasidefish is a species of medium - small gouramies native to southern India and Sri Lanka .
The Buffoon lemniscomys or Buffoon striped grass mouse ( Lemniscomys macculus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Proscelotes arnoldi , commonly known as Arnold 's skink or Arnold 's montane skink , is a species of lizard endemic to Africa .
Desulfuromusa ferrireducens is a species of psychrophilic , Fe(III)-reducing bacteria .
Sticharium clarkae , the Dusky crawler , is a species of clinid native to the coast of southern Australia where it prefers living around coastal outcrops in which it can find partially sheltered sandy bays .
Raorchestes manohari is a species of frog of the genus Raorchestes found in Bonacaud in the Western Ghats of Kerala in India .
Neomyia cornicina is a common species of fly which is distributed across many parts the Palaearctic .
Only a single species , Philotrox condoni , is recognized .
Anomaloglossus rufulus ( common names : Sira poison frog , Chimantá poison frog , tepui poison frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Tribosphenida is a group ( infralegion ) of mammals that includes the ancestor of Hypomylos , Necrolestidae , Aegialodontia and Theria ( the last common ancestor of marsupials and placentals plus all of its descendants ) .
Struszia mccartneyi is a species of trilobite named after British musician Paul McCartney .
Bellacartwrightia is a relatively uncommon genus of Phacopid trilobite , found in the mid - Devonian Hamilton Group of New York state , mainly in strata exposed near Lake Erie just west of Buffalo .
Luzula nivalis , commonly known as arctic wood - rush or less commonly as snowy wood - rush ( both names are used with or without hyphenation ) , is a species of perennial rushes endemic to Canada , Greenland , Alaska , and Northern Europe in Scandinavia .
Ochradenus socotranus is a species of plant in the Resedaceae family .
David 's echymipera ( Echymipera davidi ) , or David 's spiny bandicoot , is a species of marsupial in the family Peramelidae .
Sepiidae is a family of cephalopods in the order Sepiida .
Nanorana minica ( common names : Nepal paa frog , tiny frog , small paa frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Cryptanthus beuckeri is a species in the genus Cryptanthus .
Atelais illaesa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Atelais .
Tephrosia apollinea is a legume species , native to southwest Asia ( the Levant , Arabia , Socotra , Iran , Pakistan , northwestern India ) and northeast Africa ( Egypt , Sudan , Ethiopia , Eritrea , Djibouti , Somalia ) .
Selatosomus aeneus is a species of click beetle found in Europe .
The São Tomé fiscal or Newton 's fiscal ( Lanius newtoni ) is a species of bird in the Laniidae family .
Inocybe tahquamenonensis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Inocybaceae .
The Argentine cougar , commonly known as puma ( Puma concolor cabrerae ) is a subspecies of cougar native to western and central Argentina .
Lactarius affinis , commonly known as the kindred milk cap , is a species of milk - cap mushroom in the family Russulaceae .
It contains the single species Sewardiella tuberifera , which is endemic to India .
Sidalcea reptans is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Sierra checkerbloom .
Tropheops microstoma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers sheltered bays with calm waters .
Gastromyzon is a genus of gastromyzontid loaches native to Borneo .
Montipora digitata , also known as finger coral , is a species of stony coral .
Rhizochromulina is an unusual genus of marine heterokont algae , with one species , R. marina .
Saccodon is a genus of scrapetooths found in the Tumbes - Chocó - Magdalena region from Panama to northwestern Peru .
Orchis punctulata , the small - dotted Orchis , is a species of orchid .
Karsten totoyensis is a species of goby native to the western Pacific Ocean where it has been recorded from the Philippines , Fiji and Indonesia .
Proxiphocentron is a genus of caddisflies .
Falsoropicoides laosensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsoropicoides .
Abelmoschus ficulneus is a species of flowering plant in the genus Abelmoschus , family Malvaceae .
Hoplitosaurus ( meaning `` Hoplite lizard '' ) was a genus of armored dinosaur related to Polacanthus .
Carabus perrini is a species of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in South Russia , Ukraine , and Georgia .
The Martinique oriole ( Icterus bonana ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Kaloula indochinensis is a recently described species of frog in the Microhylidae family that is found in Indochina , in southern Vietnam , eastern Cambodia , and southern to central Laos .
Theodoxus meridionalis is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum .
Crataegus biltmoreana is a species of hawthorn native to the Southeastern U.S. It is one of many hawthorn species named by Chauncey Delos Beadle when he worked at the Biltmore Estate .
Aclistomycter is an extinct genus of oreodont during the early Chadronian subepoch ( 42 - -39.9 mya ) existing for approximately 2.1 million years .
Stromboscerus is a genus of the weevil subfamily Dryophthorinae .
Salix laevigata ( red willow or polished willow ) , is a species of willow native to the southwestern United States and northern Baja California .
Ophiactis is a genus of brittle stars ( Ophiuroidea ) .
Pleuromeris tridentata , or the three - toothed cardita , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Carditidae .
Stygoparnus is a monotypic genus of beetles containing the single species Stygoparnus comalensis , which is known by the common name Comal Springs dryopid beetle .
Amphisbaena xera , known commonly as the Puerto Rican dryland worm lizard or the North American worm lizard , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Charpentiera obovata , known as Pāpala , is a species of flowering shrub or small tree in the pigweed family , Amaranthaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Isisaurus ( named after the Indian Statistical Institute ) is a genus of dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period .
Plexauridae is a family of marine colonial octocorals in the phylum Cnidaria .
Bithyniidae is a family of small freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Cranopsis major , common name the large puncturella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Pseudoxyops is a genus consisting of 5 species of mantises in the subfamily Stagmatopterinae .
Sicyopus is a genus of small gobies .
The family Saturniidae , commonly known as saturniids , by most measures include the largest species of moths .
Confuciusornis is a genus of primitive crow - sized birds from the Early Cretaceous Yixian and Jiufotang Formations of China , dating from 125 to 120 million years ago .
Bathypolypus is a genus of octopuses in the family Octopodidae .
Hexamita is a genus of parasitic diplomonads .
Allium nathaliae is a species of wild onion endemic to the Crimean Peninsula .
Drepanoidea is the superfamily of `` hook tip moths '' .
Only a single species , Palaeochenoides mioceanus , is known to date .
Leptothorax duloticus is a species of especially hostile slave - maker ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Megachile melanophaea is a species of leaf - cutter bee in the family Megachilidae .
Kyllinga nemoralis , white water sedge or whitehead spikesedge , is a plant species in the Cyperaceae family .
Large - tooth flounders or sand flounders are a family , Paralichthyidae , of flounders .
Bhutanthera is a genus of terrestrial orchids native to the Himalaya Mountains of Asia .
Zodarion timidum is a spider species found in Spain and France .
Paradiscopus maculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paradiscopus .
Leptospermum myrsinoides , commonly known as silky tea - tree or heath tea - tree , is a shrub species that is endemic to south - eastern Australia .
Geum rossii is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names Ross ' avens and alpine avens .
Chrysiptera taupou , known commonly as the southseas devil , southseas demoiselle , and Fiji damsel , is a species of damselfish .
Prepusa miranda is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Prepusa .
Kinyongia matschiei , common name giant monkey - tailed east Usambara two - horned chameleon , giant east Usambara blade - horned chameleon , and Matschie 's two - horned chamaeleon , is a species of chameleon .
Cataulacus taprobanae is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Cowiedesmus is an extinct millipede genus known from the middle Silurian of Scotland , and is one of the earliest known land animals .
Orthosuchus is an extinct genus of protosuchian crocodyliform that lived during the Early Jurassic .
Cecilioides is a genus of very small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Ferussaciidae .
Dicynodontoidea is a superfamily of dicynodont therapsids that includes Lystrosauridae and Kannemeyeriiformes .
Arizona elegans arenicola , commonly known as the Texas glossy snake , is a subspecies of glossy snake , a nonvenomous colubrid snake endemic to North America .
Acidiplasma is a genus in the phylum Euryarchaeota ( Archaea ) .
Celmisia pugioniformis , commonly known as Slender Snow - daisy , is a species of perennial herb in the family Asteraceae .
Conus lynceus , common name the lynceus cone , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Phleogena faginea , widespread in north temperate areas .
Phyllostegia renovans is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name red - leaf phyllostegia .
Branchiostegus is a genus of tilefishes found in the eastern Atlantic Ocean through the Indian Ocean to the western Pacific Ocean .
Rhagoletis is a genus of tephritid fruit flies with about hundred species .
Sicyonia is a genus of prawns , placed in its own family , Sicyoniidae .
Eutropis bibronii is a species of skink endemic to India and Sri Lanka .
Solenostemon , commonly known as Coleus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae .
Ctenophorus maculosus , commonly known as the Lake Eyre dragon lizard or salt - lake ground - dragon , is a species of agamid lizard endemic to South Australia .
Pterarene sakashitai is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Liotiidae .
Magnetospirillum is a Gram - negative , microaerophilic genus of magnetotactic bacterium , first isolated from pond water by the microbiologist R. P. Blakemore in 1975 .
Howella is a genus of fish in the family Howellidae , the oceanic basslets .

Koopman 's rat ( Rattus koopmani ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Phenacobius mirabilis , or the suckermouth minnow , is a North American cyprinid fish , one of the 324 freshwater fish species found in Tennessee .
Chrysomela is a genus of leaf beetles found almost throughout the world , but missing from Australia .
Rhododendron concinnum ( 秀雅杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Guizhou , Henan , Hubei , Shaanxi , Sichuan , and Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2300 - -3000 meters .
Parapsettus panamensis , the Panama spadefish , is a species of spadefish native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from the Gulf of California to Peru .
Diplognatha gagates is a species of beetle belonging to the family Scarabaeidae , Cetoniinae subfamily .
Syncope jimi is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family . It is endemic to Brazil and known from Humaitá , Amazonas , its type locality in Amazonas and from the Pará state .
Truncatella caribaeensis is a species of very small somewhat amphibious land snail with a gill and an operculum , a semi - terrestrial gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Truncatellidae , the truncatella snails or looping snails .
Baryglossa histrio is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Baryglossa of the family Tephritidae .
Dorstenia caimitensis is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Haiti .
Cryptantha intermedia is a species of wildflower in the borage family known by several common names , including common cryptantha , Clearwater cryptantha , and nievitas .
Abronia mellifera is a species of sand verbena known by the common name white sand verbena .
Buddleja × weyeriana is one of the more remarkable buddleja hybrids , the first crossing of an Asiatic species ( B. davidii ) with a South American ( B. globosa ) .
Pseudopezicula tracheiphila is a species of fungus in the family Helotiaceae that is found in Europe .
The genus Plecotus consists of the long - eared bats .
The Odacidae are a small family of fishes in the order Perciformes , commonly known as cales , and weed whitings .
Formotosena is a genus of cicadas from Southeast Asia erected by Kato in 1925 to accommodate the species Formotosena seebohmi which was previously placed in the genus Tosena .
Richtersius coronifer is a species of tardigrade of the family Macrobiotidae .
Chalceus is a genus of characins from South America , from the Orinoco and Amazon Basins , as well as rivers in the Guianas .
Ctenosaura melanosterna , commonly known as the black - chested spiny - tailed iguana , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Aeneator attenuatus is a species of sea snail or whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Loudetiopsis is a genus of African and South American plants in the grass family .
Avian sarcoma leukosis virus ( ASLV ) is an endogenous retrovirus that infects and can lead to cancer in chickens ; experimentally it can infect other species of birds and mammals .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pleophragmia leporum .
Acaena minor is a species of flowering plant whose range is confined to Australia 's subantarctic Macquarie Island and to New Zealand 's Campbell and Auckland Islands in the Southern Ocean .
Anisopodus curvilineatus is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by White in 1855 .
Gonolobus arizonicus , common name Arizona milkvine , is a species of plant in the Apocynaceae family .
Araneus is a genus of common orb - weaving spiders .
Cyperus trachysanthos is a rare species of sedge known by the common names pu`uka`a and sticky flatsedge .

The Chiroteuthidae are a family of deep - sea squid , generally small to medium in size , rather soft and gelatinous , and slow moving .
Cryptocoryne mekongensis is a species belonging to the Aroid genus Cryptocoryne that was described in 2010 .
The lightning whelk , scientific name Sinistrofulgur perversum , is an edible species of very large predatory sea snail or whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Busyconidae , the busycon whelks .
Aphaniotis is a genus of agamid lizards from Southeast Asia .
Rubus tholiformisis a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Elrathia is a genus of ptychopariid trilobite species that lived during the Middle Cambrian of Utah , and possibly British Columbia .

Hemiculterella is a genus of cyprinid fish that occurs in eastern Asia .
Thaumastus crenellus is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Megaspiridae .
Ophioblennius steindachneri , the Large - banded blenny or the Panamic fanged blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern Pacific ocean .
Sphagnum magellanicum , commonly called Magellanic bogmoss , Magellan 's sphagnum , Magellan 's peatmoss or midway peat moss , is a widespread species of moss found in wet places throughout boreal forests of North America , South America and Eurasia .
Pilularia globulifera , or pillwort , is an unusual species of fern native to western Europe , where it grows at edges of lakes , ponds , ditches and marshes , on wet clay or clay - sand soil , sometimes in water up to 30 cm ( 12 in ) deep .
Vaccinium oxycoccos is a species of flowering plant in the heath family .

Eucheuma denticulatum is a species of red algae and one of the primary sources of iota carrageenan .
Larimichthys crocea , called the large yellow croaker , the yellow croaker or the croceine croaker , is a species of marine fish in the Sciaenidae family ( croakers ) native to the northwestern Pacific , generally in temperate waters such as the Taiwan Strait .
Acer republicense is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a single fossil samara .

Clarkia epilobioides is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name canyon clarkia .
Nodosaurus ( meaning `` knobbed lizard '' ) was a genus of herbivorous ankylosaurian dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous , the fossils of which are found in North America .
Scoloparia is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile from the Late Triassic of Canada .
Monitor lizard is the common name of several large lizard species , comprising the genus Varanus .
Psorophora ciliata is a large species of mosquito indigenous to the United States east of the continental divide .
Peltula is a genus of small dark brown to olive or dark gray squamulose lichens that can be saxicolous ( grow on rock ) ) or terricolous ( grow on soil ) .
Aristida californica is a species of grass known by the common names California threeawn and Mojave threeawn .
Mystacocarida is a subclass of crustaceans , that form part of the meiobenthos .
Pseudobahia heermannii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names foothill sunburst and brittlestem .
Cristatosybra jeanvoinei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cristatosybra .
Peltodytes is a genus of beetle native to the Nearctic , Europe , the Near East , and North Africa .
Grania is a genus of marine annelid worms in the class Clitellata .
Hyantis consists of one species , Hyantis hodeva .
Saccoloma squamosum is a species of fern in the Saccolomataceae family .
Conraua derooi is a species of frog in the Conrauidae family found in Ghana and Togo .
Heliamphora ceracea is a species of marsh pitcher plant known only from the Brazilian side of Pico da Neblina in the Neblina Massif .
Ptychochromis ernestmagnusi is a species of fish cichlid only known from the Mananara du Nord River in northeastern Madagascar , but it is probably more widespread in that region .
Rhagoletis mendax is a species of tephritid fruit fly known by the common name blueberry maggot .
Huebnerius dux is a species of moth of the Noctuidae family ( owlet moths ) .
Searsioides is a genus of tubeshoulders native to the western central Pacific Ocean .
Coracistis erythrocosma is a moth in the Elachistidae family , and the only species in the genus Coracistis .
Auchenipterichthys coracoideus is a species of driftwood catfish endemic to Peru where it is found in the upper Amazon River basin .
Icefishes or noodlefishes are a family , the Salangidae , of osmeriform fish , related to the smelts .
Cyathea colensoi , also known as the Creeping Tree Fern , Mountain Tree Fern and Golden Tree Fern , is a species of tree fern native to New Zealand , from the southern part of the North Island south to Stewart Island .
Jatropha gossypiifolia , commonly known as bellyache bush , black physicnut or cotton - leaf physicnut , is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae .
Vernonia proctorii is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Proctor 's ironweed .
Polylepis pauta is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Rhododendron calendulaceum , the flame azalea , is a species of Rhododendron native to the Appalachian Mountains in the eastern United States , ranging from southern New York to northern Georgia .
Myotomys is a genus of African Karoo rats that inhabit the Karoo , a semi - desert region in the southern portion of the African continent .
Erigeron pulcherrimus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Basin fleabane .
Pristipomoides is a genus of snappers native to the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific oceans .
Burmannia capitata is a plant species widespread across the West Indies and much of Latin America .
Bauhinia acuminata is a species of flowering shrub native to tropical southeastern Asia .
Bats of the genus Pteropus , belonging to the megabat suborder , Megachiroptera , are the largest bats in the world .
Gyrinichthys minytremus is a species of snailfish from the northeastern Pacific Ocean where a single specimen was found once at a depth of 640 metres ( 2,100 ft ) near Unalaska island .
Abies sachalinensis ( Sakhalin fir ) is a species of conifer in the family Pinaceae .
Fuscospora solandri , commonly called black beech ( Māori : tawhai pango ) , is a species of southern beech , endemic to New Zealand .
Archaeolemur is an extinct genus of lemurs that includes two species , Archaeolemur edwardsi and A. majori .
Dasymetopa quinquepunctata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Dasymetopa of the family Tephritidae .
Gnaphosa stussineri is a ground spider species found in Greece .
It was described by N. V. Zelenkov and E. N. Kurochkin in 2010 , and the type species is Lophogallus naranbulakensis .
Pericopsis mooniana , the nandu wood or nedun tree , is a species of legume in the family Fabaceae .
Muhlenbergia montana , with the common name Mountain muhly , is a species of grass .
Oedilepia striginervella is a species of snout moth in the genus Oedilepia .
Uraeginthus is a genus of bird in the Estrildidae family .
Microcotyle is a genus which belongs to the phylum Platyhelminthes and class Monogenea .
Nebria spatulata is a species of brownish - black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the US state of California .
Riponnensia splendens is a small metallic species of hoverfly .
Fresnosaurus is an extinct genus of plesiosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( Maastrichtian stage ) of what is now California .
Lepidospartum squamatum is a species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common names California broomsage and scale broom .
Discula tetrica is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Elosuchus is an extinct genus of neosuchian crocodyliform that lived during the Early Cretaceous of what is now North Africa ( Morocco , Algeria and Niger ) .
Heliofungia actiniformis is a solitary species of mushroom coral , a large polyp stony coral in the family Fungiidae .
Freziera spathulifolia is a species of plant in the Pentaphylacaceae family .
Phytocoris ulmi is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Mirinae .
Ceriagrion cerinorubellum , commonly known as the orange - tailed marsh dart or bi - coloured damsel , is a medium - sized species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Hololeion is a genus of East Asian flowering plants in the dandelion family .
Coregonus baicalensis is a species of freshwater whitefish in the family Salmonidae .
Phyllostegia warshaueri is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Laupahoehoe phyllostegia .
Lepidocephalichthys guntea , the Guntea loach , is a species of cobitid loach native to southern and southeastern Asia .
Enypniastes is a genus of deep - sea sea cucumber .
The Sumatran tiger ( Panthera tigris sumatrae ) is a rare tiger subspecies that inhabits the Indonesian island of Sumatra .
The type ( and only known ) species is Loncosaurus argentinus , described by the famous Argentinian paleontologist Florentino Ameghino , but is considered a dubious name .
Nepenthes glandulifera ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˌɡlændjuːˈlɪfɛrə/ ; from Latin : glandis = gland , ferre = to bear ) is a species of pitcher plant endemic to the Hose Mountains of central Sarawak .
Eomola is an extinct genus of sunfish from the middle Eocene .
Syntripsa flavichela is a species of freshwater crab found in Sulawesi .
Succinea putris is a species of small air - breathing land snail in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Liparoceratidae is a family of eoderoceratacean ammonites from the Lower Jurassic that combines genera with a variety of forms including dimorphs that change from one form to another during ontogeny .
Starksia atlantica , the smooth - eye blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western central Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea where it inhabits coral reefs at depths of around 8 metres ( 26 ft ) .
Rosa wichuraiana ( syn . memorial rose , R. lucillae ) is a species of rose .
Herminium is a genus of plant in family Orchidaceae , widespread across much of Europe and Asia .
Gray 's grasshopper warbler ( Locustella fasciolata ) , also known as Gray 's warbler , is a species of grass warbler in the family Locustellidae ; it was formerly included in the `` Old World warbler '' assemblage .
Megophrys montana ( Asian horned frog , horned frog , Asian spadefoot toad , Javan horned frog , Malayan leaf frog ) is a species of frog found in Java and possibly Sumatra .
Bulbophyllum abbrevilabium , also known as the Short Lipped Bulbophyllum , is a warm - growing species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum .
The Jalisco mud turtle ( Kinosternon chimalhuaca ) is a species of mud turtle in the Kinosternidae family endemic to Mexico .
Philadelphus ( /ˌfɪləˈdɛlfəs/ ) ( mock - orange ) is a genus of about 60 species of shrubs from 1 to 6 m tall , native to North America , Central America , Asia and ( locally ) in southeast Europe .
Arixenia esau is a species of earwig , one of three species in the genus Arixenia .
Renanthera monachica is a species of orchid endemic to the Philippines .
Dendrorhynchoides was a genus of anurognathid pterosaur containing two species known from the Middle Jurassic Tiaojishan Formation of Qinglong , northern Hebei Province , China .
Tetrapturus is a genus of marlins found in tropical and subtropical oceans throughout the world .
Anemarrhena asphodeloides is a plant species in family Asparagaceae , subfamily Agavoideae , native to China , Korea , and Mongolia .
Oxyptilus scutifer is a species of moth in the genus Oxyptilus , known from Costa Rica and Ecuador .
Alcides agathyrsus is a species of day - flying moth of the Uraniidae family .
Mascelia ectophoea is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Mascelia .
Anadoras grypus is a species of thorny catfish the upper Amazon basin of Ecuador and Peru .
Thalassoma virens is a species of wrasse native to the reefs in waters around the Revillagigedo Islands ( though during El Niño years , it has been recorded from Baja California ) .
Anthrenus pimpinellae is a species of beetle found natively in `` Europe , northern Africa , Asia and portions of the Oriental region '' ; it has also been introduced to parts of North America .
Rhamphochromis is a genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
Calathus metallicus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Albania , Bulgaria , Greece , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Ukraine , all states of former Yugoslavia ( except Slovenia ) , and Near East .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Ormomyces clivinae .
Viola striata is a species of violet known by the common names striped cream violet and creamy violet .
Parabrimidius ovalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parabrimidius .
Diloma subrostrata , common name the mudflat top shell , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Barbus andrewi , the Cape whitefish or Berg - breede River whitefish , is a ray - finned fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Conus parius , common name the Parian cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Maxburretia is a genus of three rare species of palms found in southern Thailand and Peninsular Malaysia .
Chrysopsis linearifolia ( narrowleaf goldenaster ) , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Brachinus pectoralis is a species of ground beetle in the Brachininae subfamily that is endemic to Crimea .
Oxynoemacheilus leontinae is a species of stone loach found in Israel , Jordan , Lebanon , and Syria .
Monetaria caputdraconis , common name the `` dragon's - head cowry '' , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Cistecephalus is an extinct genus of dicynodont therapsid from the Late Permian of South Africa .
Anny Schlemm ( born February 22 , 1929 in Neu - Isenburg ) is a German operatic soprano , and later mezzo - soprano .
Mariska Aldrich ( March 27 , 1881 -- September 28 , 1965 ) was an American dramatic soprano singer and actress .
Romain Bussine ( 1830 - -1899 ) was a French poet , baritone , and voice teacher who lived during the 19th century .
Corrado Miraglia ( 1821 -- 30 December 1881 ) was an Italian operatic tenor and in his later years a voice teacher and theatrical agent .
Ashley Riches is a British operatic baritone .
Martha Angelici ( 22 May 1907 -- 11 September 1973 ) , was a French operatic soprano of Corsican origin , particularly associated with the French lyric repertoire .
Sonia Prina ( born 30 November 1975 ) is an Italian operatic contralto who has had an active career in concerts and operas since the mid-1990s .
Céline Scheen ( born 1976 in Verviers , Belgium ) is a Belgian classical soprano .
Štefan Hoza ( 20 October 1906 , Smižany--6 April 1982 , Czechoslovakia ) was a Slovak operatic tenor , actor , librettist , educator , music publicist , and historian .
Enrico Di Giuseppe ( October 14 , 1932 -- December 31 , 2005 ) was a celebrated American operatic tenor who had an active performance career from the late 1950s through the 1990s .
Jongmin Park ( born 1986 ) is a South Korean opera singer who has sung leading bass roles in the opera houses of Germany , Austria , and the United Kingdom .
Anna Chandler ( born July 4 , 1884 , New Cumberland , Pennsylvania - d. July 10 , 1957 , El Sereno , California ) was an American vaudeville actress and mezzo soprano singer of popular and light classical songs .
Maroochy Barambah is an Australian Aboriginal mezzo - soprano singer .
As a self - described `` split tenor '' ( between an alto and a tenor ) , Pete Seeger was a founding member of two highly influential folk groups :
Cécile Simonnet ( 14 March 1865 , Lille - ? , ) was a French operatic soprano .
Riccardo Massi is an Italian operatic tenor who had performed at such Italian theatres as both the Giuseppe Verdi Theatre and La Scala .
